reviews.text: Ordered brown rice with paneer makhani from Pishus four bunglow branch .Best veg dish ever had with exotic veggies in gravy with brown rice. the taste was truly delicious. Food was deliciously healthy.i assure if someone has love for continental and if they will have this dish they will surely love it and will recommend others to try.

Pishu's is a great place to have healthy food. 
Details of the food like it's calories and protein content are mentioned in the menu which helps you to keep a track on your calories and protein intake. 
Food is very tasty and service is very fast.
A healthy take on fast food. Really delicious, at the same time guilt free healthy food. Value for money

The outlet serves healthy food. They even have mamy detox juices. Check the menu for more details. They even have mentioned the tentative number of calories in their each dish.
.
I ordered the Burnt Garlic pizza. The base is replaced with multi grain cracker. You can even replace the cheese with paneer. The taste is awesome with burnt garlic taste and crispy cracker as it's base. This is something new. Must try.
.
Next ordered pasta garlic cheese - this is not for people who love cheesy white pasta. As it has many vegetables and it is not very cheesy. It is healthy pasta. Whole wheat penne pasta with broccoli, jalapeno, zucchini, olives etc. The pasta is accompanied by lavash crackers. Loved this too. Crispy cracker with white pasta :) :D
.
There are many seasonal juices too. They have even mentioned the benefits of the fruits used in the juice. Loved the concept of healthy food. Must try if you are health consious. :)

They offer healthy drinks and food. I ordered Green Effect juice and Hummus Platter. The juice was pretty good while the platter was below average. The salad and hummus did not taste great. 

I feel that some of the items in the menu are healthy for name sake. For example, they have healthy pizza on their menu. I have no clue what is so healthy about Pizza.

The service is pretty good. Waiting time is pretty low. Overall hygiene of the place is good.

Its a great place to have a quick refreshing fruit juices and shakes.

reviews.text:
Well while my favourite football team was getting beaten there was something saved my day...ofcuz it was Pizza but this made me forget my embarrassment. Ever since I'm in love with this outlet...
Something I love to order...

1. Double Cheese Margarita pizza
2. Smokey Joe Pizza
3. Tandoori Chicken Wing

Quality Pizza, delivered hot & fresh at your door-step.
Mojo  Pizza  is one of the delivery pizza joint that offer many different selections of fresh delicious pizzas .

So what did we have?
 
‚Ä¢ MEAT EATER (big 10 inch NON -VEG pizza)

If you are a meat-eater & you haven‚Äôt tried a Meat Eater pizza, then it‚Äôs safe to say you are missing out on something special. 
Loaded with Bbq chicken, Roast Chicken, Chicken Keema, Chicken Sausage to this pizza that you are sure to love.

‚Ä¢ FIRE ME UP (big 10 inch NON -VEG pizza)

Your best bet if you‚Äôre craving for some delicious Spicy Non Veg pizza.
Loaded with fresh cookedBBQ Chicken, Chicken Tikka, Spicy Jalapenos, Baby Corn, this pizza is juicy with every bite.
 
‚Ä¢ TEX- MEX SPECIAL (big10 inch VEG pizza)

 Loaded with Red Paprika, Golden Corn, Capsicum & veggies, richly flavorful  salsa sauce. The Tex - Mex vegetarian pizza is a must try for everyone.

Whoever wishes for more toppings and cheese in their pizza fear not coz Mojo Pizza is here.
MOJO pizza in the least year or 2 have gained quite a popularity among all the pizza lovers coz of promise of 2x toppings.

We had:
‚ñ™Ô∏èGarlic bread with cheese dip:
The garlic bread was made and baked well. The cheese dip went great with it. 

‚ñ™Ô∏èBbq Chicken Pizza:
7 inch pizza topped with BBQ chicken, corn and Jalapeno was made to perfection. The chicken was juicy and the cheese was amazing. 

‚ñ™Ô∏èClassic Pepperoni Pizza:
Generous quantity of cheese was topped with the pepperoni. It was tasty and delicious. 

‚ñ™Ô∏èButterscotch Blizzard:
New in their dessert menu so gave it a try and was not disappointed. It was very similar to a butterscotch cake and completed out whole meal. 

MOJO always delivers the pizza hot, fresh and on time. It is one of the best places for pizza cravings. 
They also have great offers that continuously goes on which is great.

Another bad experience with Mojo pizza's Instafresh not-at-all "zero contact delivery."

The delivery guy did not sanitize his hands before delivering the items. Mojo does not provide a bag anyways. And the choco lava cake he brought had spilled as it was lying clumsily at the bottom with onions and veggies on top of it. 

I make it a point to wash all the veggies received as they are all touched by hand. Do u expect me to wash the choco lava cake? 
This executive argued that he sanitized his hands at the store. But what about him touching the bike handle and ten other things on the way? 

I want an immediate call back and replacement. 
I am going to share this second horrible experience online on all possible channels (Twitter Facebook and wherever else possible). 

Enough is enough.

After many get together's,I have decided to take a break from every and pampered myself.Its all about me time.i had ordered pizza from Mojo and believe me they were amazing in taste.chicken wings were so juicy and spicy and garlic sticks are crispy and taste good with mayo.The toppings on pizza are very crisp and delicious.

reviews.text:
Krishna Restaurant

What we had
Murgh Musallam (Recommended)
Chicken Biryani
Chicken Crispy

Ambience : 3/5
Food :4/5
Value for money : 4/5

Krishna Restaurant , a a hidden gem in Bandra East for seafood ,non veg dishes aks Chinese cuisine!! The flavours are amazing here and quanity very filling!!
Coming to what I had :-
Rawas tikka :- This was a soft , extremely Delicious and spicy rawas tikka.The flavours were amazing and that masala was lip smacking!! Highly recommend this dish!

Prawns Rava Fry:-Fried Rava  King Prawns in generous quanity!! Prawns were crispy and very juicy and just loved the Prawns and rawa flavours!!Good enough for three people.Highly recommend!

Kungpao Chicken :- The smell of this dish was wonderful and so was the taste and quanity!!The kungpao sauce was just so amazing and very delicious!!! Chicken was juicy and soft and tasted amazing !

Surmai malwani fry :- This consisted of a medium sized Surmai cooked  in spicy red masala .The surmai was cooked  to perfection!! The Flavours were just Amazing!!Highly Recommend this malwani fried Surmai.

Prawns crispy :- This consisted of king Prawns cooked in red sauce with some Crispy sev which is usually served with soup.Loved the idea and it definitely worked in terms of flavours. Prawns was tasty and with that sev gave that lovely crispy and flavour to it!!

Mutton maratha gravy with garlic naan and missi roti :- This gravy was so appetizing and delightful!! Mutton was soft and pieces were quite good!! Curry was spicy and served hot.Tasted fabulous with garlic naan  and missi roti!! I liked garlic naan more ,it was yummy and lovely with that maratha curry!Highly Recommend this maratha Mutton curry

For desserts we had

Custard:- This was a lovely custard with a god consistency and texture.Jiggly and sweet it looked good.Tasted Yummy!
Rabdi :- This was one of the best rabdi I ever had.Had the perfect sweetness and texture!! Cold and lovely ended my meal on a perfect note!

Good food,but   below Average service, ordered for kebabs was told after 20mins that's not available,  suggested a different kebab which took a hour to come, had to wait for the order for more than hour hungry.  Killed our appetite for the food.

Recently visited Krishna restaurant in Bandra.food was too good there,i was looking for good restaurant I found this i order butter chicken and kebabs was too pretty.if you are looking for good Chinese Indian dishes this restaurant is perfect..guys to visit this place.....

AMBIENCE 4/5
SERVICE 5/5
STAFF 5/5

Awesome place. But they should maintain aquarium. I saw they don‚Äôt clean aquarium properly.
Had Kolhapur Vada Pav. It is delicious and worth trying it.

Cafe Hydro is such an outlet which really blows your mind off , the multi cusine restaurant really surprises you as soon as you step right in .
It's a 3 floor  restaurant, and each floor is dedicated to a certain theme .
The outlet in whole is Aqua themed.
So the ground floor is  themed after  Mumbai's lifeline i.e. Local trains .
Even the flooring is upon railway track.
And seating is designed like train seating the props are the rack where luggage is kept.
It is very detailed execution.
The first floor is about ocean ,Also what amazes here is that the walls here are of one huge fish tank , which just really makes it more beautiful. Its very lavish.
The second floor is garden theme, even this has fish tank in one side, but the seating here changes and there are cloth swings , various masks are stick on wall. The lighting and everything makes it so soothing. Cute seating area and whole concept makes it soo amazing!! 
It even has 3 different kind of seating.
Talking about the food , we had an amazing experience.

Here's what we had ?

üî∂ Dynamite :-

This was a 3 layered juice which had 3 different layers , and it was very nicely presented taste was also perfect and refreshing.

üî∑ Spicy Guava :-

This is our all time favorite mocktail but this was quite actually more spicy.

üî∂ Chicken Manchow Soup :-

The soup was great , it was spicy and also the chicken pieces were big enough. The flavor of ginger , garlic and chilly was strong , 
Only it was may more thick 

üî∑ Chicken Zaffrani Tikka :-

Pieces of chicken perfectly marinated and cooked , which had an amazing smoky taste is all you need as a perfect appetizer.

üî∂ Chilly Chicken Dry :-

Presentation of this was good , fried chicken pieces with an amazing marination tossed with a Little sauce and not loosing it's cripsyness. Taste was good it was spicy.

üî∑ Burnt Garlic Chicken Rice :-

This is usually our favorite item , but here it was tasting quite bitter in between. Quantity was very good .

üî∂Brownie with Ice Cream & Ice Cream:-

Brownie with ice cream is something which we always prefer and this is  best part of any meal it was really good , even we took only ice cream, 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream rich and full filling.

reviews.text:
The best part about this place is LIVE MUSIC. It is simply marvelous , multiple drinking option and it is vegetarian restaurant with quite Jain option available.. Live music is basically on weekends so plan it accordingly rest of the time DJ rocks.. it has multiple seating option as per your convenience.
I'm definitely going to visit this place again as the vibes about the place incredible.

Good Live music option restaurant with amazing food. I have visited twice this place. Once on valentines day when it was superbly heavily rushed thus not so good experience in food and staff treating customers. Second time it was all opposite, being moderately occupied they served amazing food. For foodies its worth trying and for live music hunters its worth visiting and chilling üòÅ

Visited Timess Square for the first time, and the first impression was pretty good... Off beat interiors, Huge infrastructure with 3 storied dining area, a fairly diverse menu, plenty of staff to look after you, good service... And most importantly, Tasty Food with Good Quantity!!! A good place to spend time with your family or friends.... Table reservation recommended since the restaurant is quite popular and buzzing with food lovers!!!

One of the best places in Borivali for some live music and great food. It has 3 sections out of which one is outside seating. They have a variety of dishes to choose from. Also, Zomato gold is applicable here.

It's good place for grabbing some good food and brunch! They have two facilities, a ac hall and open garden restaurant with live music. The band was awesome. Rates of food is bit costly but for the vibes you get here it's justifying. Also it's noticeable from the road in heavy traffic as well. It's good place for weekend evening getaway with good food and music.

¬†

The second dish we ordered was Italiano Pizza Fries...it was so cheesy...üßÄüßÄ ...quantity was also tummy filling..üçü¬† A must try!¬†

restaurants.address: 301,The Bombay Cartel, 3rd floor, Hubtown Skybay, Bhulabhai Desai Marg, near Mahalaxmi Temple, Mahalaxmi(W), Breach Candy, Cumballa Hill, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400026, India

reviews.text:
Bombay cartel is the place to visit if you want to have good drink. Long Island Tea was one of the best I have drunk anywhere. Other drinks like Fireball were beautifully presented. Russian Mafia presented in traditional copper mug was good too. In all the cocktails, the alcohol taste was subtle while the punch was still there.
Food wise the fare is ordinary to good, the cheese filled pakodas were good while the salad was barely passable, being too sweet.

The dessert was sinful and amazing to eat. Overall a great place to visit and have evening out.

The Bombay Cartel is located near the famous Mahalaxmi Temple. The name Bombay cartel itself give us a reach feeling about this restaurant. This restaurant is located inside a building where there are more restaurants on the other floors. This restaurant is located on the third floor of the building. This restaurant has a lift to go up to the third floor. As you enter to the third floor you will be in another world this place also has parking facility. The ambience of the place is too good this place have live bar facility so that you can order your drink easily and this place also play matches on a big screen so you can enjoy your drinks with your favorite match streaming live on a big screen. The staffs and the service of the restaurant is good they are good at their service special thanks to Mr. Prabhat and Mr. Priyatam this two steward did not gave any chance of disappointment they ware best at their service. Service was fast and quick the food they serve was just awesome it was fresh and hot also loved the drinks at place you should definitely try Cocktails at this place. And the biggest thing about this place is they serve some of the drinks on MRP which is really amazing. This place has everything you want. There was soft music played in the restaurant which really feels me comfortable. Coming to the food we had.

.

WHAT WE HAD

DRINKS

1)	Sex On The Beach

This was looking to good it was nicely presented and was garnished with orange on top of the drink. This drink was having orange flavor in it the taste was also good.

2)	Polish Cooler

This drink was a vodka base drink which was having cucumis juice and coconut syrup in it. The taste was good it was nicely presented not to strong not to mild it was just perfect.

STARTERS

3)	Charles Marbles

This was one of my favorite starters among both I loved the cheese feeling there was marble shape balls having schezwan over it the ball was soft and yummy.

4)	Voila Quesidilla

This was a pizza shape tortilla filled with cheese, kimchi, and avocado and heated from the top.

MAINS

5)	Paneer Tikka Masala

Paneer was soft and the taste of the masala was also good it was not much spicy loved this one it was served with butter naan

6)	Naan

The naan was also soft and was freshly made it was loaded with butter and was tasting good with paneer tikka masala

7)	Nasi Goreng Indonesian Style

This was nicely presented the taste of the rice was good it was hot and red in color this was something I tried for the first time.

Coming to the price.

PRICE

DRINKS

1)	Sex On The Beach = Rs355/-

2)	Polish Cooler = Rs450/-

STARTERS

3)	Charles Marbles = Rs425/-

4)	Voila Quesidilla = Rs465/-

MAINS

5)	Paneer Tikka Masala = Rs375/-

6)	Naan =Rs120/-

7)	Nasi Goreng Indonesian Style = Rs485/-

Taxis Will Be Applied On This Price

Best Place To Visit
Excellent service #excellent ambience#awsummm veg food #crazy desi DJ night on sat# friendly manager Mr.sanjay
Excellent place with great service and good food. Had a lovely evening with family. Lots of different varieties and all tasted good. The sizzlers are a must try

This is a very special venue I visited till date.

A venue situated in very top rated area of mumbai.

Breach Candy ,Yess I am talking about Bombay Cartel.This resto bar is very perfectly designed and the space management is been done beautifully and precisely.

The ambiance was perfect and ofcourse the food quality never seems to be compromised.

The staff response was very nice and the orders were on time with perfect recipe and love.

We had plenty of dishes there and we were totally satisfied with the quality we received.

We tried,

DRINKS

1. Peru Ceremolada

A very best in class mocktail served at the place with very little spice of guava and some spicy flavour around the glass.
The glass and the colour it exhibited was nice and appealing for photos .

2.Tusker

That's a cocktail served in very unique glass torred at its base but it looks very impressive and the taste was very nice.
I personally loved this one and will definitely recommend to try this one out anytime.

STARTER

1.Kung Pao Potato

Vegetarians always have plenty of varieties of dishes to try out, just we need to have a proper knowledge of dishes.
We discovered a very special dish here to be a must try one and to feel amaze.

2.Cigar Roll

Done get jumbled with the name though.
To be honest I thought something different but this dish came out on our table and after tasting it really made us feel like in heaven once again.
Fried cigars dipped in schezuan sauce really exhibited impressive taste and looks too.
Served in shots glass made it look even more wonderful.

Then we tried their main courses and those were,

MAIN COURSE

1.TRIPLE SCHEZWAN FRIED RICE

This was very special dish.
Simple looking and also made simple.
Not much spicy and really loved it's simplicity as I like it always
It really made my taste buds go crazy with its smell when we started taking photos.
I would definitely recommend this one.

2.Cheesy Shells Sushi

Personally I never tried this dish but tasting it here changed my mind one side.
This dish is quite an innovative to try here and the ingredients used were made so beautiful the whole dish came out very good looking though it has a unique taste.

Then at last we took desserts in hand.

DESSERTS

1.Deep Fried Oreos

This dessert is very special.The quantity and the quality was so best that we really love this dessert.
Different waffles were put in different dishes and in the middle, molten chocolate was kept.
The looks were very appealing and best in class.

2.Chocolate Fondue

This one is also very recommended dessert.
This place really amazes you with its taste in dessert and all recipes.
I really love the way they represented everything and decoration was first preference.

The staff was courteous and everyone was so good with us that we would love to visit here once again if possible.

reviews.text: Afzal restaurant is famous for it‚Äôs ‚Äúkepsa rice‚Äù.  Kepsa rice is a mixture of chicken fried rice and chicken tandoori. This rice also includes 3-4 boiled eggs along with some salad which includes carrot, onion and tomato. Instead of serving it in a plate or a medium sized utensil, they prefer to serve it in a big thali which gives you the feel of eating like a nawab or a Mughal. The kepsa rice is served in two proportions half and the other one is the full. Half kepsa is ample enough for serving 2-3 people while full on the other hand can easily serve 5 people.  They do have 2 sections ac and non ac. Ac section is located besides the restaurant and goes under the name of Mao Chinese centre.  Talking about the hygiene part, it is below average, so just in case if you‚Äôre looking for an hygienic place this is not the right place to be. Instead you can opt for takeaway option which is must better than eating at that particular restaurant. They do serve different types of deserts as well of which caramel custard is the best out of all the deserts served over here.

Recommended by my friend. Ordered triple rice n schezwan rice n chicken hakka noodles. One of the worst noodles I've ever had n both the rice were equally poor in taste. Fried noodles were soft n omelette was the worst prepared. I can get a better one on the roadside. Only saving grace was the boneless lollipop. I swear I won't order or dine here. Not recommended

but due to rush need to be improve fast service   which helps more sales & Profite.

reviews.text: Cozy ambience. Good music since it was not loud. Can have conversation with friends. Very good experience. Nice beer options. Liked the German one.

Quite happening place in Belapur. Ambience and the interiors are quite appealing. Talking about food the taste is nice. We really loved the Pizza and nachos.
Sometimes there is live music going on which just sets the good mood. Love this place!
Food-4/5
Staff-5/5
Ambience-5/5

It is inside a small shady Bhoomi mall with no parking. 
Went for a birthday. 
Got a table with a nice window and a nice view. 
The place is extremely beautiful on the inside. Loved the interiors. 

We asked them to reduce the volume as were seated right under the speakers and couldn‚Äôt hear each other at all but that didn‚Äôt go through at all. It was a Saturday night so the place was bustling with people so the volume never went down.
There was only 1 server/waiter for quite a few tables so we struggled a little with that. So service was slightly slow too. 
However the food made up for it. The food was great. 
We asked them to play Happy Birthday when they brought the cake but that didn‚Äôt happen either. So had a happy-sad experience there.
Good place for having a beer with friends even punjabi food is delicious one should must try it .

Came here for an office party and it certainly is a great place for the overall ambience it provides. The food is also quite good. A good place for both a small group as well as large one. 

Ambience: (4/5)
Opens out into a large opens space and there is a separate section available to the right after entry. There is a small stage that is there and a DJ section to the left after entering near the bar. There are limited toilets so when it‚Äôs a larger crowd this is something to be mindful about. There are many interesting design elements that make up the space. Some brilliant wall decor and lighting. 

Food: (4/5)
The buffet menu was extremely good. I was especially surprised by the quality of the fried rice. It had a really great flavour and just get light. The other dishes were also great, but nothing compared to the friend rice. The cake for dessert was also quite good, not too sweet, but still rich in flavour. 

Summary: (4/5)
Good place in Belapur to drop by with friends or office colleagues. It‚Äôs not too expensive and hence make for a good even especially if there is drinking involved. Do drop by and enjoy a good evening here.

reviews.text:
99 pancakes which is located in many places but i have visited fort outlet has it is near from my friend's home, as i have visited their. So after a long time decided to visit here to have a new flavours of desserts from here.

They have good Ambience. Also their interior decor was very well and they have good numbers of sitting arrangements.

They have installed good music system. 

I have ordered,

Exotica Pizza 
It is a regular size of pizza which costs around 130 with tax. The taste of the pizza was superb and the base was thin and properly cooked.

Dark and white chocolate pancake.
Comes with 6pcs of Mini pancakes with a chocolate loaded cream and with black and white choco chips toppings.

They have quick and fast service. Loved the staff behaviour and the way they have presented the desserts was excellent and worth.

They have taken all the safety measures. Staff were worn mask, gloves and head cover cap. 

They have parking for bikes and one car. They have only indoor sittings.

All over experience with 99 pancakes was superb and wonderful. 

Thanks for a amazing service.

Enjoyed ordering food from this dessert store.

I would recommend trying their waffle as they are soft as cotton, just the way I like them.

In the pancakes, they have a wide range of toppings, my personal favourite is the salted caramel and cream & jelly.

In Savouries they have very good pizzas, freshly made and served.

While eating you can see that the batter they use for each of these items is freshly made as it reflects on the food

Waffles and pancakes are mine all time favourite and during this time I missed them a lot, but all thanks to 99pancakes that they are up with their outlets.

Chocolate heaven waffle and KitKat waffle is what I love the most of this place they are amazing and I prefer them a lot, also the Paneer pizza is good with a crunchy base.

Also they are taking proper precautions and maintaining the social distance which is the most important thing. I am waiting to order soon again.

99 pancakes is the best place to have pancakes.
If you are looking to binge on pancakes and you are unsure where to head for some yummy ones 99 pancakes should be. 
A box full of hot pancakes with Nutella overload is true love. 
Each pancake i ordered was different from another, standing out with its unique taste. 
Valentine pancake was also so nice and yummy Nutella and whipped cream pancakes which turned out to be amazing in taste.

Absolutely Delicious pancakes and crepes. Tried the chocolate indulgence and it came in 6 small pancakes drizzled with crunchies and chocolate syrup that was just finger licking good.
Would definitely recommend 99 pancakes if you are craving a dessert delight!
The pizza was a good add on and they have quite a variety of unique dishes.
Waiting to try it out again.

reviews.text:
Ambience- 4/5
Service- 5/5
Food- 4.5/5
Pocket Friendly - 4.5/5
Overall - 4.5/5

Navratree Prasad is a vegetarian Fine Dine restaurant in Ghansoli.
This place can be easily sighted from outside Ghansoli Station.

Talking about the ambience, this place is thoughtfully designed to give simple yet spacious seating arrangements.  One of the wall that is covered with plates and bowls, looks impressive.

Being a weekday, the footfall was moderate, so fortunately we received a wonderful hospitality. They have ample staff to handle big numbers on any given day. For food we totally relied on our table captain. Right from the juices till the desserts, we loved almost everything we had.

Lets come to food now:
Off the mark, we started with juices. Ordered for Cocktail, Orange and Watermelon. All these were amazingly refreshing, but I would recommend Cocktail juice if one would like to have tangy and sweet taste. Also tried Sweet Lassi and Kesar Lassi, Sweet Lassi was yum and thick.

Next we headed to their soup section,
We ordered for Palak soup, Sweet corn soup and Manchow soup. Here, according to me, sweet corn and Manchow soup was nothing different from what we usually have at different places, but if you are a spinach lover, then definitely try creamy spinach soup.

Coming to the starters:
Here comes Paneer Koliwada, Spicy chilly Manchurian dry, Corn Palak Kebab, Mushroom Tikka and hara bhara kebab.
Spicy Chilly manchurian tasted well, the presentation was good, it was served in a wheat basket.
Mushroom Tikka was well marinated, very juicy from inside and delicious(Recommended)
But the spotlight was on Paneer Koliwada, everyone loved it that we asked for one more serving.(Recommended)

For the main course we ordered for Veg Maratha, Paneer Khurchan, Dal Makhani and Dal Tadka.
Dal Makhani was amazing. Paneer Khurchan was fine but Veg Maratha is a definite show stopper, perfectly spiced, flavourful and aromatic, loved it.

For the desserts we ordered for Rabdi with Gulab Jamun and Chef Special Dessert of the day.
Chef special was really special. This dessert was served in a fruit salad bowl, it had yummy brownie crushed along with dry fruits and fruits.( Recommended).

Overall the experience at this place was good considering that I am a hardcore Non-veg lover.
The menu is set Moderately priced. Will visit again for sure!!!!!!!!!

Pathetic uncooked food. I ordered rotis, garlic Naan, paneer pulav and paneer handi from navratree Prasad through zomato and the quality of food was very pathetic that me & my relatives remained empty stomach even after paying so much for the food. I would not recommend this restaurant to anyone. They provide the food which is totally uncooked and quality is very low. I wish they had a negative rating system then I would have opted for the same. Worst experience till date.

It's a very good place to hangout...The Ghansoli one which I visited is great...service is good...but takes time to deliver food.. otherwise, it's a very good place for family and friends..they have two portion in restaurant..one Bar and another family.
We were sitting in the A/C hall and there were so many flies around us while we were having our meal. That was looking untidy. And to be very honest, I don't feel like having meal after that.

Good ambience good service food quality was decent good amount of varieties price is little too high for the kind of restaurant it is.
Overall good experience but not the best I have seen.

reviews.text: Decent vegetarian food right at the Opera House junction. The Velvet Zucchini with Basil soup was excellent, the crispy Lotus Stems was also fairly good. The Green Thai curry lacked the genuine Thai flavour and was so-so. Prices are reasonable considering the quantity. Service was a bit slow

I had been passing by this place for a while now and it was after a long time that I finally made it to this one. When looking at it from the outside, it looks like the perfect fine dining place with just the right amount of elegance. However, once you step inside, it is more casual and less business like. I was here with a group of friends and we had quite a few things here.

We started off with the Avocado Toastie which was crispy and delicious. A base of toast with guacamole is essentially what it was. It was bite sized and tasted pretty good but it wasn't extraordinary. It was not something that you would get a craving for, in the middle of the night.

The Botanical Bloom Bread was a delight. A huge loaf of bread was buttered up and stuffed with molten cheese and a flavor of garlic. It was crispy and the cheese sauce was just amazing. Bread and cheese is something that one can't really go wrong with and it was perfect here.

We even tried the Crispy Lotus Stem. It was slightly sweet and sticky. However, it tasted okay. The stem became chewy very quickly and it wasn't at par with the ones that I have had but it was a good effort.

We went for the Veg Exotica Pizza. It was loaded with veggies as the description stated and it was crispy, spicy and delicious. The toppings were good and it was well balanced with the amount of cheese. When it comes to pizza, the proportion matters and the proportion for this one was completely right.

Lastly, we tried the Avocado, Asparagus and Cream Cheese sushi. It was put together well and rolled up in white sticky rice with a slightly crisp centre of the avocado and asparagus. It was served with soya sauce and wasabi. The taste was almost perfect but it needed a bit more binding when it comes to flavor.

The place is decent and worth a shot if you like the way it looks. They have some unique dishes on their menu which are really good. They could work a bit more on enhancing their flavors and it could surely be on my list of the places to visit!

Ambience: 4/5
Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5

Sometimes its so easy to move away from the norm. I visited botanica with a group of girl friends and suffice to say that we couldn't be happier.¬†
Brand new, Botanica is so ideally located near Girgaum Chowpatty. It offers no booze and no meat. That is where the beauty starts.
They have an extensive menu. Indian, asian, continental and even fusion.
All mocktails and drinks are made with natural ingredients. Blue Pea, rosemary,thyme ,jalapenos, black tea, mint, chopped fruits ,you name it and they have a great drink.
served in pretty glasses, the drinks all taste good. Since we were so many, we could order different drinks and taste almost everything on the menu.
We tried Mexican Tomato soup, Miso and Green Latte. My miso soup had shitake . Well made and light.
The Asian delight was glass noodles in a mason jar. The wow factor was the smoke. And the smoke was in the cold salad. Each element....even the sesame seeds was so well flavoured. try the Mushrooms and mango or watermelon and feta salad if youre not keen on keeping it fresh and simple.
Zucchini cheese rolls were nice.
The assorted savoury cakes were a take on the kothambir wadi...with broccoli, yam etc. SO well made and the fried garlic crumbs made it even better.
The icing on the cake was the Rajma Galouti. So well smoked and so well smoked. For a second, I almost thought it was keema.
So worth the calories. you Must try this.
We had a dumpling platter. The drama and the plating....full marks to the chef. I liked the mushroom dumpling the best.
The greek pizza was super. Thin, crisp semolina base, cheese and arugula. Adult taste and awesome.
The chilli bbq jack fruit and asian spiced paneer baos were nice. Im not too fond of baos, so I didnt have more than a bite.
The sushi burger was super jazzy to look at. And on point for the sushi rice. But the paneer could be substituted with a crunch factor. That paneer made it mushy for me.
The jack fruit biryani was fragrant and nice.
As was the makhani ravioli. Pretty ,pretty and super yum, and bang on sauce.
The pumpkin tortellini with foam was¬† nice.
Dessert... theer was a chocolate with lemon grass pudding. I didnt get any lemon grass taste , but because I was full already, I didnt really miss the dessert. The basundi with rose balls...basundi with rooh afza caviar was nice.

A lot of chatting, good food and good times. And we took loads of pictures that I had to share. Go here and try all the chefs and servers recommend. They know their food

Go to botanica for a good time with family and friends.

The most amazing and perfect place for all vegetarian. The Botanica!!!
Nice and cosy place to have a perfect meal. The Botanica is located in cherni road, and its 10 minutes walking from the cherni road railway station. The place can be easily located on Google map as well.

The has really nice and cosy Ambiance with really cute sitting arrangement. The round tables, sofas and amazing dining experience. They also have different country clock displayed just to have a feel of international cuisines. The ambiance is really calm. The best part about the Botanica is their hospitality and lip smacking food. They have sitting capacity of around 80-100 people. The food can be at your table within 5 to 6 minutes after ordering.

The classy Ambiance and delicious food with super friendly and humble staff makes this place perfect for a meal with a family and friends. In the menu, around 90% of the dishes can be made jain.

We tried,
Mocktails: their range of Mocktails are really refreshing and amazing. As per their recommendation we tried Botanical martini, Miss mary. And bang on both were really amazing. The taste of jalape√±o in martini was coming out well, the smoky flavor was good in miss mary. Overall both were really refreshing. 

Mexican tomato soup: A perfect start of a meal was a soup. All the flavors were coming out really nicely. The spicy, the tangy, little sweet. A perfect which can increase your craving. The soup had nachos and beans. A must try soup. 

Corn cottage cheese seekh: the kabab was perfectly cooked. The smokey flavors along with the flavor of corn and lots of cheese. The kabab was served along with cabbage and bell pepper salad and mint chutney. This was not that spicy. But was really soft. 

Asian spiced cottage cheese: again a perfect apittizer.. The rich red gravy of cashew and tomatoes along with small dices of cottage cheese and bell pepper. The perfect in taste and texture. The cheese was marinated properly and the balance flavors along with the drink was pure heaven. 

Arancini cheese poppers: this was something new in arancini. The cheesy poppers along with the salsa sauce and cheese cream. The best presented dish. The perfectly cheesy balls going well with the tomato salsa. 

In main course we wanted to try their kofta, as it was suggested by the staff. The kofta had a rich red thick gravy along with the Indian spices. The kofta was made-up from paneer and herbs. The quantity was sufficient. And can be eaten with Roti or biryani. We had missi roti, tandoori roti and Nawabi biryani.

The biryani was really rich and royal. The flavors were really amazing. Little more spicy then expected, but tasted really well. The rice was cooked properly and was not dry. The veg biryani lovers must try this here. the Indian herbs has enhanced the taste of the biryani. 

The last segment was THE DESSERTS 
Tiramisu: the mascarpone cheese along with vanilla cake and a strong flavor of coffee. This was mesmerizing and amazing. The taste was good. Coffee had a strong flavor in this dessert. Also, 

Melting chocolate cake: a melting lava cake was served along with the butterscotch ice-cream. The preparation was really like a melting chocolate. A dark flavored chocolate was just perfect and mouthwatering. 

Gold dust Cappuccino: Heard of this, but never tasted before. The Golden sprinkle on Cappuccino. This has made our meal. The edible sprinkle was garnished on the Cappuccino. The strong Cappuccino had a great taste along with the creamy milk. A must must try drink.

Overall had a great time with family. The staff has made our meal a great meal. Special thanks to @live_life_royal for amazing meal experience.

Botanica cafe and dinner is in girgaum opposite opera house near Chowpatty. Ambience was quite good and awesome. 

We ordered

1. Fruity flavoured beer. 
2. Watermelon and basil spritzer. 
3. Greek pizza. 
4. Stuffed mushrooms. 
5. Asian spiced cottage cheese. 
6. Crispy lotus stem. 
7. Chilli cottage cheese baos. 
8. Tiramisu. 
9. Melting chocolate cake. 

Ambience service food 5 on 5

The ambience is decorated beautifully. The place is cool. Location is great too. It is located opposite central mall. Everything we had was delicious. Dishes were unique and tasty with good quantity. Hygiene was well maintained. Nyc staff and service.

KASBAH GRAND 

SEATING ARRANGEMENT & SERVICE ( 4/ 5 )
Located at top floor or I would say the rooftop area of chandiwala arcade, Goregaon west;  grand kasbah serves some authentic  dishes which includes the asian varieties, arabic, mughlai, indian. In Mansoon, its covered but on other days you can enjoy the lively atmosphere of rooftop. Has great decor and comfortable seating arrangement. This place don‚Äôt serves alcohol so you have to go with mocktails only. Staff were quite helpful and would help you on selecting your orders. Vallet parking is available but its at owners risk. 

We started with, 
Mocktails 
BLUE ALASKA:  ( 4 /5 )
It's a blue coloured drink. with a lot of crushed Ice.

GUAVA MARRY: ( 4 /5 )
guava juice with a twist of chat masala.

SUMMER DELIGHT:  ( 4 /5 )
a mix of orange juice along with cranberry juice

STRAWBERRY PUNCH: ( 4 /5 )
its was a milk-based drink with a flavour of strawberry.

QUEENS PUNCH: ( 4.5 /5 )
mild sweet orange juice with cranberry at the bottom.

BROWNIE OVERLOADED MILKSHAKE: ( 4.5 /5 )
It's a thick shake with milk and crushed brownie

We ordered some appetizers 
 
KOWLOON SPINACH WRAPPED CHICKEN : ( 4.5 /5 )
Chicken pieces wrapped with Spinach leaves and prepared with inhouse spices. Its tossed with chopped ginger and garlic. You get 7-8 pieces and tastes great.

LUCKNOWI SEEKH KEBAB: ( 5 /5 )
Our all time favourite, lukhnowi mutton seekh kebab. This would just melt in mouth. Served oved the sizzler plate.
 
MURGH TANDOORI KASHBAH: ( 4 /5 )
Unlike the traditional tandoori, here this is first tandoored to perfection and then is tossed in schezwan gravy. Chicken pieces were tender and its a spicy dish. 

SMOKED MACHLI: ( 4 /5 )
The dish is presented on Sizzler plate with silver foil covering with charcoal placed at middle & is surrounded with the Basa pieces . 6 pieces of Basa is marinate with turmeric based spice and is smoked to perfection. Few might not prefer the taste but as it has the hint of charcoal. 
  
CHICKEN WITH CASHEW NUT AND CORRIANDER : ( 4.5 /5 )
Boneless chicken pieces tossed along with Cashew nuts, Yellow - red Bell Peppers , Onions , Chopped ginger and garlic along with celery leaves. Its just amazing and something new. 

MURG DAHI LASOONI: ( 4.5 /5 )
Chicken Pieces marrinated with Curd, along with mixture of spices and Ginger garlic. Its then tandoored to perfection. Garnished with Lasooni dahi. Served over the sizzler plate. Superb taste.

PRAWNS KING TEMPURA: ( 3 /5 )
Deep Fried Prawns with a coating of Flour. The prawns tasted good but the coating was not cooked properly. Served with 7 pieces along with Mango chilly mayonise dip. A bit disappointment. 

THAI FLAVOURED GRILLED FISH: ( 4 /5 )
A Thai based preparation of Basa fish. The fish is marinated with spices and grilled. Garnished with Tangy Thai sauce. 6 pieces are served.

BALINESE BARBEQUE CHICKEN: ( 4.5 /5 )
Boneless chicken pieces without any coating is shallow fried and is tossed in balinese sauce. Placed over banana leaves and is served along with grated cabbage salad.  

In mains,
We tried the mains with Steam rice and Naan.
GOSHT PATIYALA: ( 5 /5 )
Absolutely wonderfull. Presented over miniature Flat tawa ; this dish is prepared with tenderised lamb pieces along with inhouse spices. This is a dry masala type dish. The prepared dish is Placed over a omelet & is served. A little disappointment in terms of portion size.
 
KORIYA PRAWNS:  ( 5 /5 )
The best prawns gravy one can ever try . A medium spicy Gravy which goes best with plain rice of Steam rice. With hint of coconut & spices, the dish just makes you more hungry. Portion size is good for 2 person.

SHREADED CHICKEN WITH GINGER ONION SAUCE :  ( 4.5 /5 )
Long slices of shreaded chicken prepared in ginger onion sauce along with yellow, red and green bell peppers. Garnished with spring onion leaves. Portion size can be shared among 2.

Finally,

In desert we had

KESAR FIRNI: ( 5 /5 )

GUL BAHAR SHAHI TUKDA: ( 5 /5 )

We tried-
Adraki
Sangria
Fruit Shoot
Chicken Seekh Kebab
Jalapeno Cheese Bites
Spaghetti
Chocolate Hazelnut Fondant

Yeda Republic in Juhu is undoubtedly one the quirkiest clubs in town. I've been a frequent visitor here and I've had one hell of a night every single time I've visited this place. They've come up with this new beautiful entrance which is decorated with golden fairy lights. They have a huge green wall opposite the entrance as its selfie point. Yeda Republic is an evil styled lounge bar with space suits and dark alleys. The lounge bar is located underground in the basement with Carribean flags with life like props wearing space suits, gas masks and respiratory pipes while you walk your way down. They have huge a jeep like structure located right in the centre where cute little staff members dressed up in spacesuits dance during weekends. Dark zones, Gas chambers, Ceiling with human bodies strapped with masks, ropes, jute bags, tunnel-like entry to the restrooms, waiters dressed like prisoners in orange one-piece suits are some of the traits of this lounge. The bar counter is clearly the highlight of this place with large cylindrical pipes which drop down from the ceiling and houses the Bar Bottles, for the rest of the display. They also have a fancy telephone booth with 5 ancient telephones. Talking about the food, the menu is a little compact when it comes to food. One thing they could work on is their menu. They have a wide bar menu but only 4 mocktails and 3 desserts in all. Also, I'd recommend y'all to place your order for maincourse and desserts along with the appetizers itself as they take a while to prepare the food.

We'd ordered :
In Mocktails :
1. Fruitshoot - Mixed fruits blended with sugar and vanilla ice-cream. The taste was good. If you like your drink sweet, you can opt for this one.

2. Lipstick - This is a tiny glass of mocktail having a very attractive red colour consisting of orange, mint, cranberry juice and peach crush.

In Cocktails :
1. Bloody Mary - This is our all time favorite, red colored spicy cocktail which will surely get you in the mood.

In Appetizers :
1. Cheese Corn Nuggets - Seven pieces of nuggets having melted cheese, corn and capsicum in its filling served with a dip. They are medium spicy in taste. 

2. Chicken Lollipop - Six pieces of chicken legs served with green chutney. They have a tangy taste. 

In Mains :
1. Chicken Sphaghetti Pasta with Pesto Sauce - They have three options in pasta base, ie. Sphaghetti, Macaroni and Penne Pasta. We'd opted for Sphaghetti Pasta in Pesto Sauce with chicken as its add on. It's served with two long garlic breads, garnished with cheese and black olives.

2. Chicken Makhani Pizza - This is a thin crust pizza which has Makhani sauce in its base topped with chicken pieces and cheese.

In Dessert :
1. Paan Falooda - I'm a huge paan lover so went for this one. This a satiating glass of falooda with paan syrup, jelly, almonds, cashews and french vanilla ice-cream.

reviews.text: A restaurant and bar situated in palm water club, kalyan, with great ambience and food. I went here with my family we were around 13 people. The food is good.. But service is bit on slower side..we went here for dinner. Price is on higher side.. Its better if you call them and reserve the table, especially on weekends.

Well, it was a favorite for our family until recently. The food quality had been going downwards but our last visit on Sunday, Jan 26 was an ultimate low. The restaurant is under renovation so we were asked to sit out in the garden accompanied by stray cats, hoards of mosquitoes and flies. I don't know what was worse, the sound and smell of flies and mosquitoes being electrocuted right at our table or smell of mosquito repellent or the pieces of coal in our nan or the stale paneer or the cold chicken soup. Eventually, I suffered from food poisoning, my brother had severe acidity. So yeah, it was an ultimate letdown. Just stay clear out of this one. There are better places available If you wanna spend a premium price for a dinner with fowl and flies around you. 2 stars just because it used to be nice in the past.

reviews.text:
Tea Villa Cafe in Kandivali has a far more vibrant setup as against the more traditional one.
F&B perspective, stays true to it's standards & delivers quality!

The new menu and new dishes added to the tea villa menu are really good. Not just that but the summer menu is good too. They come up with these seasonal menus which is excellent.

Tried a couple of dishes here from the summer and the new menu. Loved a few.

Do try the Sichuan Sliders. They were delicious. Crisp patty, spicy sauce.. one lipsmacking slider. The noodle bhel salad accompanied was to die for.

The potato wedges were crisp and delicious. Loved the seasoning.

Crispy cracker mousse from the summer menu.. creamy smooth Mushroom mousse and spicy guacamole topped over a crisp cracker. It was quite good. A balance of textures..  creamy, spicy, crispy and smooth.

Power protein salad from the summer menu.. this salad was delicious. Loved it. Chickpeas, Arugula, almonds, edamame and quinoa with a super delicious dressing.

Red and black combo from summer menu.. Manipur edamame black rice served with a coconut based chickpeas and Vegetable curry. This dish was delicious and healthy.

Sweet curd with mango .. from the summer menu.. a delicious yougurt with mango sorbet..I quite liked this one.

Chocolate Churros... Oh so good. Loved them. Do try!
Big fat churros drizzled with dark, milk and white chocolate and served with more Chocolate sauce.

Paneer Makhani sizzler... This one was decent..but my least favourite since I'm not a Makhani fan. The pulav was delicious. The paneer was melt in the mouth soft.. the gravy was a little sweet for my liking.

Cottage cheese rolls with Crunchy oats... These could have been better. The cottage cheese and the sauce within was delicious but the outer skin can be worked on.

Kashmiri kawah/twings and berries.. both the teas were good.

Overall a good experience.

If you are looking for a restaurant serving authentic, good Local Non Vegetarian and Vegetarian Delicacies from Andhra Pradesh then Aavaky is the Great Choice!
Great Hospitality, Comfortable Seating Arrangements, Decent Interiors, Cool and Clam Ambience, Very Neat and Clean Premises, Hygienic Cooking Practices and Truly Authentic Andhra Food are some of the major reasons for The Foodies to visit here time and again!
Do Try Their Legendary Miryali Rasam, Drumstick Sambar, Mouthwatering Aavaky Vegetarian Biryani, Delicious Chicken 65, Andhra Royyalu Prawns Pulao, Andhra Mamasam, Bhendkaky Peanut Vepudu, Andhra Parathas and Many More!
If time permits, don't forget to taste their Signature Authentic Andhra Thali Meals which is available only during Lunch Time in the afternoon!

A fine dining resturant in Kandivali food hub-Thakur village. Aavakay-The Andhra Kitchen as the name implies specializes for authentic Andhra cuisine. It is one of its kind place for fine dining.

Location/Ambiance: It is conveniently located considering crowd from Inox multiplex and foodies of Thakur village. Ambience is classy with luxurious confortable sofas. It is divided into compartments separated by pillars. Soothing background music adds to the experience.

Menu: They provide 4 different spices and 2 pickles which enhances the dining experience. They also give complimentary fried kurkure. Really crispy and in good portion.

Analysis-
> Mirapakay baji -
Mirchi pakoda stuffed with onions, tomato and chilli powder. I sprinkled some of the add on masala served alongside. They really enhanced the taste and flavour.

> Lemon coriander soup-
Diced veges simmered in veg broth. Consistency was thick and tastewise really good.

> Masala wada:
Deep fried wada made of chana dal and mix of spices. Wadas were sumptuous, fluffy and crunchy on oustside. Aftertaste was spicy. Highly recommended!

> Drumstick sambar-
Popular South Indian dish- cooked with toor dal, chopped onion and tomatoes. Drumsticks were properly cooked. Really delicious, flavorful and healthy sambar.

> Tomato rice-
Masala rice made with tomato, onion, dal and spices. It was slightly spicy but taste extremely good. Comfort food.

Overall this place can be visited for quality family fine dine experience. Definitely vising in near future to try their non veg food and other dishes.

reviews.text: A mind blowing place with value for money. Service is very quick and the quality remains super fresh and healthy. Pizza which is generally supposed to be a junk food, seems healthy with the kind of vegetables added to the pizza. The macaroni too has a homely touch to it which is loaded with gravy and the quantity is more than enough for 2.
good stuffed pizza.. i wish the place had good seating ambience nd some mild music... anyways food is good
Taste was too good.. little delay in service, yet worth waiting for it.. it's a good place for group of 7-8 friends at a time..

The place is too small and won't be that appealing, but the taste you get is tooo good and highly unexpected. So I ordered a Mexicana spicy chicken pizza and a veggie overload as a part of medium combo offer which comes with garlic bread and cold drink. Garlic bread is worthless but both the pizzas were superb and it's too filling. Toppings are added graciously over here. The cheese burst add-on is definitely a must have. No complaints for pizzas, only cheese garlic breads needs to be improved. Packing is nice and proper. Time taken to prepare and deliver is proper.
We ordered pizza many times from this place. Spicy chicken tikka pizza is really very tasty but problem is with packaging only.

reviews.text: Most restaurants are nowadays not delivery the food cause of high number of COVID 19 but Box8 DM's are doing superb job in delivering the food During lockdown you will not found any Quality and Quantity issue
Great food for students and people who live away from home. Chicken biryani is good too.

If you are coming late from the office around 12:00 Am and your wife has not cooked anything or because of the uninvited guest, the food is over then you can order from the Box8 and you will get the Fresh and Real Desi food within 30 minutes
Which containers and Boxes they are using trust me its fully air tight container. Good packaging ever in food chain industry this restaurant use Biodegradable plastic which is good for environment

The place is located in the film city road. It is a delivery kitchen...
They have great and best options available here for vegetarians and non vegetarians...
It is well known for north indian food and Biryani. They also have sandwiches, paratha wraps, desserts available here...
I love their fusion box the most and i have mentioned 3 fusion box which i had...
I ordered my food from here and the food was prepared and delivered before time which is a good sign...

We had 3 curries..
Daal Makhani is the one you should definitely order from here. The amount of makhan in it was perfect, and the perfectly cooked and absolute amount Red Kidney Beans and Whole Black Lentils making the dal makhni astounding...
I also had "Amritsari Chole Curry" and "Kadhai Paneer Curry". Both were perfect to order and good in taste. The pieces of paneer in Kadhai Paneer Curry was perfect the only problem was the amount of spices in it was too much...
All the above curries were served with a green chutney and onion salad...

We had 3 fusion box....
They serve salad, curd, rice, green chutney and curry in it...
I had "Dal Makhni Rice", "Dilli Wale Rajma Chawal" and "Paneer Makhni". Dal makhani rice box and rajma chawal box are amazing.... Paneer Makhni box is also nice, but gravy in it is in less amount. Else the taste was perfect...

Dal makhni 5/5. (must order)
Amritsari chole curry 4/5.
Kadhai paneer curry 4/5.
Dal makhni box 5/5. (must order)
Dilli wale rajma chawal box 5/5.
Paneer makhni box 4/5.

reviews.text: Nice place to visit and to have a good time spend. With family and friends. Mostly events are managed over here and they have special lounge for parties. The place is very friendly and even staff is curtious. Nice place to go for a date. Nice place do visit once

'Keiba' the Jap name points to horse race, as located at Mahalaxmi, and highlighting the horse stable in the outlet.

Cuisine- Pan Asian
Service/Category/Style- Family-friendly/Bar/Casual Dining
Ambience- Lively, Ambient Lights, Live counters
Staff- Courteous but inarticulate and not well-trained
Well Known for- Sushis, Live prep

The spacious outdoor and indoor seating areas, high-octane bar and chic d√©cor are eye-catching and exude a warm vibe. The hard rock music suits well with the decor of the outlet. The menus are exhaustive and there is a separate one for vegetarians and non-vegetarians. Apparently in the kitchen too, the sections are strictly divided. The bar menu is equally an exercise in choices. The food here is replete with fresh, high-quality ingredients, yet all dishes do not hit the right spot. It is the service here which mars the dining experience as the staff is inarticulate and not well-trained.

Our orders:
- Chilli Chicken (balanced spice)
- Chicken Dimsum
- Prawn Dimsum
- Crab stick Sushi (winner, with the juicy fresh crabs)
- Stir fried Noodles with Chicken
- Pineapple Piscour (best cocktail of the day)
- Red Wine Sangria
- White Wine Sangria

‚Ä¢ Overall - 4
‚Ä¢ Food - 4.7
‚Ä¢ Atmosphere - 4.5
‚Ä¢ Service - 4
‚Ä¢¬†Value - 4

Keiba has been a very interesting location for all to dine in the cosy relaxing atmosphere with those Horses around in their stables, is considered the charm of this place and it doesn't stink at all.
There are quite appealing live prep counters for Dimsum, Mongolian, Wok. They need to work on the service, as the staff needs a touch of training to make it a wonderful dining experience for it's customers.

Do visit for your own Foodie Experience
And for more follow us on IG @_quintessential.foodie_

Amazing ambience & yummy food! Staffs are very friendly too. A must visit if you love horses & racing! 
Definitely a value for money :)

reviews.text:
Considering the lockdown and takeaway situation, I wasn't expecting too much from Joey's this time round. But I am so glad that I had a surprisingly amazing experience with the takeaway! We had ordered beforehand and reached there post half an hour to collect our order, I think it was a wise choice to do so because the place was crowded. Luckily for us, our order was ready when we reached and it made a lot of difference since we didn't have to stand amongst the crowd and could stay socially distant too! 
We ordered cheese garlic bread, plain cheese pizza, garden fresh pizza and veg supreme pizza. All were hot and fresh and absolutely yummy! Would recommend you to pre-order in case you're doing a takeaway.

This place has some of the best pizza in town. They have a vast variety in both veg and non veg pizza. The staff is also polite an help us is choosing the perfect pizza. The price is reasonable and the quantity is also enough. Also, it has another outlet in Andheri. My all time favourite place. Surely a must visit place for all pizza loversüòç

Very famous for pizzas in the suburbs.
Currently serving only takeaways due to lockdown guidelines.

Average delivery time on weekdays is 30-45 minutes, weekends 45 minutes to an hour.

China gate and chicken tikka pizza in cheese burst are must haves.

Chicken garlic bread is also awesome.

Slightly on the pricier side but bang for buck!
Mouth watering varieties, doesn‚Äôt cheap out on toppings, fresh veggies, very hygienic and polite staff.

I also ordered a fruit punch to set my mood, which was classic, tasty! But nothing new in the drink menu. For main course I ordered Chicken Patiyala, and I have to say that it was the most uninteresting looking dish I have had. Chicken patiyala consists of a base of chicken stuffed omelette which is topped with a great tasting gravy. But here at neel Kamal, it was just a plain chicken curry and they topped the whole subzi with a huge omelette. A delivery kitchen with a dine in option, we tried Indizza Delivery Kitchen, Peddar Road.
Quaint, little outlet with an open kitchen for the customers to get an insight into the cooking, it was a lovely experience. 
We chose to order the Basil Mushroom Spinach and Cheese starter along with Chicken Achari Tikka. The mushrooms were heavenly and left us salivating for more! The chicken was spicy and a little salty due to the flavour combination of acchar but definitely succulent. 
Jumping onto our absolute favourite Butter Chicken, we decided to pair it with Chilli Cheese Naan and Stuffed Chur Chur Kulcha. The gravy was creamy and sweet, great quantity with bite sized pieces of chicken which we loved! More so the naan with the perfect amount of cheese. The kulcha could be savoured all by itself with the masala stuffing. 
We would absolutely suggest this place for a wholesome and happy meal!

I have always been a big fan of Indizza - The Delivery Kitchen ever since it opened in Worli! Had ordered for food from there and was really impressed! Was excited to hear that they recently opened a delivery and takeaway outlet near Vama, Kemp's Corner Flyover, Pedder Road! And finally I decided to visit this new one.

First thought, I would do a takeaway, but there is space for about 6 to 8 people to sit and eat at the outlet. So thought might as well do that! This outlet delivers to places in the radius of 4 kms or so, which means pretty much entire of South Mumbai. Indizza serves North Indian food - Appetizers, Rolls, Curries, Dal, Rotis and Desserts! In short a wholesome meal. They have reasonable amount of Veg and Non Veg options which I believe would cater to all.

Talking about what all I tried at Indizza -

We started with few starters - Bharwaan Mushroom Tikka, Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka and Aloo Achari Tikka. I would personally recommend these starters in the same order. Mushroom Tikka is too good, lipsmacking! In case one doesn't prefer mushroom, then one should go for Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka, there are other options as well in Paneer Tikka. Paneer was soft and all appetizers came along with Pudina mint chutney and some onions. Aloo Achari lacked the taste though.

We ordered for some drinks. Besides the regular soft drinks they serve Nimbu Pani and Pudina Nimbu Pani! Nothing fancy about it and the drinks were also served in basic bottles, but effective and refreshing taste to go along with the food!

Next from the rolls section, we ordered the Paneer Makhani Roll, wrapped neatly in an aluminium silver foil. Rolls are served in tandoori or Roomali roti! We had this roll in Roomali Roti. Yummy, the filling was too good, roti cooked well. No complaints at all. Would recommend people trying rolls as per their likings and preferences.

Moving to the mains, we ordered for Dal Makhani, Paneer Tikka Masala. From the Rotis, I was really excited to try the Truffle Cheese Naan. Naan was cut in a way Pizza is cut. Stuffed with regular cheese flavoured with Truffle. Truffles have garlicky flavour and a peculiar aroma. I personally loved it, some may feel it to be pungent. So please use your discretion. For me Truffle Cheese Naan was the Highlight or Star of the evening! Dal Makhani creamy - rich - thick, perfect in taste. Paneer Tikka Masala adequately spiced and rich in flavour! What an awesome meal.

Finally turned to desserts, tried the Gooey Chocolate. Served in a basic container, but loved the chocolate crumbles and topping on fresh swedish chocolate cake! Divine and perfect way to end!

I am happy, that I decided to have my meal there rather than takeaway. Liked the overall experience, staff was courteous, Mr. Vijay was helpful! Would recommend all, do try Indizza, definitely worth every penny that you spend!

reviews.text: Rooftop is good with an open bar and a large projector screen for sports matches. The lower floors are really shady and the possibilities of you passing out on the floor are greater than normal due to the pitch black lighting.

This place is awesome. This is open roof place. The food here is simply awesome. Just the service is bit bad. U can try food whatever you want veg or non veg both are equally tasty. We tried few starters here all were very good in taste and they were served really nice. Ambience is very nice. Music is good and relaxing. The only think we doesn't like is the people who smoke because it makes uncomfortable.

Great place to have a party. Good ambience and well maintained. Great staff which gives a quick response. The food is well prepared. The drinks menu has variety and is affordable. The Sound system is great and the light is same. Sitting area is also nice. Great place. Starter and food takes less time to get served. Three layers of area including sitting, dancing and Smoking area as well. This place also has a parking spot which is the main thing a bar has to have.

AMBIENCE:

The entrance is quite cool with posters and frames on walls. The graffiti on walls are very attractive. The lightings are not as good for taking pictures. Overall its good.

FOOD: 

The quality of food as compared to the amount we are paying is too low. Even the taste was not as good as other bar provides. They usually takes time to prepare but the wait isn't worth. 

BAR:

The bar has good menu options with various types of alcohols been served. The beer quality doesn't fit with your regular taste. I was not feeling like having it. So think before ordering.

SHEESHA: They have herbal sheesha. Mostly it doesn't create much smoke but is good as compared to other sheeshas.
They have an hour limit for each pot. It was nice.

PRICE:

Everything is overpriced plus additional taxes are imposed. A small redbull can costed us around ‚Çπ220. All other food items were heavily charged. For no taste we paid excessively high amount. Totally dissatisfied with their pricing system. 

SERVICE:

Service was very prompt and the persons were very polite and well mannered. They obeyed properly and served professionally. 9/10 for them. 

Overall experience:

First of all, the main factor is price and food. I was disappointed by both. There was no proper taste or flavour in food. Paying more for those were other issue. So, I don't recommend anyone to go here unless it's urgency for you. There are several more in area which gives best service.

Over all drinks and food, both are great in this place.
It's a must visit place for weekends.

Mumbai is known for street food and pav bhaji is one of the most popular dishes here. Nearest station is Mumbai Central. Located at Tardeo. Place is very famous and very small as well, I waited for almost 30min outside in queue and 15 min to get my order and offered seats on sharing basis, no customer service ! Make sure  you have enough free time as there you may face a long queue and waiting time . The service may seem a little bit slow Just because of the crowd but the quality of the food is graet . No  Ac . Tables are very congested can't even sit and eat with comfortable posture, but taste is wow ! Sardar is very old outlet dating back to 1966 and known for its delicious buttery pav bhaji. They have maintained the same taste since then and the outlet seems to be always crowded with people and on weekends you have to wait for a hour or so to get seats. Must recommend for someone who wants to try out one of the best Pav bhaji !! Good by taste with loads of butter. It is having good service but too much of waiting specially during weekends as process is one round for parcel and one for having it there. It also serve milkshakes but it's costlier than it should be . Limited parking place .
       Overall had an amazing experience over there and would love to visit this place again.

reviews.text:
I visited this place when it was newly opened. The entire theme of the restaurant is Post office theme. I'll breakdown my review in few pointers

Location: Pretty far from Vasai railway station. This is a good hotel for the locals who live nearby

Ambience: Great with good ventilation and seats. The restaurant also offers a music area where music is played in the evening. It also has bar area

Food: The food quality is good and tastes well. I have tried some of the things in the menu and it has not really disappointed me

Price: Fairly priced the food can come upto 1000 approx for two people. With drinks it would be extra

Parking: There is a big parking space available downstairs for both two and four wheelers

Overall review: Good for a weekend dinner. You can make reservations or walk in too. For certain occasions or festival do make reservations. The hotel is big enough to accommodate quite number of people. The staff is good and the hotel offers great value for money

3 STAR is for the ambience and the live music which goes on in the restaurant. Menu is too small to choose from. Service is Too quick might be because of less dishes. The taste of food in not as expected. They must improve the taste of their food.
This is yet the best restaurant in this location, has a variety if vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes. I had the post office platter here, and it was mouth watering. Surely recommend to visit here.

This place has been one of my fav hang out places.. the ambience here is absolutely perfect with the perfect blend of music and alcohol and food.. I mus say evy dish over here is worth trying esp the blanket prawns and the chicken sizzler.. the sizzler s absolutely refreshing with veggies and the chicken s perfectly cooked.. the concept of ice cream in a tea glass also s out of the box.. a place worth trying..

Great place to go with family and friends, good service and delicious food. Chicken chowpatti is a must try. üëç

My first experience with Gujurati cuisine and the verdict is...fantastic!!!  I was on the fence as to whether I should visit Gujurat, but if they cook like the chefs at Nimantran, I'm definitely going to go.  The menu is simple, there's a thali, but there's such variety with sweet, savory and spicy.  And it's a subtle spiciness so if you're a white person like me, don't be turned away.  Its 325 rupees for an all you can eat thali at dinner time, and the owner and staff were really welcoming and friendly guys.  I arrived at 7 on the dot so I had some time alone to talk with them and they answered any questions I had about any of the new exotic dishes.
Lovely unlimited thali, reasonable pricing. Service is leisurely, which might not be to everyone's liking.
Good though fairly simple thali. And not really expensive. Just about Rs325 pp. Strangely not crowded on a Friday afternoon except for a large group of elderly women.

Of course it will come with a price, drinks are costly and so is a table if you don't fancy the idea of dancing for long or want to take a pause.
Whole place is divided in half, the other half is seems a private place. On a Saturday night People start coming around 11 and its good number of people who visit.

1.Entry fees is 3000 rupees.
2. Once you go inside you can not go out and re enter.
3. There is no single chair to sit.

7. Club is divided into two. To enter the half where crowd is less and has seating arrangement, you have to pay hefty.

reviews.text: 145 was really good! The fries I ordered were amazing, along with the sharing bowl drink which did not disappoint either. Absolutely enjoyed my time here with my partner. I'll probably visit again to explore more of the menu.

It's located on 1st floor and is regular kind of place, I found it more suitable for college going students. Food and ambience is average not worth the price. Staff is very good, polite and quick. 

They have a pool table for entertainment and ambience is dark. If you are planning to take lot of group snaps, you will find it very hard to get a good picture in this lighting.

145 Bandra serves a variety of lip smacking food and refreshing cocktails. A signature part of their menu are their thick shakes. An elaborate bar counter and a pool table are the two key attractions of the outlet. Their staff is super cooperative and polite, one of the brownie points. The service is also very prompt. We tried a couple of preparations like chicken cheese cigar rolls, nasi goreng, 145 mighty oreo shake, and butter chicken bao. Prices are bit on the steeper side and they've got very limited options so you need to choose accordingly. Table reservation is strongly recommended. Nice place to unwind with friends or go out on a date.

Recommend must try this its too good

reviews.text: Love this place.Been here 3/4 times and I absolutely love the ambience. The staff is cordial and look after you. The food is good. Waiting for this Covid situation to get over with soon.

3 Wise Monkeys at Khar is a well-known popular Sports bar. The bar is also known for its big TV screens that showcase the latest football and cricket matches, live. Matches from the English Premier League, La Liga and the Serie A are regularly shown at this bar. Known for not being heavy on the pocket one can surely enjoy the atmosphere during live screenings with some of their favorite drinks and sizzling hot starters. Every Wednesday and Sunday they have crazy Karaoke nights where you can sing your heart out and unwind after a hard day‚Äôs work. The average cost for two people is Rs 1900 /- and Rs230 for a pint of beer. You can visit this place with family, friends and acquaintances, either way it will be a enjoyable evening.

Had a ball of a time here. Came for a show and it was so fun. Bonus is the owner here is a ManU fan so got to see a live match as well. Overall a very great place and make sure you visit during happy hours if you don't mind drinking.

The staff was very hospitable and they went out the way in ensuring we were comfortable while they were still setting up for the day. reviews.text:
5 Spice Missing on spice
The food that we ordered was pathetic and not worth the money. We have had food at 5 spice a couple of times but this time the food was worst. I placed the order at 10.30pm on the 23rd of August and we ate the food at 1.30am. The next day when I called 5 spice letting them know how tasteless the food was they stated that you should have called on the same  every day.when I already told him that we had the food at 1.30am. Later he tells me that you should have called before 12.00pm because the chef's were there till that time and only then this feedback/complain would have been considered. He also stated that we do not have a manager present at the moment and are working with minimum staff. I did tell him then why did you take the order when you guy's can't keep up to the mark of providing good food and service. When I told him that I will put my reviews he was all OK about it. This was the worst experience ever in terms of food and service. Will order food from small Chinese stalls hence forth.

The best place to eat Chinese and thai food. The quantity is huge so order accordingly. The taste is great and suits Indian taste buds. 5 spice noodles will never disappoint. You should also try rocky road and mission impossible desserts. They are finished quickly so reserve once before ordering main course.

The food was very tasty and the staff was very friendly... And the price was not very heavy on the pocket. The ambiance of the place was also very nice for family's and also had a trendy crowd... Overall a good experience. A must try place if you are a foodie..

Nice place to hang out with friends or family. Great food at a great price. Completely worth the money. Authentic Chinese cuisine. Desserts here are without a doubt one of the best things a person van have. If you ever come to Sakinaka, this is a must-try place.

I ordered food from 5 spice through swiggy. The chicken fried rice was too salty while the gravy was very bland with no spice at all. There was nothing to differentiate between veg and non veg that led me and my family members to confusion. Also, we ordered garlic fried rice both in veg and non veg. But only the veg one had garlic in it while the chicken did not. It was just a plain fried rice. Normally the quality is really good but today's food was a let down.

reviews.text:
It's been a while I visited this place but posting the review now.
Lovely ambience!!
Great food.
Most lovely staff ‚ù§Ô∏è which reminds me of an incident.

I had a meeting at rosewood which didn't really go well, and it was so bad that anyone could tell by my face that something is wrong. Probably the staff noticed that too and smilingly gestured me to sit down, in seconds two of them came to clean the table, passed all the leftovers towards me, asked if I needed anything, although being part of their job, I could feel the extra warmth.

So kudos to the staff and thanks for the lovely gesture that day :)
First thing its purely vegetarian... Unlike d routine menu, it has varieties.... Value for money... Good quantity.... Freshly made bread is awesome... Service is superb...

It's a vegetarian continental restaurant.

The decor is very beautiful. Seating has variations and are very comfortable. They have a fireplace too.

Outside seating is also there. There is ample seating provided to sit and wait for your table. 

Drinks, cocktails and mock tails are available. The menu is quite big. The dessert section is equally impressive. Tiramisu, Blueberry cheese cake, skillet cookies, sizzling brownie and so much more.
 
The unique feature is the salad bar. You can choose ingredients to make your own salad.

There is small bakery upstairs. Our kids went to see it too. 

The service is quick and efficient. They kept clearing the tables as soon as we were done with the dish. The serving staff is very helpful and good natured.

Washroom is available.

It's on a little expensive side but you get equally tasty food.

I love occasionally visiting this place. Slightly heavy on the pockets but the services are great and very professional. They will definitely be known for this forever. Make me a little conscious since there's someone always around my table, but the staff does everything to keep us happy. 

Food and drinks are definitely a hit. Loved their Pizza's! Most recommended is their Amboda Pizza. Comes with an extra bowl filled with cheese. Looks fancy too!

Walk into this upscale vegetarian all-day dining restaurant and bar, and be treated to a wonderful fare for your taste buds! The staff is very friendly and skilled, starting with Anthony who literally treats you like close friends! Over three visits I am yet to be less than awed by even one single dish, starting from mocktails and soups, down to some amazing starters, excellent main course, and killer desserts. They also have a boulangerie inside for your baked staples to take home, and a salad bar. Recommended any time!
