reviews.text: Aharveda restaurant one of the top vegan and satvik restaurants. I really wonder how they are making vegan food so tasty. I am in love with Aharveda restaurant. Also a sparkle of liquor can be deadly healthy combo.

We had gone there for lunch. Usually it‚Äôs required to book a table but it being an weekday we got a table immediately.

The ambience is ok, it‚Äôs subtle, small place as compared to other joint restaurants. 
Staff is friendly, helpful at suggesting dishes. They know their preparations.

Parking is a hassle,
Place is worth a visit

I eat non-veg food four times a week at minimum and vegan food was the last thing I would've ever tried had it not been for my Mom.

My ma had read about Aaharveda long back in some newspaper and was really keen to try it out. After giving up on me she finally convinced my friends and we were there for a brunch last Sunday!

It's inside the famous Golden chariot restaurant on Andheri West SV road and operated by the same management itself. The ambiance has good-decent classic family restaurant vibe. 

The menu on the other is poles apart from your usual golden chariot menu. 

We ordered a lot of food from 
- non bread pizza
- Sandwiches
- Garlic (non) bread sticks
- pulao
To 
- vegan Dahi Vada üßê

Must say, I was impressed with Non-Bread bread made of Rajgira (Desi quinoa) to vegan Dahi made out of almond milk(!?)

It all tasted nice and delicious for first couple of bites but nah I couldn't finish or gorge on any of the dishes. Although between four of us we managed to finish it all.

Giving it 4 stars cuz if I was a vegan I would've truly loved it I must say. Also at the given price point how many Vegan restaurants do we have in this side of the bay is something which is unknown to an uninitiated like me.

All in all good experience, will definitely visit next time I'm out with my Vegan friends (I barely know 3 people who are True vegans so umm I don't know when tbh ;))

My only complain is the staff although very polite, patient and professional lacks knowledge about these Vegan dishes.

I have been to this restaurant  a couple times  which is a 5 minute walk from Andheri station and they have best thali which is dairy free, gluten free & oil free at a very affordable rate of Rs. 400. Also their gluten free vegan Pizzas are a must try.

Long waiting time for getting table , please book  your table. Tables were vacant still we  had to wait.  Managing of tables not good. 
Food was good and tasty. We took limited thali. Quality and quantity both was very good.  Service was nice. Courteous staff, explained to us about food as it was Vegan thali. Overall good experience.

reviews.text:
In times like these, if I‚Äôm ordering from outside, it‚Äôs only from places I trust. Amidst a busy day at work, I often find myself looking for something tasty that I can almost never find the time to prepare. Thank god for trust worthy restaurants that are still hustling to keep us going.

I recently ordered in from All Elements and was extremely happy with how seamless the experience was. Safely packed, promptly delivered and most importantly, delicious! 
Here‚Äôs wheat I tried:

- Chipotle Chicken Tacos
This dish consists of 2 soft shell tacos generously filled with diced chicken in a spicy sauce and salsa. It comes with a side fresh sour cream to compliment the heat of the dish and some extra salsa if you‚Äôre looking to add some more. Quick to eat and we‚Äôll balanced flavours. 

- Garlic Bread 
This ones a classic, no messing around with the OG. Bread that‚Äôs toasted to a buttery crisp, topped with smashed garlic and herbs, how can one go wrong? Loved that this reached me crisp and not wet and soggy from condensation. 

- Fettuccine Carbonara
I save this dish for days I feel indulgent. A rich creamy sauce, bacon strips and mild herbs. Simple, flavourful, rich and delicious. It comes with a little garlic bread too :) 

I generally visit all elements cafe but haven‚Äôt been able to due to the pandemic. I‚Äôm very very glad that I can still enjoy my favourites at home without any fuss. Definitely worth checking out in my opinion.

Perfect place for new age comfort food. They even have great healthy eats on their menu. They even follow all WHO safety protocols, so i decided to try:
1. Beverage- Watermelon lavender chia seed
2. Appetizer - Hummus Kulcha & Mushroom Bruschetta
3. Pasta - Penne Alla Romana
Taste was so delicious and fresh with generous portion. Packaging A+ no spills. 
My favourite was Pasta so creamy and loaded with mushrooms and broccoli accompanied with garlic bread. 
A must try is mushroom bruschetta - Juicy inside & crispy on outside edges. 
Cannot wait to try some more from their menu‚ù§Ô∏è

So last night I had ordered Garlic Bread from this outlet and first of all I am impressed with packaging of food. It's properly covered. 

And coming to the food, 
In this you will get 6-7 pieces of Garlic Bread, it was too tasty and well made by the chef. 

Definitely going to order some more dishes, also outlet I would like to recommend this awesome outlet.

We wanted to eat Pepperoni üçï pizza so decided to order it from all elements, also ordered for Garlic Bread, Mushroom Bruschetta & cold coffee. Absolutely loved our pepperoni pizza, was made very well. Got just 3 pieces in Mushroom Bruschetta, it was yum but not happy with the portion size as per the pricing. Garlic bread was ok, cold coffee was spilled in the bag and didnt have sugar in it. Overall food taste was good. Needs to focus on good packaging and appetizer quantity.

reviews.text: Food was too spicy and oily..... Didn't expect this kind of quality from such a brand

All the variety of tasty and fried indian food is here. The restaurants has a nice ambience and great for family or friends get together or birthdays. The quantity is big so all the dishes can be shared.

B Bhagat Tarachand, Mulund.

Who hasn't heard bout B Bhagat Tarachand?!! You will hardly find anyone!. It's famous since generations & widely spread across Mumbai!. We had been here recently again, situated@N.S. road, near Panch Rasta, Mulund West!.

The surrounding ambience has pleasing vibes & aroma is soothing too!. The decors are well lit & gives the feel of its long lavish legacy of generations!.

The staff here is very friendly & prompt while placing several orders & suggestions & serving hot too!.
Dharmendra, incharge for our table was very attentive to recommend & serve with delight!.

Let's checkout the food we had ordered here, 

Papad Churi was totally crunchy & tossed up with onion & chaat!. You just can't stop after one bite!.. It's all time regular favourites for most of the tables!. Surely try this dish for starters!.

We next ordered Chinese Platter, it was finger licking & platter had sufficient quantity for sharing wise!. Several Chinese items include manchurian balls, Vej crispy, paneer chilli & spring rolls & salad in sidings!.

We also had Paneer Tikka Dry, it was mouthwatering to glance & craving for more!. The spices were nicely blend & paneer was coated crisply & lip smacking!.

Paneer Cheese Tikka, is a nice fusion of seasoned paneer & over loaded cheese!. If you love both, surely go for this tikka, it's finger licking awesome!.

Bhagat Tarachand Special Thali  gives a glimpse of its succesful tradition it carries!. Balanced so well with ghee chapatis, 2 sabji of own choice, papad, dal, raita etc!. It's wholesome & flavourful by all means!.

Gulab Jamun is tender soft & sweet to its core, lingering sweetness for a long time to cherish!. Surely good to try Gulab Jamuns for dessert!.

Icecream slice looked tempting & every slice of it was yummm!! After heavy dining, it's truly a bliss to pounce on desserts like this for sweet tooth lovers!.

B Bhagat Tarachand is a proven excellence & you surely visit this place quite often to experience it's awesome treat & hospitality!. Thankyou!. ‚ù§

reviews.text: Loved the food and especially the ambience of the restaurant. It gives a good vibe.

South Bombay has these cute collections of cafe, and bake house cafe is one of them! Colonial sorts of entrance and interiors, furniture and food presentation! They serve you with such a smile and such warmth, that you want to finish the entire food :P We had the lebanese platter and crispy potato skins! Lebanese platter will win your heart with the variety and taste and presentation! A must try when you here. We had strawberry smoothie and hot chocolate! Poles apart, both of them were amazing! We also had strawberry cream cheese tart! Season of strawberries and this perfect dessert just was like the strawberry on top of the cake! Had a great time, thank you! Will visit again soon :)

A pretty little cafe, in the hidden streets of Kalaghoda, this place definitely falls on my most recommended list!
You walk in, and the ambience is beautiful, and the staff is friendly and helpful. 
We stared of by asking for a berry shake, and it was super refreshing.  You can actually get pieces of the berries while you sip on it! 
We asked for a Lebanese platter, cause hummus is bae! And it was an assortment of various items, which were packed with flavor!
We moved on to having and avocado salad, with green apples, and they had the flavor on that just right!
For mains, we asked for a beef steak, which I HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
We finished off with a delicious strawberry tart! 
The entire experience was superb!

A really cozy space to spend some time by oneself or with a friend. The iced teas were quite disappointing, high on sugar and low on flavour. The Mezze platter was nice and the dish one must try here is the Mac and Cheese pizza. It's amazing. 
The ambience is pretty good too. 

If you found the review useful, please hit the like button :)

This is One of the classy places of fort area a hidden joint with a wonderful ambiance. The food is really good here as it serves a variety of Italian and continental dishes. The staff is also really friendly. There is also a display of deserts. The prices are also reasonable. I tried a veg sandwich which was ok. I also tried continental chicken dish which was really good as it was served with gravy and smashed potatos with veges. The desert was also too good which was served with ice cream. Mostly fancy crowd comes here. It has a ample of sitting area.

reviews.text:
One bite of the Biryani from here and we thought which rock were we living under? How did we ever not call for Biryanis from Behrouz? 

When we called for a delivery from this Biryani speciality joint we didn't know it was this big and when the order came, our entire house got filled with the rich aromas of the Biryani that came!

What we had: 

Paneer Subz Biryani: This definitely would be those slow cooked dum biryanis for the vegetables, the masalas and the perfectly seasoned and soft paneer cubes were so beautifully cooked and carried so much flavour that we were floored by how they must've achieved this. Even the rice was cooked to perfectly and so rich with the aromas or spices that each bite was delightful! Even the pudhina curd and the gravy it came along with were absolutely delicious and we couldn't have asked for more.

Falafal-e-Khaas: A little flavour bomb, these falafal-e-khaas nuggets were the perfect appetizers to our main meal.

Chaas: Nice refreshing chaas that went perfectly with our food.

Gulaab Jamun: Soft warm balls of sweet heaven. These gulaab jamuns were the perfect end to a scrumptious meal. 

Have you tried Behrouz Biryani yet? If not, do try for sure!
Best mughlai biryani and best packaging

reviews.text:
In order to satisfy my evening hunger thought to try out non vegetarian food from Belly Darbar located at chembur. The Butter chicken roll was a big one which was totally filling for one person. It tasted good too. Little veggies as stuffing would be preferred. Also tasted a few chicken kebabs which was good but the taste can be improved.

Belly Darbar is a Delivery kitchen located in chembur. As it's the place serving variety of veg and non veg options I thought of giving a try to this place.

I ordered following dishes from belly darbar

1. Chicken chimichurri: spice alert extremely spiced but tasty chicken tikka like starter with green mirch tadka and well cooked fresh chicken. I loved it.

2. Cheese melt stuffed mushrooms: this was something I tried for the first time turn outs to be the best. Cheese and paneer stuffing made mushrooms tastes heavenly. The green chutney accompanied it well.

3. Hyderabadi Veg Biryani : it was not the regular mainstream biryani but the aromatic long grain rice prepared with goodness of veggies and creamy white sauce gravy. It was different and very tasty.

4. Butter Chicken Roll: Highly Recommended. I loved it totally. The butter chicken stuffing was so tasty and consistency was well maintained as it goes into a roti. The butter roti outside was so yummy it was very long and heavy. Its sufficient for 2 people.

I loved the food which I had from belly  darbar the quality and quantity both were amazing. The packing done by them is really appreciated. Food was served hot and fresh‚ù§üíØ

Paneer Makhani Roll: This roll is their signature roll. Roll stuffed with loads of paneer pieces marinated in makhani gravy, which is not so spicy & creamy, is definitely a great choice for those who love non-spicy food. reviews.text: I normally rate the APMC market Bhagat Tarachand as the best. In fact, they are the original ones. But today was my first visit to them (while the lockdown is still in effect) and we got the parcels to it. The taste was right up there. The service was fast. The folks were polite and I would rate it highly. This is right inside Vashi which is pretty convenient for people as well. Recommended.

Bhagattarachand is famous for their veg mouthwatering dishes. They have so many branches all over the Mumbai. We visited their vashi branch during last year November on the special occasion of our 6 month wedding anniversary and it is very nice place to celebrate your special days. We have ordered veg spring roll in starter and it was very tasty and in the main course there was Garlic Naan, Kadhai Mashroom and Baby corn Masala, all the dishes are very delicious. which own my heart was  their special kulfi falooda, It is their best iteam in dessert. Must recommend place for the vegetarians if you are near to vashi, Navi Mumbai. The staffs are very helpful and they try to make your visit memorable. Ambience of the restaurant is normal. In vashi branch they have two floors, while ground floor is non AC and upper floor is fully air-conditioned and the price different for both the floor.
Home like food ,the food was quite awesome last time I came here with my friends

reviews.text:
A nice, clean and warm place serving delicious and healthy parathas. I doubt if parathas can get any better. My association dates back to a misty morning in August 2005, when six friends trudged together for almost an hour, covering three (or maybe four) kilometers in search of a hearty and filling breakfast. Less than a month in Navi Mumbai, we still showed some reluctance to vada pav and maisal pav (of course that soon got added to our list of favourites). What started off with parathas on that day, continued with thalis, combos, makke di roti and sarson da saag, just to name a few. This place suits all your requirements, a small party with friends, not feeling like cooking, something to suit your taste and budget, office breaks, in short anything. The best part is you can order anything and rest assured that you will like it. Oh yes, I forgot the chhaas, the best accompaniment for all your orders.
Thanks Naveen Ji for making our life more beautiful and happier.

A paratha house serving almost 110 varieties of paratha a great figure almost unbelievable  and you will be amazed that you will actually find the veggies in the parathas that you ordered for. A perfect hangout for college students and professionals. A great place to have parathas and good Punjabi food... This place as far as ambience is concerned is not too good but taste of food makes it all go away.. 
The food is tasty and yummy and their passion is also good. They are no where compromising on their food taste. 
At my first I have posted pictures of paneer paratha.. It had only paneer and no potatoes or onions in it... Well astonished  to know that..... Will visit more often..... 
My second visit to this place I choose to have the Methi Palak Paratha, Spring onion and Pudina Paratha followed by 2 Sada Paratha with Rajma...We were 2 people sharing all this couldn't finish it though so leftover was a takeout for us. You can see in the images that they actually  have the veggies that you ordered for no potatoes  as binding as most place you see that. 
The lassi was soothing not too sweet not too heavy just right.
A second visit was really memorable had loads of dishes as we were in a group. 
We ordered for Maharani Thali, Laccha Paratha Thali and Paneer Paratha Thali followed by a Special Bimal Paratha. 
I can describe the dishes as much as I want but I won't be doing justice to the food served.
Lipsmacking taste and actual foodgasm.

I had heard a lot about this place from friends and relatives, as it's close to my workplace, but never got to try it as it has a limited seating capacity and used to be always full with waiting list. Luckily one afternoon, it wasn't much crowded, so decided to check this out with my colleagues.
Now don't expect fancy ambience, it's a simple place, very famous for parathas, and that's the only thing we ordered - different types of parathas (I didn't try other cuisine like thali, or rice items). 

The price starts from around 80rs and goes till 180-200rs depending upon the filling. Seeing the price I assumed there will be two parathas, so confirmed with the waiter, but was shocked to know it was the price of a single paratha. There are various combination of fillings, i decided to go with make your own paratha with any 3 fillings, i chose paneer, onion, and potato. 
It takes time for the food to be prepared and served as they are freshly cooked and served. The paratha i ordered was served in 4 pieces with green chutney & curd, i mix them to get a good mixture. One bite into the paratha, and i could feel that they are very very generous with the fillings, i was almost full in 2 pieces. Some of my friends who have less appetite managed to eat only 2 or 3 pieces of their paratha and had to take parcel of remaining pieces. 

Final verdict - It's a heavenly place for paratha lovers, pleasr visit at least once for lip smacking hot parathas, and you won't be disappointed.

Good food
Good variety
Inexpensive pricing
Limited other food options
Ambience and Hygiene is poorly maintained
Amazing variety of parathas and great food. The ambience is also very clean and comfortable

Ambience and feel: A spacious, relaxing caf√© with a good ambience. It has beautiful art on the walls showcasing and promoting the use of organic ingredients which is quite interesting to look at.

reviews.text: Best coffee‚òï ever had and awesome place for breakfast. Kings breakfast üçΩwhich serves French butter croissantsü•ê, sausages eggsüç≥, baconü•ìbaked beans, waffles and don't miss the coffee ‚òïas well. Great ambience üòçand perfect place for meetings / hangout.

Always had good food here. This place is busier Th at it used to be with more foreign customers now. Service is better than it used to be, which was never bad, but lacking. They accept foreign credit cards without any problems. Good go to spot for a proper breakfast, excellent coffee, and decadent desserts.

Bombay Coffee House 
This is one of the well known brand located in bandra, just next to Bandra Linking road. 
They serve a great variety of coffees and healthy snacks to opt for. 

The menu also consisted of some good cheat meal varieties also a huge spread for some breakfast meals. 

We ordered for a Pesto Grilled Veg Sandwich and Mix sauce pasta. 
Both were really good. 
Also reasonably priced 

You must try their desserts and pastries. 
It was just drool worthy! 

It's definitely going to be one of my best visits till date

I have been there so many times, I love their famous King's breakfast too. It has so many things, it's worth every penny, it can fill two people but it's fun not sharing good food. Their only problem would be their sausages, I am not sure what is it, but it's very off, I don't like the taste much and it doesn't feel very good too. Apart from that, I have never had a problem here

Bombay coffee house certainly does have the look and feel of Bombay with the historic pictures on their walls. Their staff behaviour is warm and courteous and will be willing to help you chose the perfect dish for you. I started my evening with their Vietnamese Ice Coffee, which is served with a portion of condensed milk to be added to your coffee. Truly amazing ! We also their their Dark chocolate milkshake, and God it was too good. In starters I had their chicken strips along with their Chicken Caesar Salad which was served very fresh and looked healthy. In mains we had their Chicken Steak, which was topped with a White Mushroom sauce, with a portion of veggies and garlic bread on the side. Overall, it was an excellent dish. We also tried their Chicken Sapo Rice, which is a must try if you are a Chinese lover. Great taste, great quantity. We ended this perfect evening with a lovely hot cup of Mochaccino. Overall, it was a delight to visit this place. Best wishes to Team Bombay Coffee House.

reviews.text:
Well being a foodie, going to a salad place at times is not a bad idea. Especially when they are soo healthy and delicious.

I visit this place whenever I crave for eating healthy stuff.

My favourite is the Red Samurai. This has wheat noodles, chicken, broccoli and soy ginger sauce as dressing. You get an option of half and full. Half portion is enough for one person.

The Protein overload is also a good one to try which has eggs as a part of the ingredients.
Amazing salads and sandwiches. Extremely healthy and hygienic. Highly recommended!

If you are looking for a healthy meal, this the place. Small, cute and well lit place with outdoor and indoor seating. From the menu, would recommend you make your own salad. If you find this too complicated then choose from a range of veg and non veg salads. The portion size is huge. So for a couple, order one and then decide.

Whenever I craved a salad this is place I've headed to.

All the salad is freshly made. In terms of taste it is good and the quantity is very good.

Do visit if you love salad.

Ambience service food 5 on 5

Caf√© Free India in Lower Parel is a 5-7 minute walk from Prabhadevi station. The ambience had a vintage look, wicker chair and witty quotes on all the walls. The waiting staff was courteous and well read on the menu. It was raining when we went there which just really elevated the experience on the whole.

Service 5/5.

Ambience 5/5.

We started with two soups. The FRENCH ONION SOUP had a thick consistency and a mild but great flavor. Italian flavoring and the cheese garlic toastie made it a good start the meal.
THUKPA SOUP had a load of spices and had a Tibetan sweet and sour flavor. The soup has well-cooked thin noodles and pak choy.

In mocktails we had two shakes and two soda based mocktail ORANGE MOJITO and GINGER GARLIC SODA. Mojito was having lots of lemon in it and ginger garlic soda is perfect one to have here. RED VELVET SHAKE was my favourite and oreo lovers should try OREO CHOCO MILK SHAKE.

For starters, we ordered CREAMY MUSHROOM BRUSCHTTAS. It mainly consisted of finely chopped mushroom amongst other things. It was one of our favorite dishes ordered here. The crispy flavorsome bread topped with a creamy dressing was a mouthful of joy on a plate. The next starter was the VEG NUGGETS, that came filled with cheese and cream. The dressing and crispy nuggets can be good siders for when out drinking with friends, or even otherwise!

Thin crust, vege-loaded and tangy-ish BOMBAY MASALA PIZZA was amongst the many things that tasted delightful. Main courses we ordered, included a ‚Äòproper italian‚Äô PENNE ARRABIATTA RED SAUCE PASTA. One bite of it and you can clearly know that the red sauch has been made by the caf√© from scratch, giving it a fresh taste‚Ä¶ Something we always look for in red pasta. The very popular GODFATHER VEG BURGER was specially recommended to us by the waiting staff and they were right about doing so. The burger was a handful, with two patties and cheese, dressing and veggies. The other one was a VEG PARMAGGIANO BURGER with a potato, veggies and seasoning filled patty. Both the burgers were sided with very crispy and fresh French Fries.

Moving on DESSERT OF THE DAY‚Ä¶ A pastry with White Rum infused dark chocolate. It was bitter-sweet and really rich. BLUEBERRY CHEESECAKE was how a cheesecake should be. Very rich, dense, creamy with a very-berry flavor and a crispy biscuit base.

Thupka 4/5.
French onion soup 5/5.
Orange mojito 3/5.
Ginger lemon 4/5.
Oreo choco milk shake 4/5.
Red velvet shake 5/5.
Veg nuggets 4/5.
Creamy mushroom bruschetta 5/5. (must order)
Godfather veg 4/5.
Veg parmaggiano 4/5.
Penne arrabiata red sauce 5/5.
Bombay masala pizza 4/5.
Dessert of the day 4/5.

The landscape of Mumbai cuisine would be incomplete without the vast number of Irani Caf√©s dispersed across the city. One of the most legendary caf√©s has to be Cafe Military.

Located on a busy street in Fort, Mumbai, this caf√© may not look like much on the outside but has character on the inside. Just enter the restaurant and seat yourself. You only have to wait for a few minutes before a server comes to take your order.

You must have their Irani Chai. This is one of the best I have had. This light chai is packed with lemongrass goodness. And no chai is complete without some Bun Maska. They add tutti-frutti to their bread and slather plenty of butter.

I do recommend their cheese toast as well. While vegetarians don't have a lot of options for a hefty meal, you have enough choices to have a light snack. Most people do visit Cafe Military for its affordable range of alcohol.

Service is no frills. The servers are sweet. They come, take your order, and give you your food as soon as possible. 

I hope Cafe Military starts providing more options for vegetarians. For now, I'll always go back for their tea.

reviews.text:
After an evening bargaining for a discount of probably 20 rupees on Linking Road, my friend and I were ravenous and wanted to catch an early dinner before a show at the comedy club. He had heard of candies, as had I, from multiple friends who had raved about the food and environment. Since Candies is literally right next to the Cuckoo Club (A+ on location you guys!), we decided to eat at the popular joint. 

Though we had come about 2 hours before closing time, there still were a lot of menu items which weren't available. So unfortunately I was not able to try a lot of the items I wanted to. 
We ended up choosing the BBQ pizza, which was alright, but was very filling. However the drinks were on point and I had no complaints. For all the food we had, I‚Äôd rate it 3/5

Since neither of us had been to Candies, we wanted to see what the gossip was all about! Clearly we had no idea that the food is not the only thing that is said to be excellent at Candies but the structure is something to be praised at as well. I had initially thought the main floor and a second floor was the entirety of the joint, but as we started to ascend floor after floor, I definitely started feeling I had entered Wonderland. We had legitimately gotten lost because of how huge the place was!
There is an area for everyone here! A area to plug in your earphones to quietly study while huge groups of friends laugh loudly multiple floors beneath you, secluded nooks for candle lit date nights and many spacious spaces if you ever wanted a private event. 

I have never seen a joint that it structured like this.. it's so indie and artsy that the vibe makes the entire ambience. Totally loved it! Ambiance and location is definitely 10/5!

One of the oldest cafes of Bandra, Candies is such a fun place to chill and hangout while munching onto some delicious salads, ice teas and desserts. Especially the one in Pali Hill. Spread over three stories, this Candies is so good looking on a bright spring day that you just want to sit here, laze and go click click. The cafe understands that the premises make for many a photo opportunities and may be that's why doesn't allow picture taking from professional DSLRs! 

We enjoy coming here on Sundays to have our Wild Berry Ice Tea and Quiches along with the Salad bowls from the Salad bar Candies is known for since years!
The food is delicious the roast chicken with stuffing is amazing and the chicken stake was outstanding

reviews.text:
Chakh Le Lucknow

Lucknow or the city of Nawabs is a paradise for foodies. Lucknow strongly dominates the culinary culture of our country with its profound traditional delicacies and spices. The reason why Lucknowi food is so popular and loved is the fact that traditional food is given a royal flavour and this awadhi custom is passed on since ages and will continue for the years to come.

Very recently ordered a Lucknowi meal from Chakh Le Lucknow. They have focussed on this particular segment and have maintained a very short crisp menu.

When you think about Lucknow, its majorly a fare for the nonvegetarians especially meat lovers however this kitchen has dishes for the vegetarians too.

What I ordered

VEG GALOUTI

As desired ! Melt in the mouth Galoutis. I dont eat mutton hence opted for the vegetarian ones. These strongly had flavour of black pepper and cooked to perfection. It's a blasting melange of flavours.

CHICKEN ROLL

Very spicy but delicious. Generous portion of chicken with lots of onion wrapped in a flour roll. It would be ideal in a multigrain roti as alot of people avoid maida these days. Tasted good with mint chutney.

CHICKEN LUCKNOWI BIRYANI

Very flavourful as I had thought of it. Served with smooth curd. The chicken pieces can be better and fleshy as these were very boney. Quality should improve.

CHICKEN KORMA

This was my favourite dish amongst all. Loved the spices used and consistency of gravy. Recommended.

So if you desire some Lucknowi food you can give this place a try.

Chakh Le Lucknow is located in Powai. Its a delivery only outlet. 

The menu serves authentic Lucknowi dishes plus North Indian cuisine. They also specialized in Galauti Kabab, Shami Kabab & so on. 

The delivery was done on time & packaging was really good without any spills. It arrived hot. 

What I Ate ~ 
Mutton Galauti Kabab. ( 4 pcs ) 
Mutton Kheema made in good amount of garlic ginger paste. It really melted in the mouth. Taste wise it was flavourful & good. It was served with green chutney which was good. 

Veg Paneer Lazeez.
Thick gravy with paneer pieces which was good. It was oily & had a very unique creamy flavour. Served with Ulta Tawa Paratha which was amazing. Overall really great. 

Chicken Briyani. 
The rice was cooked perfectly. The aroma was also great. The ratio of masala was decent. However the chicken pieces had more bone & less meat in it. Served with ratia. 

So this place is must recommended for some great food. Do give it a try.
Best place for Lucknowi Kebabs & Biryanis

At first, I was upset that my order was late by almost an hour, but when it finally arrived, the food turned out to be quite good.

I had a plate of Veg Navratan Biryani which had baby corn, paneer, carrot and green peas. It was suited to my taste as I'm not a fan of very spicy food. This came with raita which was slightly sour, and onion rings.

Their Ulta Tawa Paratha was unbelievably soft and huge. I had this with Paneer Lazeez which was extremely spicy. We also had Veg Galawti Kebabs (too spicy again) with chutney. The kebabs were soft, though.

Overall, I'd recommend the biryani and the paratha.

I ordered gallowati rolls, reshmi murg kebab, chicken gravy and paratha. I liked the reshmi murg kebab. It was sweet and creamy, typical lucknowi. The gravy was also soft and creamy. The taste mild and bit sweet. My favorite one was paratha which was not chewy but soft. I think they serve authentic lucknowi food. Gallowati rolls melted in my mouth. Again, the paratha was soft. The food is nawabi no doubt. But I wish they make it little spicy.

reviews.text: Today one of my office colleague ordered (order no.  chole bhature through zomato from #chakle the street food and it was served with insects as complimentary in bhature. Please be careful with your order and double check before consuming it. If you order from zomato than you should be worried more as zomato takes no action or doesn't care about its customers, all they do is refund and than sleep over the complaint.

Tried the Chole Bhature here. It was okay but not the true Dilli style chole bhature. The Bhatura was more like Puri. This is a small place with 2 maybe 3 two-seater tables. More suited for home deliveries. Would like to add that the staff was very courteous.

Amazing food. Extremely happy.  Was told about the Rajma chawal but in a rebel so I ordered the chole bhature and friend ordered Mathura Puri aloo. I'm in love. The taste s on point. A must have. To end the meal just go for that big glass of lassi and enjoy your nap.

A wonderful place to sample some delectable street food from the by-lanes of Delhi. Chak Le India is a hole in the wall type of restaurant. Their idea is to serve delectable, authentic and pocket friendly food.

MUST HAVE:
- Mutter Kulcha
- Chhole Bhature
- Bantewala Soda
- Paratha
- Punjabi Kadhi Pakoda

Since the resto is vegetarian and with that, it serves Delhi cuisine, the expectations were already set high.

1. Chole Bhature (7/10): Not the best chole ever, but it did its job of being one well and can be taken as a good tasting dish.
2. Amritsari Aloo paratha (9.5/10): One the best parathas one has tasted. JUST ORDER IT
3. Rajma Chawal (4/10): This might be worse than expected. Rice were cooked right, but rajma disappointed by being almost tasteless and nothing like what rajma should actually should taste. One had to order chole seperately just to finish the rice.
4. Lassi (7/10): Not the best tasting lassi, but with aloo paratha, lassi just complements & enhances it. JUST ORDER IT.

A special regard goes to green chilly, onion and lemon, without which the cuisine itself is incomplete. Ask for more and the staff doesn't hesitate to serve.

Also, the Punjabi Kadhi, that the staff offered, is worth trying.

Service : 9/10
Food : 7/10
Ambiance : 6/10
Quality : 7/10
Overall : 7/10

Expensive : No

Will I go there again : Yes
Will I recommend to someone : Yes

Bottom Line :
Looking forward for better Chole and Rajma...

This place is amazing from outside and from inside 
The food quality is very good and rich 
You can go for plenty of cocktails available in fancy style 
Moctails are also very good here 
But the best thing about this place is its ambiance and desserts 
Desserts have a very beautiful presentation
Staff and manager are very friendly.

CRAFTBAR 
everything in here is quite crafty, be it their tables, chairs, lamps, the handcrafted decor in the walls, and especially their cocktails 
They have a very comfy and cozy seating arrangement for all kinda groups 
They have also got a blissful outdoor seating arrangements 
The staff here are prompt, courteous and through with their menu 
overall amazing ambiance as well as the staff 
but they have got even more amazing food...lets discuss that 

Food Language 

A. Beverages 
   1. The 7 island iced tea:- literally had a mixture of all, a well crafted drink for alcohol lovers, may be the best 
   2. Pinacolada :- White rum infused in pineapple, coconut and vanilla cream which was very soothing and also my most fav 
   3. Spider Bite Shotz :- 2 are served in a chilled glass with vodka infused in lime 
   4. nujito :- aerated minty flavoured have always been my fav so i definitely loved this one as it had a quite unique twist to the mojito 

B. Starters 
   1. Lord Of The Wings :- Delicious crispy chicken Wings tossed in spicy siriracha, a bit oily but worth the taste 
   2. BEER BATTER PRAWNS :- Deep fried crunchy and tender prawns served along with mayo was too awesome to taste, am sure you won't get enough of it 

C. Main Course 
   1. Chicken Molten Lasagna :- This was the first time i had a lasagna and this place made me fall in love with it 
layers of cheese and shredded chicken one above the other a blend of which made the whole totally delectable, i couldn't stop eating it even after i was full 
   2. Khow Suey :- The name is weird but the dish isn't, Fresh veggies cooked in coconut milk coverd with the bed of noodles and pieces of chicken all over had a unique interesting and lovely taste 

D. DESSERT 
   1. Rasgulla Birds Nest :- small Rasgullas  are served in vermicelli nest with rabdi below was ultimately luscious 
   2. Flambeed Kal Jamoon :- Gulab jamoon bathed with flaming rum is served along with ice-cream a blend which was made to be quite piquant 
overall Had marvellous experience in here

Curry Culture is a delivery kitchen sitatued at Powai, near the IIT campus and delivers to a good number of places around the Powai area.

In my opinion, this is one of the finest delivery kitchens across the city and I say that not only because of the delicious food that they offer, but also due to the delivery timelines they adhere to of offering piping hot food and their remarkable packaging.

Recently I ordered for a Reshmi Malai Tikka, along with Paneer Tikka Masala and Butter Naan. I must say, that it was almost impossible for me to find a flause in any of them.

So, a few days back, I received a mail, Curry Me Up had opened for service in the Goregaon, Malad and Kandivali area, needed someone to review the same.

Well, you see, good food is a weakness, free good food makes me weak in the knees, but "good food" is the active verb. So a quick look at their other outlet profiles and I am assured, it's good. Still, it's Zomato, yet, I did give it a try.

So a day was set, Sunday to be exact, the day of my Sabbath.

The spread was huge, literally, humongous. I explicitly remember, asking them to send me their best, was surprised to find out, they had so many bests.

The breads were fine and plenty, ranging from rotis to parathas, all pretty good (it's bread, not much judging there except if it's burnt). Coming to the meats, from the tandoori, we had the kalimiri kebabs and the white tandoori chicken, both were pretty good. The curries were chicken tikka masala and garlic chicken masala, the chicken tikka masala was pretty great, the garlic chicken faded in comparison

Quite frankly, not wanting to drag this a long way, pretty much everything exceeded beyond expectations. The thing is, I have grown tired of these only delivery services, very few live up to the expectations.

The quantities delivered by most joints is horrible, food tasting sub par and nothing really justifies the price, but this is exactly where, Curry Me Up shines bright, they give amazing quantities, with lip smacking tastes and just the right price. Plus they deliver on time and that these days, is an asset.

P.S. Do try their biryanis

Curry me up is a delivery outlet in Malad West . Which is well known for North Indian , mughlai and kebabs . The food here is really delicious . The service is on time and the food that is served is hot and the packing is really good . The North Indian cuisine that they serve  is one of my favourite . Had tried the Panner Tikka masala - the paneer pieces are really soft and the gravy taste the best . The spices are just proper . The Kadhai paneer is really yummy and delicious . The panner dishes can be eaten with a paratha or a butter naan or tandoori roti . The roti is also soft . The veg biryani the spices and the flavours of the biryani are just awesome . If you are a biryani lover then this biryani you must try . Highly recommend you to try and order food from here . It‚Äôs just tasty and yummy not just for the taste but also for the best quality and the quantity they give but for the best service that they provide . Really had a wonderful experience . Surely will recommend others and will definitely food from here .

reviews.text:
Dakshin culture specializes in various South Indian dishes. The ambience is so quaint and beautiful. The bright lights and soft music makes it so peaceful and enjoyable.
The menu has vast range of dishes, with fish preparations, chicken, mutton.
Their motto is that South Indian cuisine is much more than Idlis and Dosas.

What we ordered:
In Starters üç¢
üî∏Fish Fry Porichaphu üêü‚ù§Ô∏è
This was a very tempting dish. Pomphret which was nicely marinated was served in red masala and fried. It had a nice tangy sweet taste. The covering was crisp with hint of spices and the sauce served along was tangy sweet. A must try!

üîπSpice Rubbed Rawas ‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
Rawas fish marinated with spices and yogurt and nicely grilled. The flavors were soaked in the fish. The dish was so well prepared that all I wanted to eat was this yummy Rawas. My new favorite.

In Cocktails üçπ
üî∏Cosmopolitan üç∏‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
Our usual favorite. This Cocktail was well prepared. Just the way I like it. Nothing can ever go wrong with Cosmo. Went perfectly well with the starters.

üîπMango Margarita üçπ‚ù§Ô∏è
This was tangy sweet due to the mango flavor but again a yummy boozy drink. Well served with sugar coated at the rim. It was an eye candy.

In Mains üçõ
üî∏Prawns Manglorean Sukkha üç§‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
This was a delight. If you want something light to go with your breads then this is it. This was so flavorful and tasty. Hint of all the spices nicely marinated in prawns. The prawns were in good number and juicy.

üîπChicken Chettinad üç≤‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
This was the best Chicken Chettinad. Spicy and tasty, with so many flavors. I could eat it everyday. Just like homemade gravies but much more flavors and spices. Too yum. A must must try here.

üî∏Malabar Paratha
It was served hot and crisp. Went really well with Chettinad gravy and the chicken pieces.

üîπAppam ‚ù§Ô∏è
They've a special counter to make appams. And my mum loved it to the core that through out the meal she had more of appams. Beautifully made and served steaming hot.

üî∏Neer Dosa
Soft and light. Non sticky and thin slices. The beauty of neer dosa. Just perfect.

In Desserts üç¶
üîπShahi Tukda ‚ù§Ô∏è
Fried bread stuffed with rabdi. The rabdi was so so good. Specially made by the chef. It was full of rich milky flavors.

üî∏Watalappam üçÆ‚ù§Ô∏èüíØ
Similar to our beloved custard but a famous South Indian dessert made from Coco and jaggery. Only if you taste it then only you can understand what I'm saying. It was so soft and tasty. Loved it!

The service is a bit slow, but once you taste the food you'll be on a joy ride. The food is so well prepared and so delectable. Each dish is pretty unique and delicious. It is a melange of flavors dancing in your mouth.
The servers are well trained and will help you with your selections. You'll definitely leave with a happy stomach and a smile on your face.

reviews.text: Doolally taproom is a great place to catch up with your friends and grab some freshly brewed beer. Their menu includes comfy food and the quantity and taste of the food was amazing. It has a cozy ambience with calm music and they also have free to play games like jenga, monopoly and other card and board games which will help you have a fun time with your friends. They have indoor as well as outside seating. The best part about this place is that it's pet friendly. So you don't have to leave your pet at home by himself, he can just tag along and play with other pets here, the menu also has a special section for pet food.

This is a really great place to enjoy some delicious craft beers. If you're one of those beer people then this is a place you certainly shouldn't miss out on. You have a decent variety of craft beers to choose from. The apple cider is one of the popular choices. Not only are the beers good but the snacks are equally good too. The potato fries are served with a variety of dips which is a must try. And to add to it you have various board games to choose from to enjoy with friends. The entire ambiance and the food adds to the experience. Really good place to visit with a group of friends.
The food tastes great and the prices are quite feasible! They have special offers in the month of October, especially on the beers.

I am used to visiting Doolally at Palm Beach Road, Navi Mumbai. So visiting this one was a good change for me. The only issue I faced was that the premises outside the pub were unhygienic. Apart from that, this is a great plea and I will definitely recommend!

*Flavoured Beer*
Try their apple/mango cider with house fries.
They offer drinks which is best in town which includes 
-apple cider
-mango cider
-stout beer
-Belgian wit
-pale ale
 and various more depending upon stocks and availability.
This place is pet friendly and pet food is also served here.
Very delightful and happening place at Andheri West. I was amazed to taste beers that too of fruit flavours and it‚Äôs definitely worth it for especially those who make wacky faces when it comes to drinking beer.
Cheers!

Spanish cuisine is one of the very distinct & assorted cuisines to explore. So be it delightful tapas to appetizing seafood or cheeses to churros, it's always exciting to try original as well as innovative options in Spanish cuisine.

Currently, there is no stopping to the different cuisines we get to explore in Mumbai city. Then why authentic Spanish cuisine too will be left out of the line?
El Mercado - meaning market in Spanish, is Mumbai's first ever dinky cafe offering classic Tapas Spanish dishes with a little modern twist to suit the Indian palate.

With rustic decor, soothing music, delicious food & hushed environment, El Mercado is your go-to place if you are looking for a relaxing corner that offers yummy coffee along with other innovative dishes to munch on.

Few options that should be definitely tried here-

From Breakfast-
Pan Con Tomate Mallorquin
Spanish Omelette

From Tapas-
Gazpacho Andaluz
Beetroot Borani

Desserts-
Crema Catalana
Caramel Custard

So take a quick tour to Spain by enjoying delightful Spanish food offered at El Mercado as it's definitely one of the best tapas in Mumbai.

Happy Meal! :)

Once you get a taste of real Spanish food, you just can't have enough of it. I'm so glad to have feasted on some out-of-this-world Spanish food on my travels through Spain. El Mercado is as good and as authentic as it can get in this part of the world. 
From the cozy little space, to the cutsey decor, they do take me back to the intimate restaurants in the bylanes of Madrid. 
Start of with some plump pimento stuffed olives & toasted bread that come gratis while you ponder on what to order. 
I recommend you try the Gambas Al Ajillo, cooked in a ton of really good olive oil, garlic & chilly flakes. Perfect to dip your bread in and soak up all of that flavored oil. For vegetarians, you can't go wrong with the Patats Bravas.
Although I was really looking forward to the Paella, ü•ò this one was a little of a let down. We had the mix seafood one. But, the rice wasn't cooked through and the flavors weren't as punchy as I remember it to be in Spain. Although, I have to ad the calamari was surprisingly nicely done and not rubbery at all. The sea food is really really fresh! 
They just have to work more on the flavors. It's also the priciest dish on the menu at a whopping 1300 rupees for a portion for 2 good eaters. That's really expensive for an average dish. 
I can't wait to go back and try some more food there though.

A cute Spanish restaurant hidden away in one of many Bandra streets.

The decor is very traditional so you do feel like you are sitting in a Spanish home.

They have great options spread across breakfast, appetizers, mains & dessert. They also serve good coffee and authentic Spanish coffee.

Been their twice so far and the food has been good, their is room for improvement in flavour as I felt it wasn't seasoned well enough for my pallet.

We tried the
Eggs benedict with chorizo - was good
Potato bravas - packed flavour
Prawn in garlic and chilli oil - the prawns has a weird taste
Croquettes -ham & cheese - was good.

Definitely give this place a try when looking for something new

ordered bombil fry and solkadhi. Bombil were pretty small and lacked taste as well. Solkadhi was spicy. Not enjoyed meal at all.

This is a very good remembrance for the experience we had. The hold some food specialities that make us go to them again and again. If there are some place in town where you can really get some homemade food this is going to be on the top list. May it be the chutneys for the tandooritandoorior the Tandoori itself, I think this is a place that you cannot miss do not go. The staff is courteous and also very very willing to go to extra mile to make your experience awesome. Make sure you order the thalis and Tandoori item there for sure. We love them for whatever they make and serve for our ever craving souls of roaming foodies. If you folks are one of them please feel free to jump in there and Grab a bite.

The ambience of restaurant is good. The food is fine quality and quantity wise. I found the salt was less in all the items of Surmai Thali..may be they kept it as per customer's preference so we can add it later. I would give 4 out of 5 as rest of the things like service, location is good. Enjoy having dinner here. Good for family dining.

reviews.text:
Nice ambience.
Great variety of food thanks to so many restaurants/ stalls. The food was fine, not so amazing. Some restaurants had amazing variety and dishes. Would have really loved to have more dessert options and also food from Socials.
But overall a great place to hang out.

This place has such an amazing ambience with a lush green vertical garden on the inside. They have amazing options in food. I loved the place. My friends and I spent a good amount of time in there since we had reached early at 6 pm. You must check out this place.

A very lively atmosphere, this place has a menu with multiple varieties available! Tried a cocktail called Thai Maalish. Would not recommend it. The nachos are good! They also serve Jain food on request. The interiors are really good and give it a festive vibe.

A food court kind of a set up makes it a really nice place to hangout. You have loads of options to choose from, various cuisines to try out. The fact that you can order a variety of small dishes from different places really appeals to some. The ambience is super cool. Recently they have added table service for which you will be charged in the bill but it makes things a lot easier now. Occasionally they do project sports on the screen. A nice place to visit if you find yourself in Kamla mills and can't figure out what you wanna eat. Come here and try a little of everything!

Concept of the restaurant is quite clear: Flea Bazaar of Food from around the world and India, and the decor manages to.communicate the same. 

But as far as putting that concept into action is when it goes either wrong or right....

For Flea Bazaar it goes quite wrong. Half of the things on the menu weren't available. And out of the limited choice we had to choose from, nothing quite interesting. 

Music was good and whatever we ordered on the plate was decent enough but not up to the standards one would think of. 

In all, a decent place to catch up with friends.

Lovely place. Great taste. Kind staff. Down to Earth Owner!

One should just visit this place in Mumbai if you love seafoods üòç‚ô•Ô∏è

I have been here for over 10 years and Francis has managed to maintain the highest quality for all this time.Crab Butter Garlic,Neer Dosa,Bombil Fry,Rice and Mild Goan Prawn curry washed down with Sol Kadi.
Food Heaven!

Attention sea food lovers, you have to try this place out. I don't think any review would do any justice to the delicious and pure awesomeness of the place and food. The gentleman who owns the place (I am guessing so because there are pictures of him all over the place) was kind enough to recommend what we must try. Since some of us are anti bones, they cleaned the fish up and just served the meat for us. Every single dish, from the prawns to squid were just amazing. Oh and then, just finish off your meal with some authentic Goan Bibinica!

This is really the place you should be to eat innovative and local seafood. Bland version also available. Clean toilet and parking available. Nicely laid down traditional table and cutlery. reviews.text: Classy and calm place. Amazing way to spend the afternoon, by the race course. Food is equally awesome here. The taste is quite authentic and sumptuous. Quantity is decent enough too, for the price and the view. Only the service can be more prompt, especially the senior staff. Else, a great place to spend time

The restaurant, located inside the Mahalaxmi race course, gives an amazing view of the entire place. While you can enjoy the mouth watering food inside, you can enjoy the lush green view of the race course. I would recommend it for a lunch outing, rather than dinner, since the view is breathtaking in the day. Gorge on their kebabs or continental surprises, as all come as perfect for the taste buds. It's ideal for a romantic date in the heart of the city.

The restaurant is situated in mahalaxmi race course so this place is green and has a great and chilled climate because of the trees the ambience near the restaurant is amazing the ambience of the restaurant is very much classy the bar table looks very awesome and the food we had was panner shashlik which was amazing the price is overpriced but it's worth it and visit this place during evening time

Ambiance is perfect, with the old structure and long hanging chandeliers.
It definitely has the old world charm and it surely is one of the best located places that we have in mumbai, with overlooking the race course.
Coming to food - well, it was good food, nothing to complain about. However the service was terrible and sloppy as the servers at our table were having an argument about something and was not something with listening to.

Fantastic location and well maintained place . I dint feel like i was in Mumbai . Amazing food. The place was all greenish . Indian food was yummy. Just for the beautiful cozy atmosphere and food , I recommend you to visit this place .  How ever staff deserve 1/10 rating. I was trying to make an order and staff dint even bother to come and was postponing my order asking me to wait more etc . It took 45 mins for them to come to my table and take order !!!! Such a rude behaviour. Recommend you to take appointments early as place can be crowded on weekends .

reviews.text: Go Biryan is a famous Delivery only outlet that delivers 17 distinct and unique biryanis including 4 vegetarian options that come in 5 sizes namely Prince for the light eater, King for the heavy eater, Emperor serves 2, Royal family serves 3-4 and Kingdom which serves 8-10 pax.

Any Late Night Carver's for biryani then go for
Go Biryan !!

They have 4 different outlets located in Mumbai till now.

I tried the outlet located at Lokhandwala in Andheri West
Serving some pocket woth and tasty Biryani's with some other Mughlai and North Indian Dishes.

A special kind of happiness when you recieve your order some 20 mins early and you just hogg in to enjoy the food.

Yes! You heard that right. Go Biryan tries its best to give the delivery most priority with a perfection of handle and care.
So you may need not worry about how the delivery will be? , will it be early or late? , etc etc...

So now lets start which what i got for my cravings.

-> I tried the personal recommendation of
"BUTTER CHICKEN BIRYANI" which was an absolute combo of butterchicken tossed and made with the indian rice with long size rice with amazing aromatic sense which will surely drool you to eat it faster. The taste was also up to perfection, the chicken pieces were plenty in number, the amount of rice and gravy they offer for a prince size box is enough for a person. You may go for this option if you are a big fan of Butter Chicken üòã.

-> Later i tried my own choice of "SCHEZWAN CHICKEN TIKKA BIRYANI"
A fusion of India & China, Chicken dum biryani with shezwan chicken tikka with a blend of spices with macro Chicken pieces with a classic dum in biryani. This can also be ordered in different size. Quite Aromatic and drool worthy for Biryani lovers in Mumbai
That are - Prince size, King size, or family pack which may serve 4 people.

The next on my ordering list is
-> MUTTON SEEKH KEBAB accompanying Reshami Paratha which was a whole wheat paratha.
The Seekh made of Mutton Kheema with a less spice but i felt it could be better by a more marination and using spices a quite more in quantity. The quality was at its best. Presented with some lemon, coriander leaves.
The Reshami Paratha made of whole wheat ,even after the delivery it was easy to chew for more 30 mins. It would be better if you eat as delivered, it tastes way too good with seekh. But if you really wana eat seekh only except the biryani there are much more places to order the seekh kebab.

So my final call was the
-> Phirni - Phirni made of rice served in Shikoras flavoured in cardamom, almond slices and pistachios its an amazing mughal indian based dessert. Specially made in different flavours in the holy month of Ramzaan, i got this dessert in odd time but with the same taste.

So i started my meal with some mouth watering Biryani and ended with India's favourite dessert Phirni.

Rating :
Taste - ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
Delivery speed - ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è

Amazing place for late night cravers

Go biryan is a favourite when we crave biryani of any sort be it veg or non veg. The range of varieties that they host is a delight. They have categories as per servings wherein "king" serves for a completely satisfying meal for two people. Their variety in starters is something that you must try. From rolls to tikkas to kebabs, we have tried it all and everything has set a new benchmark for us.

The packaging of food is commendable. We would only suggest if they can provide some Eco- friendly wooden cutlery along with the food, it would be very helpful.

The briyani they serve has a different taste in them them they smell so amazing than a half a mile person can also smell it on should try out the dum ghost briyani and the dum chicken briyani the Rita they serve with the briyani is the best Rita that I have been tasted till now

Popularly known for its Biryanis, Go Biryan does absolute justice to its name. I'd ordered food from here. The delivery was made in time and the packaging was tamper proof. The food was hot and the aroma of the biryani was just amazing. 

We'd ordered:

1. Paneer Tikka Biryani - This tasted really good and the caramelized onions were just amazing.

2. Paneer Makhani Biryani - This tasted really good. It had sufficient amount of paneer and the taste was just perfect. Highly recommended! 

3. Paneer Makhani and Malabari Paratha - They went really well with each other. The Paneer Makhani was incredible and the parathas were soft. Highly recommended!

Mr Suhas has come up with this fabulous chain of restaurant and we simply look forward to visiting the restaurant again.

reviews.text: The Bangda curry is awesome. Just like they do in the konkan villages.The correct synthesis of triphal and green chillies was a culinary operatic melody!  The fried prawns were crispy yet with a juicy centre, not the rubbery stuff one gets in most restaurants. Try to go in the afternoon on a Tuesday, no crowds. It opens at 1130.
The taste is not similar as it use to be very tasty and authentic, 10 years back of this hotel, but it's worth it's price, quality and quantity.

This place is very famous for continental food. You get all type of fish as well as chicken thalis available here. The thali is in the range of 300 to 450. They also have their special gomantak thali for 450. With the thali they give you fish fry, fish curry(without fish in it) rice and solkadi. To be frank the food is very Basic with no extra taste. If you love spicy food sorry guys this place is not meant for you all. Go watch my video on YouTube on my channel the trending vlog for detail review.

Hi Guys,
I visited here yesterday after a lonnggggg time.
Basically the best malvani/kokani nonveg seafood restaurant in town.
I ordered the Mutton sukha thali costs 320 with vade and 280 with normal chapatis.
The thali consist of suka mutton,One gravy , 4 piece wade ,rice and solkadi.
The taste was amazing.
But i feel the mutton was not cooked well.It was more rubbery and chewy texture so not really enjoyed the pieces .
But the gravy and the masala the vades was amazing 10/10 for that.
Overall a great experience.
The next time will tey some chicken and sea food dished.
The timings are 11.30-4.00 & 7.30 - 11.30 in night.

reviews.text:
Service: Peculiar is always the customer service of every outlet & this one did outclass all others. Very kind and respectful staff with all the knowledge about ingredients and suggestions to chip in with.
Ambience: One amazing decor with vibrant colors and thus antique features within makes this place a wonderful one to have food with fun and makes it look even more cozy. Awesome way to keep it lit.
Food: Off course had a great time with food as it just melted with my taste buds with ease and satisfied the tummy to the fullest. Amazing meal with a crazy supreme thali to finish off with made my evening. Lovely tinge to every spice mixed in the food and thus gives the exact flavour from the south.
Super meal. Great outlet. One amazing service. Cheers

I visited this amazing place gughan-a south indian restaurant ‚ù§Ô∏èthis place serves you authentic south indian food‚ù§Ô∏èstaff was really good and service was excellent :)
I had this amazing milagapodi idlis as starters. They were amazing. Then I had upma, onion rava dosa and maysoore cheese dosa:) they all were excellent. Perfect cooked especially maysoore cheese dosa. Then I had filter kappi‚ù§Ô∏èone of the best things you should try at this place.
Then I had a madras meal(unlimited) which literally made me feel like I was in south india‚ù§Ô∏èthere were soo many items in that small banana leaf:) this was traditional and I loved it:) this place has a pretty ambience üòª
South food lovers must try this placeüíØ

One of the nicest and authentic South Indian restaurant I've found in Mumbai  which serves authentic South Indian cuisines which include a huge variety of dosa, idli and many other delicacies. Also their filter cofee is amazing.

Loved the place with superb ambience well maintained. All south Indian lovers must visit once I loved all the food also very good quantity I have never seen anywer. Quick service with good quantity staff excellent hospitality.

Gughan is a supreme south Indian food serving place which is very much famous for their food and also they are nominated in The Times for the best South Indian food serving place. They have a variety of South Indian dishes to try and it has a authentic and good taste. I have tried few of them which were very good in taste and it was giving the feel that I was in some South place and having it. The ambience is very nice and has a comfortable seating with good interior.
I have tried
1. Rasam Vadai: the vada was dipped in rasam and also served with coconut chutney in side, it was very good in taste and the rasam was delicious.
2. Ghee Milagapodi Idli: it is a folk dish which is very famous in south, it is served with sambhar, coconut chutney and tomato chutney. Idli is fried in some spices and served with this three, it was very good in taste.
3. Payasam: this is the very popular dessert from south, which is made of sabudana and some sevai and milk, it was very tasty.

reviews.text:

There is no sincere love than love for food... When you have a half day and your next to Crawford Market just wander...... you will definitely find something..... I found this joint..... There is always wanting in this restaurant it is better you go early.....
The food is really good.... The ambiance is decent.... The service is super fast.....very cost effective....
I tried couple of things
1) chicken Taronest...4/5.... It's there signature dish only available on weekends it's worth trying soft chicken chunks in a basket made out of crispy fried noodles.
2) mutton buna with naan roti 4/5..... Quantity could be slightly more...
3) fruit salad with ice cream...3/5.
Would definitely like to visit again to try something new.....

reviews.text:
Gustoso!!

A Beaut diner, a snug zone (revamped) to indulge into the authentic Italian cuisine. New Additions To The Menu ‚ô•Ô∏è

Soup
Zuppa Di Cipolle Con Tortellini Di Parmigiano
Roasted onion soup in brown butter, had a mild cheesey essence, lovely consistency effortless on palate, garnished with saffron sprigs was delish. You got to delevop a taste for it, eventually you will.

Salad
Insalata Di Cavolo E Quinoa
Kale and quinoa salad with roasted almonds, bell peppers, avocado tossed in honey lemon vinaigrette, sweet lite and nutritious loved the dressing of the salad that sweetish tinge got my heart. ü•ó‚ô•Ô∏è

Sipped On The Mocktails This Time, Cheers To The Mixologist!

Siam Fresh
Refreshing! Call it a lemongrass mojito

Henley Tonic
Cumcumber, lemon juice, tonic water.. Unfortunately Tad bitter, the cucumber was a bitter one 1/10 cases! Overlooked!

True Passion
The Tangy Citric Twist, Passion fruit puree +fresh grapefruit juice + lemon juice, cinnamon syrup was good.

French Kiss
Nostalgia! Raspberry puree muddled with honey vanilla syrup + lemon & orange juice! Slurpicious!!

Antipasti

Burratta
Puffed hand bread filled with fresh burratta restingon a bed of arugula with San Marzano tomatoes + Marinara Sauce consistency of the burratta was wow!!

Frittura Di Gamberi E Calamari
Batter fried king prawns and calamari served with lemon aicli goes well as an accompaniment for a drink.

Pasta

Classic!! Homemade Fettuccine in lamb ragu A must try. Not going into deets this was yumazing.

Canelloni Gratinati
Homemade cannelloni filled with ricotta (l and spinach the ricotta was next level + enveloped with tomato and bechamel sauce, looked a little messy but it was scrumptious!

Pizza

Pollo Picante
Thin crust pizza topped with minced chicken (spicy) in san marzano tomato sauce + mozarella, topped with jalepenos this was hott served with chilli infused olive oil. If you like it spicy, this one's for you.

Roasted chicken herbed topped with mozarella + bellpepper reduction & rosemary oil, crust on fleek non spicy loved it.

Dessert

Tiramisu: Classic!

Millefoglie sbriciolata
You Cannot Miss On This!! This was Suaaaaave!! One of the finest desserts iv had in recent times!
Millefoglie = A Thousand Leaves
Sbriciolata = Crumbled
Flaky puffs deconstructed with custard partially oozing out (loved the citric flavor of the custard) plated with fresh berries, This was wow! This Is To Live For!! Go for it

Overall,

Not The Usual Stuff, Devour On Authenticity!!

If you are A Lactose Intolerant, You may be in a fix, but the cheese in every prep is wow. If you love the Italian cuisine, You should visit here! A beaut experience!!

Instagram@anfernandesss

Gustoso was recently renovated and hence we went to check it out. The ambience is beautiful like a bar in Italy. In some sections you can sit right next to their open kitchen. We ordered a Diavola pizza. The pizza was brilliant is every sense. Perfect bread, beautifully done tomato base and the meat was spectacular. The spaghetti carbonara was a downer. Have had much better. Lastly the Chocolate Gelato was smooth lingering on the palate. Loved it. 
Overall felt the prices have rocketed.

Gustoso is an amazing Italian restaurant located at Gowalia tank which serves authentic italian food. It's a beautiful cozy place with good music. Seating arrangement is really nice and service is amazing. Very friendly and Cooperative staff. Valet is available.

Food we ordered.

Bruschetta (5/5)

Five cheese platter (5/5)

Indianapoli (we got some rocket leaves as add ons) (5/5)

Panna Cotta (5/5)

Espresso croquant (5/5)

Espresso (5/5)

Hot toddi (5/5)

We had wonderful experience here. I would highly recommend this place.

Dined last night at the newly renovated Gustoso, Kemps Corner. What‚Äôs changed- Prices have skyrocketed and portion sizes have become half. It‚Äôs one thing to raise prices, but to make portions so small that they don‚Äôt even satisfy one person is really ridiculous! The pizzas are the only saving grace. Alcohol prices are also absurdly high. One can‚Äôt even enjoy a decent glass wine below Rs.1000 per glass. The management seems to have the misconception that they are some Michelin star fine dine restaurant! They need to come back to earth or people will stop patronising soon. 
The earlier decor was bright and cheerful but now it‚Äôs become really dark and dingy, more like a lounge bar. Seriously wonder what the management is doing.

The fried king prawns and the kalamari was absolutely heavenly to the palate
The garlic bread with cheese finger licking
The pasta superb
The pizza never had anything like this 
Just too amazing 
Perfect blend of spices chicken and the crust too good
The salmon succulent and delicious

 Safety and hygiene are handled perfectly.

Gymkhana 91 Bar & Kitchen is a restaurant situated in Lower Parel. With the weekend just upon us, we were craving for some delicious, lip-smacking food and having heard so much about this restaurant, we decided to order in. 

Their menu consists of an eclectic array of dishes that fall under various cuisines, namely, Modern Indian, Japanese, Thai, Burmese and Chinese to choose from, which certainly leaves you spoilt for choice. 

During this current pandemic, hygiene and safety is of utmost priority. Well, I must highlight the fact that the food from Gymkhana 91 Bar & Kitchen was neatly packed and the restaurant had certainly taken steps to ensure that the food is safe and hygienic. Our order arrived on time and the aroma of the food was mind-blowing, and oh well, we just couldn‚Äôt wait to dig in.

Here‚Äôs the brief of our meal:

1) Burmese Khow Suey With Chicken Fillets ‚Äì An aromatic, flavour-packed curry made up of ground spices, coconut milk, veggies and tender chicken pieces. It came along with noodles and was served along with 7 condiments ‚Äì chopped green chillies and wedges of lime, crispy fried garlic, fried onions, sliced spring onions, crushed peanuts, boiled egg and crispy noodles. This curry was absolute comfort food and my absolute all-time favourite! Love the fact that the coconut milk added to the subtlety of the curry perfectly. This curry is a MUST-ORDER and is certainly worth every penny. Highly, highly recommended.

2) Sri Lankan Chicken Sambal Curry ‚Äì A fragrant curry made up of tamarind, curry leaves and a chilly paste. The Sambal curry also had a lovely subtle hit from the coconut milk and was served along with exotic veggies and pieces of chicken. Definitely another dish that is soulful and a complete delight to the palate. Highly recommended.

3) Chicken Mussalam Masala ‚Äì A rich, thick and delicious traditional orange Mughlai Chicken curry which comprised of pieces of chicken as well as chicken kheema, and best enjoyed with a naan, roti or rice. Tasted good.

On the whole, this meal certainly was a great start to our weekend and we were happy with the delicious, tasty food as well as the portion sizes. Certainly a great place to order food from as the food is not only delicious but also safe and hygienic. Will definitely order again!

After a long time we planned to order restaurant food and thus we turned up to one of our most trusted brand .  

I am  really happy with the safe and hygienic way in which this restaurant served our favourite food to us.

My  Recommendations
Srilankan Sambal Curry
Lajawab Shahi Paneer 
Schezwan Noodles

Was browsing through Zomato and came across this place which by the name sounds fascinating and hence decided to go through its menu and it was extensive. The next thing I was building my cart and let me take you through my experience.
1 Paneer Lazeez: Start has to be with a starter and Paneer is always the go-to-dish for us Vegetarians. It turned out to be awesome as it was perfectly marinated and creamy. Paneer was tender soft, 6 thick cubes of marinated Paneer blended with Capsicums & Onions, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED üëåüëåüëå
2. Schezwan Combo Rice: Best of the lot, Chinese is my all time favorite and this was fabulous. The quality of rice was truly elegant and so perfectly cooked and blended with gravy with lot of veggies- beans, carrots, onions, spring onions, gherkins and Cucumber . The best taste and satisfaction achieved after a very long time having Schezwan Rice, HIGHLY HIGHLY RECOMMENDED üí•üí•üí•üí•üí•
3 Subz Vilayat Dum Biryani: Biryani with fragrant rice , sauted onions on top, Masala blend was perfect and moderate veggies but delicious to give you that cherishable experience. The innovative piece here was use of Gherkins, loved that part HIGHLY RECOMMENDED üí•üí•üí•üí•
4 Paneer Achari Tikka Roll : Very good stuffing with enormous amounts of Cottage Cheese and Achari enough to give you an Umm experience, 
RECOMMENDED üí•üí•
All in all a delightful experience, packaging is fabulous and precautions to keep the food hygienic were nice plus the messaging on the bag was delightful. Thanks @@gymkhana91 team

Gymkhana 91 Bar & Kitchen has always been my favorite place. In this pandemic I've missed having scrumptious meals. But not anymore!

Recently I ordered my favorite meals from Gymkhana 91. I was very much happy with the precautions being taken by them. Parcel comes with detailed report of temperature checks. Food packaging is totally tamper proof and spill proof. I was absolutely not worried about hygiene looking this!

I ordered kuber kulcha, paneer tikka biryani, lajawab shaahi paneer and breads. Kuber Kulcha would always be my favorite! Cheese stuffed kulcha. Paneer Tikka Biryani, comes with a massive quantity enough for 2-3 people. Super tasty and yummy! Lajawab Shahi Paneer is surely a must try! Loved having north Indian meal after sooo many days! 

Definitely gonna check and explore new dishes from Gymkhana!

reviews.text:
If you love Chinese food you must visit this restaurant. Staff is courteous and helpful. Place has pleasing ambience and soothing decor. Food quality and quantity justifies the price.
I have never been disappointed with their service and food.

Food 5/5
Ambience 5/5
Service 5/5
Hygiene 5/5

Best place for Chinese food lovers. Authentic Chinese food with delicious taste and best service. Spacious with approx 10 tables with large tables for group dining. Prices are little higher than any normal Chinese restaurant but cheaper then any end Chinese restaurants in the city. Parking can be availed by searching by going few meters away from the place.

It is a great place of you wish to try good Chinese food (Not Chindian but more on the Chinese side)
The place is small and nice but has really dim lights for the liking of many.
However you could opt it out for dinner dates or just a casual meal with friends or colleagues.
It is a tad bit heavy on the pocket considering on the locality it is situated in but you wouldn't mind the money over the food.
Does great sea foods and wok delicacies and noodles.

This place is good for indo Chinese cuisines. Ambience is good and very helpful staff. 
We ordered chicken drumsticks, dumplings, mini sizzler and noodles. 
Chicken drumsticks had very unique coating and were crispy. But the dumplings disappointed us. They were not looking like a dumpling and not good even for a taste.
Veg mini sizzler was great. 
Triple schezwan rice and red hot noodles were delicious.
Overall experience was good.

If you love Chinese food & want to eat some authentic Chinese cuisine, then you must visit the Gypsy Chinese Restaurant. Here they prepare a variety of vegetarian & non-vegetarian dishes. My favourites are soup, dumplings and noodles served here.
