reviews.text: The chic understated elegance that this fine-dining Michelin star restaurant stands for, is matched by its menu offerings of modern Cantonese food.The swish long blue bar with bartenders adeptly creating unique cocktails makes for a fascinating spectacle. The bespoke teas, especially the 'Strawberry and Champagne', is a must-have. For dessert, the 'Chocolate Raspberry Sphere', is a treat.

My much awaited visit to Hakkasan was to celebrate my daughter‚Äôs birthday. This is a perfect place to celebrate special occasions. The ambience   right from the entrance is very pleasing. You are greeted right at the entrance and all the way to the restaurant. The decor is refreshing and each table has its privacy. The bar is heavily stocked and looks awesome. We tried variety of cocktails and food and I give full marks to the food. Our server was very helpful in helping us chose the right combination of veg and non veg food. Dumpling platter is a good way to start and try different varieties. Hakkatini, signature cocktails and Signature Hakka noodles are must try. Don‚Äôt leave without trying some dessert. Amazing experience and we had such an awesome family time. Thank you team Hakkasan, will see you again soon.

What a brilliant restaurant that I took too long to visit. Fabulous service and food that is interesting but familiar. Hakkasan captures the best version of Cantonese food in Mumbai with flavours that you will feel compelled to share with your friends and family. Great place for all kinds of settings. Highly recommend as a place of choice for anniversary or birthday dinners/gatherings. Best to make a reservation prior, although the staff is lovely and accommodating.

The food is impeccable. I came for dinner on a Monday night and ordered the hot and sour soup, hakka noodles, and mixed veggies, and it was all amazing. Additionally, it was easy to make reservations, great service, friendly host. For such a fancy place, I thought the prices were quite reasonable. I just wish I got to meet a celebrity.

This restaurant is located at Bandra, with a beautiful and dim lit ambience and candled tables. The staff is great and well trained with the services. The atmosphere is soothing with soft music and lights, comfortable seatings, and arrangements. One of my most favourite restaurants for my favourite cuisine.

restaurants.address: shop no 17 18 19 20 36 37, Om Shiv Shakti, GTB Nagar JK Bhasin Marg, Sion Koliwada Opposite Building No.1 G.T.B.Nagar, G.T.B.Nagar, Sector V, Sion East, Antop Hill, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400037, India

reviews.text:
Great and huge place located at Sion Koliwada with comfort sitting arrangement famous for its Chinese, Mughlai, North Indian and Sea food.

In Mocktail drinks i ordered as follows...

1)Strawberry Delight.
2)Cranberry Cooler.

Strawberry Delight was properly made got the taste of Strawberry and was good in taste.

Cranberry delight was perfectly made and was very refreshing as well as taste.

In food i ordered....

1)Mutton Bhara.
2)Hardeep Punjab Special Mushroom Tikka.
3)Mutton Peshwari.
4)Jeera Rice.

Mutton bhara presentation was good Mutton was properly coocked and was soft and its taste was up to the mark.

Hardeep Punjab Special Mushroom tikka its presentation was great mushrooms were quit big in size and filled with cheese that was awesome in taste.

Mutton peshwari was cooked well served 4 pieces of mutton with gravy was enough for 2 person. Mutton pieces were soft and taste of gravy was delicious.

Jeera rice was well made rice was of good quality and was very tasty enjoyed it. 

In Desserts i ordered Slice kulfi that was very yummy in taste.

Ambiance was awesome service was good staff were polite and very friendly neat and clean place.

Must visit once.

A place with comfortable seating arrangements. More of white background. A place that serves varieties of cuisines. Chinese as well as Indian preferably North Indian cuisine, Mughlai dishes, and of course sea food too. 

I visited the place on Friday evening and it was all packed by 9 pm. More of a family restaurant. I saw many a families having dinner there. 

Generally I prefer to have non veg food but looking at a delicious menu here, I tried all vegetarian food and it was awesome. Appetizer as well as main course were delicious. 

Tried a few mocktails and they were worth every penny you would end up paying. 

Pinacolada: My usual drink. When in confusion, choose pinacolada. They had it perfectly. The blend was proportionate in a perfect way. Pineapple with coconut. Vanilla ice cream. 

Fruit punch: Mix of fruits. I requested them to make it without sugar syrup and they rightly did so. Refreshing. Fresh fruits. One of the best fruit punch preparations, I had in recent time. A bit tangy. 

The staff is very cooperative and helped me in deciding my orders. 

Tandoor broccoli and paneer: Generally, these two are different dishes: tandoor paneer and tandoor broccoli. I requested them to have it combined and they obliged it happily. Served with green chutney and red sauce. Perfectly grilled veggies. Delicious. Luscious paneer. Broccoli too was delicious. Paneer topped with cheese and coriander. Broccoli also topped with coriander. Onion slaw topped with mint and lemon. Broccoli had mustard feel as it was marinated with mustard sauce. Paneer was grilled along with onion, capsicum, and pineapple. 

Hara bhara kebab with galouti kebab: Melting kebabs. Galouti kebabs were better than hara bhara kebab but again this is sin comparing two food dishes, isn't it? Loved both the kebabs. Served with tomato sauce. Galouti kebab were made from beetroot. Filled with cheese and cream. 

In main course, we had tawa mushroom along with chura paratha. 

Tawa mushroom was cooked properly. Fresh mushroom. Gravy was perfectly fine. Goes well with chura paratha. Mushroom gravy had capsicum, bell peppers. Topped with coriander. Red gravy. Delicious. Paratha was something unique, it was more like warqi paratha. 

In dessert, we had gulab jamun rabdi. Delicious rabdi topped with gulab jamun. Perfectly sweetened rabdi. Loved the dessert too. Chilled rabdi served with hot gulab jamun. Topped with dry fruits. 

Overall, this is a nice place. The food is good. They have given emphasis on hygiene also. Cleanliness was upto the mark.

Longing for lip smacking Punjabi food then hardeep Punjab is perfect place to have delicious authentic Punjabi as well as north Indian Chinese as a well as mughlai food .
I was with my Friend .
The place is very huge I loved the way they have utilized the space .
Seating is so comfortable decor is done well .
Staff is courteous they helped us to choose the best .
The mocktails and food which we tried were ..
Mocktails: 
Cool blue and virgin pinacolada 
The mocktails was chilled ad refreshing the taste was very good.
I personally recommend cool blue .
Appetizer: 
Chaska maska chicken tikka:
It was suggested by there staff and we decided to try it out .
Well coming to the presentation it was cooked and severed in clay pot .and it tasted amazingly delicious I never had something like that before .
The chicken places were so juicy and tender It just got melted in mouth .this hi highly recommend dish .
Tiranga chicken tikka:
This dish looks so inviting and it tasted really good.
Chicken tikka prepared is three spices one of them is malai tikka ,pudina tikka and regular chicken tikka.each of them were rightly spiced.
In main course we ordered :
Chicken tikka masala which was served with butter kulcha it was so tasty perfectly cooked the chicken pieces were so juicy . and the gravy was rich and creamy .
The butter kulchas was loaded with ample amount of butter on it .
It was superb combination .
Dessert :
Gulab jamun with rabadi this is the best dessert I had till date.
The rabdi was so creamy and moderately sweet it just won my heart.
Would definitely visit this place in future.

In Mumbai, Hardeep Punjab, Mini Punjab, Ram Punjab, Sher-e-Punjab... for me, these are doyens as far as authentic Punjabi Cusine is considered and treasure fond memories of my frequent visits.
The other day landed up at Hardeep for a takeaway, at GTB Nagar (Sion Koliwada).
While everything is great out here, my fav is the Butter Chicken with Garlic Nan. 
One dish at a time and enjoy every morsel.
A day well spent üíÉüèº‚ù§Ô∏èüòÑ
Best place to have a Punjabi Indian Food at affordable price. Please try their desserts you will definitely love it.  gulabjaam Rabdi is yummy...

reviews.text:
Worst hotel about maintaining the Hygiene... Taste is very bad... Do not drink water there... You will find a dust particles in water... Cabbage which was served with Lollipop was not fresh as well as clean... Lollipop was not fully fried... Still raw from inside...

Please üôè avoid to eat from this Hotel...

Was travelling to Nashik from Mumbai and wished to have a nice sea food lunch near thane. I usually preferred malwani sea food restaurants in thane but I was a little late and most of the restaurants close down at 3.30 pm only to open again in the evening. 
Hence, after a little search, I found Harish lunch home which served mangalorean sea food and thought of giving it a try. Have to admit that it was a winning decision.
Tried the Bombay duck fry and Surmai and prawn thali. Every dish was packed with extravagant flavours from coastal karnataka. The curry leaves and peanuts packed curry was to die for.
Highly recommended for all sea food enthusiasts!!
Ok food and quantity is also ok not more it's look like limited...but price is little bit expensive than other restaurants..... overall I just taste little bit chicken mughlai.....
Nice restaurant for seafood and non-vegetarian at reasonable price
Nice sea food place. Very reasonable as well. Good tasty food

reviews.text: After hectic shopping. Finally best taste good in dinner üç≤. And really happy with food and service.
Nice seafood restaurant having all fresh stuff. They also have chicken, mutton and veg options. The staff is courteous and the place is also reasonable and value for money.
Frontage and entry is hardly 12ft but from inside its huge place upstairs. Separate area for fmly. Authenticate food variety, superb taste, peg system..if you are non veg should visit would love it..
Excellent Sea Food. Five Star service. Good Embience. A must visit for Lunch and/or Dinner. Every time I am in Mumbai, I have made a point to at least visit once.
Love the South Indian food here! Warm people.

restaurants.address: 13 A, SA Brelvi Road, fire brigade, Parsi Bazaar St, opposite fort, Borabazar Precinct, Ballard Estate, Fort, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

reviews.text: It is a compact restaurant place near Ballard Estate which serves best sea food in the locality. We had prawns, pomphret, mackerel. Later we tried chicken masala and half fry eggs.  The restaurant also serves liquor and is a good place to spend some time. The staff was good and the services were taken care perfectly.
It's a sweet little place for great sea food at really affordable price! I ate my heart out at super basic price! The staff is also very cordial.

Good quality tasty food with a dozen variety of fish as part of its special. Value for money...and not exorbitantly priced like Apoorva or Mahesh lunch home, located around in the same area. Not very oily.  Waiters are courteous and soft spoken. Simple local crowd sit down for food and drinks. Not ideal for very large families. Two people can eat a hearty meal with two servings of wine for 1500/-.
Nice bar and restaurant, delicious dish like cori roti, mutton fry, surmai fry, very famous bar in fort

This tiny but amazing joint is sure to take true Manglorean food lovers down memory lane. It certainly did for one of us bringing back memories of past delectable authentic home food Manglorean style. So at this stop we ordered their Surmai Fry, their Mutton Sukha and Kori Roti. While all three completed hit the spot, the Surmai and Mutton took the cake. Surmai was extremely fresh, perfectly spiced and cooked perfectly. The Mutton was cooked to a 'Melt in Mouth' consistency and was prepared in thick coconut based gravy. The Kori Roti was well presented with authentic flavors. This is the joint for true Manglorean cuisine lovers when in Fort.

restaurants.address: Kings Cir, Matunga, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400019, India

reviews.text:
Health, famous snack joint at matunga circle is my favourite over the years, they have multiple outlets around Mumbai. Right from thier cheese sandwich, dosa ,to thier milkshakes all are delicious. Staff is courteous but service is bit slow during weekends due to the crowd. Best part is that it‚Äôs open till 12 and crowded always.
We had ordered Manchurian dosa and cheese chilli gril and both of them were yum. 
Thier Mango and Kiwi milkshake are also delicious.
A good place to have sandwiches and milkshakes....Pajadi Grill Sandwich and Sitafal milkshake are one of the most popular order!!!!!
Good place to hang out with friends. They have open space sitting service is good and food tastes delicious

This place is super awesome they serves awesome fast food as well as juices. The taste is too good. They gives us various types of juices to taste. They serve variety's of juices. It is located exactly opposite to the king circle matunga. One of the best place to have snacky items. They even gives Wafers with sandwiches. Nice place pls do visit once
Quality juices with thought process and nutrients

restaurants.address: 44/2179, Gandhi Nagar, Behind Maratha Store, Service Road, Highway Facing , Bandra East, Samadhan Cooperative Housing Society, Gandhi Nagar, Bandra East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400051, India

reviews.text: Food is pretty good and tasty but quantity can be increased a bit....however dining in house is much better as compared to take-away but due to current restrictions it is not possible

Been visiting the place for many years now... The taste has been same throughout the years. Has good seafood options and quality of food has been great.
Its a very simple place and service is nothing to write home about. Also make sure you reach early, otherwise you'll have very limited fish options. Place is CASH ONLY

It's a known and heavy frequented place by Bombay peeps for their coastal specials.

I enjoyed the fried fish versions they had to offer , espeythe Surmai. It was phenomenal. And yes the fish is indeed very fresh. 

Still think they can be some improvement on the curry part.

Also please note, this place does not accept cards neither serves alcohol.

They do their job the perfect way. They serve seafood, non vegetarian dishes and they serve it really well. They serve almost every type of seafood including Various types of fish, crabs, clamps and the list goes on.... 
Old style place located on the highway. But maintaining its own charm and beauty. Good staff, amazing food, chunky portions (mind you they let their hand loose) 
One star less as the rates seemed overpriced. 
Overall an amazing experience and a must visit place for those who love seafood & other non vegetarian dishes cooked the authentic way

The food quality has been the same since my childhood. This place is memories and good times. Small efficient and well lit these people are very very strict about the timings. Make sure you reach within the given time frame or else your order won't be taken. The prices here are pretty decent and pocket friendly. Also it's shut on Thursday

restaurants.address: FIFC Building, Plot No. C- 54 & 55 G Block, Bandra Kurla Complex Rd, G Block BKC, Bandra Kurla Complex, Bandra East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400051, India

reviews.text: I didn't just like the food, I absolutely loved it! It's a great setting for dining with family or for chilling with friends. Versatile that way. It has a bar, but age restrictions are only during the evenings. Enjoyed most of the dishes here. Nice ambience. Oh and unique part: the menu. The dishes so wisely named. You'll enjoy just reading through the menu, it is such a fun read!

One of the best places in BKC, we had been here for Dinner. 
The ambience is good. Comfortable sitting. The staff is friendly. The food is good and hygienic. 
The starters were good. In the main course, loved the Mutton grave. 
The Desserts were also very nice. 
Overall the presentation of all dishes was very appealing.

Loved the place, will surely visit again.

Right setting that sets the right mood. Funky Menu titles will attract your attention. Food quality is good and served in good portions. Service is bit slow. Entire seating is on single floor at same level. Overall a good hangout place to chill with friends and families.

Ambiance is good. Crowd is decent, you will find more Oldies here. Drink options are great and the cocktails were amazing. The staff is not that great, they tend to ignore you sometimes when it is busy. The location is perfect, bang in the middle of BKC. Food is average at best, did not like the snacks we ordered. Prices are like most other pubs, could have been a tad bit lower, but I won't complain.
It is a good place to chill with your friends. You'll get those bollywood feels as soon as you enter this place. The food menu was very exciting as it was a fusion of Indian and global cuisines.

restaurants.address: 759, 5th Ln, Khar, Ram Krishna Nagar, Khar West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400052, India

reviews.text:
So, I'm the person who got this place created on Google maps, Why? 
Because I liked the place a lot the ambiance is great the drinks they serve are splendid and above all the staff is very cool and happy which gives a good vibe to the place the interiors are pretty and distinct that's a plus.

P.S - proof for place creation on Google attached in screenshot below
Nearer to linking shopping street...!! Recommended to chill with friends..!!

Place pretty nicely decorated with good lighting, well spaced tables. But servers are pretty inattentive. There are few board game options to choose from. Food is great taste wise but small in quantity. Pricing is pretty decent. There are a good number of options for drinks including bucket offers and happy hours. Would give a 5 star if the service was a bit better.

The ambience is really good. The staff are really receptive and the food is totally worth the price. Really yummy. Everything we ate was delicious. I've been to hoppipola few times and everytime it's like the experience there is constant, irrespective of the location. They also have really good offers and THEY HAVE GAMES! So it's a really good place to go to, especially with a group of friends. All in all the vibe is üíØ Also, the music is really good too. This place is truly exceptional, I'd recommend!

Had a lot of good and some drinks here. The staff was helpful and courteous, keep in mind that the place is right in front of Khar Social so it‚Äôs mostly packed during the weekends. Parking space is not very easy to come by near the venue so you‚Äôll have to park a bit far from the place. The nachos here are good, so is the pizza.

reviews.text:

Black pepper sizzler, lemonade, kiwi tea, Maggie garlic bread was really good..
staff, service n hygeine also good..
Evening time mostly crowded..
But really nice place to chill n enjoy..

Best place to have Maggie. This place is absolutely for Maggie lovers. They have varieties of Maggie and taste was yummiest. Just loved it. Ambience and service was also good. One who is Maggie lovers should definitely try this cafe once..!!
We visited this place and had the most recommended maggi misal. We also had a combo of one drink and nachos with salsa and cheese. A must place to visit. Vibrant ambience. Misal maggi is a must try

A cozy place to hang out with your budds. Very chirpy, music in the background, and lots and lots of MAGGI everywhere!

Maggie Sizzler which was by far one of the best sizzlers

VFM 4/5
Ambience 4/5
Recommended üëçüèª

Nice ambience, its a small but good place. What i loved about this place is its menu. Tried its maggi burger and maggi pizza just loved it. Pizza crust was better than other big pizza brands. Will surely visit again to try other items of menu.

restaurants.address: 10-B, Ground Floor, Sindhi Nivas, Sitladevi Temple Road, Mutual Colony, Mahim West, Mahim, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400016, India

reviews.text: Its a small little place near to Mogul lane Mahim. It can seat around 10 people at a time. The service was very good and prompt. We got the food within 15 minutes. Parotta is something I miss as a keralite. ( It's not paratha !) I had good parotta here, with paneer butter masala. Overall a good place for a quick bite.

Not at all up to the mark.
The original taste has been totally changed.
They have introduced awesome meal combos which serve 4 people. The combos have good quantity and taste, and so are VFM.
Amazing food and lemon coriander soup is awesome
Awesome taste of chinese grt taste with hygiene i just loved here fried rice n lollipop. Taste is very grt once u go u will visit again n again

reviews.text: My favourite parsi restaurant in Mumbai which is so not costly, with consistent taste. They don‚Äôt have a lavish sitting or anything but if you are a foodie it can be on your check list of good places to eat in Mumbai. Things I generally order here- dhansak rice, mutton cutlet, salli keema, salli boti, badam pak, caramal custard, etc
Lovely food. Super reasonable. Nice place in a corner!

Weekly specials plus regular menu are fab. Must try are salli chicken, dhansak and lagan nu custard. Have been here umpteen times and this place just doesnt disappoint. Service is quick and place is clean. Bonus tip: do try the raspberry drink as well

Just at a corner, of Hornby View building. 

Age Old restaurant serving authentic Parsi cuisine. Interiors are average. 

We tried their, 
1) Atheli Chicken Masala Potato (thick gravy, available only on Tuesdays) 
2) Sali Kheema (kheema with sali on top) 
3) Fried Bheja (dry, in an egg) 
4) Patra Fish (Rawas, Green Masala and dry)
5) Lagan Nu Custard (Parsi Special Custard) 
6) (Prem) Chocolate Mousse (just just amazing, so rich, so dense, so full of flavour) 
7) Bread Pudding 

Food is lovely and service is very fast and with a smile. 

Rates are very reasonable.

It has a Yezdi Parked I side the cafe and the food is authentic and up to the mark Loved the service and food quality. Is inexpensive. The only thing I didn't like is tea is not served during lunch time and has specific timings

restaurants.address: Ground Floor, Vihang Recreation Club Opposite Raymonds, Pokharan Road No.1,, Tulsi Dham, Samata Nagar, Thane West, Thane, Maharashtra 400606, India

reviews.text: We really liked the place, it's very spacious. Staff is good. Food spread is not much but whatever they have and we tried was simply superb. I would recommend this place if you want to try some good Indian food.
One of the best place in thane. Food, ambiance everything is top notch.

Most delicious food I had in thane till date
I like the Ambiance and who can deny a complimentary #PaniPuri

One of the best restaurants in Thane. The food quality and taste is great. The style of serving food is very unique and innovative. It will surprise you and will make your outing at this restaurant more fun filled. Service was very good. Overall, a very good experience at this place.

Fancy #panipuri isn‚Äôt it ? 
Who els is craving for a pani puri ? 

India bistro is my go to place for A familiar menu of mixed fare & Indian meals offered in a casual, homey restaurant.

The 'Guava Kulfi with Chilli Foam' is an innovative dessert that one must sample
Look out for ‚ÄòToday‚Äôs Specials‚Äô as this one on the menu offers unique dishes
'Methi Malai Seekh' and 'Gilafi Murg', both melt-in-the-mouth and are worth-a-try

The portions are generous and are ideal for sharing. The ‚ÄòHealthy Rotis‚Äô are a bit unreasonably priced. The service is quick and alert and the staff extremely helpful. Opt for the Monday-Friday lunch buffet if in a hurry as it is quick and value-for-money too.

Dine-in¬∑ Takeaway¬∑ Delivery

restaurants.address: 1, 2nd Floor, Horizon, 37 Juhu Beach, Juhu, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400049, India

reviews.text: Great experience on the whole. Food was lovely. Ambience was great. I think on the day I went, there was a special occasion like a birthday or something which is why it was unusually noisy. A great place but on the whole.

restaurants.address: Unit No.1, 2nd Floor, Janta Industrial Estate, Senapati Bapat Marg, Lower, Parel, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400013, India

reviews.text: Riso and Ithaka are two names in one place by one management. We were seated downstairs where there was a large get together of middle aged adults which was very loud. The lighting was dim which isn't good for taking pics but enough to see what you're eating. We ordered the Zucchini Fritters which is an amazing dish served with mayo and shredded lettuce. Highly recommend for trying if you like zucchini. Then we ordered the Jain version of Monza Pizza. The crust was super thin and since it was loaded with veggies and cottage cheese the bread was bending, while I expected it to be crisp and sturdy. Nevertheless taste was good. We were disappointed with non availability of desserts we wanted that is Chocolate Fondue was available without fruits and also no Fudge Cookies were available. So we settled for the Lava Cake that was a small one with vanilla ice  cream. Overall average.

For Gujjus must visit places. Cheese garlic bread is awesome.
Quantity is good. 
1* less for tests is slight sweet side!
A bit expensive, but really good jain food available. Must try jain peta with hummus

We were so disappointed with this place and service. The hummus with onions was terrible - more like a Gujju salad. Then we ordered a plain hummus which was much better. For that portion, we asked them to warm up the pita which was better. The zaatar pizza was crisp but would not recommend it.

So the place was under renovation & it was stinking of paint & pest control. But the staff were very polite & service was all round good. The veg cream soup was deliciously thick. We also order a roisti which was good, but honestly not worth what they are charging.
All in all 3 stars is because of the friendly staff. Else it would have been rated as 2 stars because they should be closed for business when conducting renovation work. The stink when we entered was too much.

restaurants.address: 7/8, Madhav Bhuvan, Kamala Mills Compound, B' Block, Senapati Bapat Marg, Railway Colony, Opposite, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400013, India

reviews.text: Located in busy streets of Lower Parel opposite Kamla Mills, this restaurant serves food so delicious that you wont look twice before crossing this ever busy street. If you have safely reached the restaurant then time to dig into a wide range of Manglorean, Goan and Konkan delicacies and the speciality is seafood. Apart from the distracting elevator style music playing in the background which you will only hear between bites, because while you are eating food this tasty, you forget about everything else. Must try the Surmai Tawa fry, Bharela Bombil, Surmai Gassi and Prawns Pulimunchi. Finish it off with a healthy glass of solkadi and forget about work if you have eaten here for lunch

I had been to the Jai Hind Lunch home restaurant in Lower Parel with one of my best friend. We had some good non veg food. The food and service was really great. Thanks for the wonderful service by the attendant.

Read a lot about this place . Finally had a lunch date here . It's nice small place . It's little cramping for space .  Ordered Surmai Fry , Bombil fry and prawns Biryani. Both the fish fry was well done but little oily . The best dish was the Prawns Biryani.  It was purrfeectttt.. one of the best Prawns biryani o had till date. Not too spicy neither bland. It's little pricy as compared to other outlets where in we get similar seafood. We ordered the only two desert available there and both were good. Chocolate mousse and caramel pudding.

Great place to dine. Amazing seafood and non veg spread. The owners or the manager here has taken an initiative to save water and that's worth appreciation. It's a simple small step which will make a difference. He was also quite open and welcome to suggestions. I'm sure they are going to do even better with such a fantastic service and great attitude.
If you're in and around Kamala Mills you cannot afford to miss out on Jai Hind - the place to be for seafood. Only thing that spoils the mood is the waiting period.

They don‚Äôt wear a mask or gloves.
The guy at the counter is more focused on taking money than taking note of the order. 

Also the food taste so bad even my dog won‚Äôt eat it.
Unfortunately now they only serve snacks. I have noticed a bit of a dip in the food quality. Their Unlimited Thali is a must try.

A great pure veg dining place located in Malad close to Inorbit Mall on Linking Road. Best for people who value quality and look for pure veg food. Wide variety. Got an outdoor dining area, an indoor area, sweet and darsan shop, banquets. A wholesome place. Delivery options as well available. Quick service.
Paneer tikka is the best part of these place. Overall the food is always best . A great yumilicious experience won't get disappointed and will have a big smile on your face after having the food

Located in Malad Linking road. The ambience is bright. Ample sitting. Friendly staff. Quality food. Have a good Verity in the menu. Few of the dishes are really authentic. A very good choice to go with family and friends for a vegetarian treat.

restaurants.Cuisines: American, Mexican, Italian, Burger, Salad, Healthy Food
restaurants.address: 7A & 7B, Beach Apartment, JP Rd, Opp. Palm, Aram Nagar Part 2, Machlimar, Versova, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400061, India

reviews.text: There is not one dish on their menu that will disappoint... reasonable prices and great ambience. Staff is very kind and eating their nachos is a must. There are some weird dishes on there like the deconstructed beet root tacos, but trust me it turned out to be the beat dish I‚Äôve ever had. It‚Äôs a must order dish!!!

A quirky little cafe situated right opposite Versova Beach. Finding it can be a little difficult as we passed this place by twice and then finally saw the tiny door and sign-board. There are 3 seating areas - the ground floor which consists mainly of the bar, the Alice-in-wonderland-esque mezzanine floor and the outdoor seating area. The decor is amazing and the restored apartment vibe can be felt. There are tons of books and games to help you pass the time while you're waiting for your food. Veg and non-veg options are both great. We called for fries, sandwiches and flower-pot dessert. The fries and sandwiches were great but the fritters that came with the sandwiches were partially cooked and we had to ask the server to replace them - which was done in a jiffy. The only thing we did not enjoy was the flower pot as it didn't have any flavour and was just a big pot of ice-cream. 
A great place for hanging out with friends after work or on a lazy weekend.

Been here plenty of times and just LOVE the place. Ambience and beautiful and spacious. Walls adorned with quirky cabinets and books. Large groups can sit on the ground floor. Smaller ones on the 1st floor. They also have a smoking section for groups who want to smoke with dinner. They have a jukebox which allows you to listen to the music of your choice while you done.

The food is great. Although priced a bit on the higher size, the quality and quantity of food is totally worth it. Loved their Seafood platter and the chicken mains. But the star of the show is definitely the Flowerpot Surprise. But beware, if you have an average sweet tooth then better bring a gang of 4 at least to finish it.

The place is a little hard to spot in moving traffic. And is located on a busy road. But they have plenty of valet parking, so no issues there. Lovely place! Worth a visit!

After a long time, a restaurant that has lived up to every expectation I've had and exceeded too!
Jamjar has been a place I've wanted to visit for the longest time, and it was totally worth the wait...
The burger, was hands down the best burger I've eaten so far! The taste, texture, flavours, portion et all.
I ate the Three cheese burger, the pull apart pao, hummus, the rum punch, hazelnut ice cream and cheesecake ice cream, and the overloaded gooey nachos!
It was all AMAZING! 
I NEED TO GO BACK!
The big bad foodie was very very happy!

The ambience is marvelous! The food was fresh and crisp. The service was also very coordinated and they valued our feedback a lot. Worth recommending to my fellow foodies! Would love to visit the place again. The retro vibe is unmatched anywhere else. From the music Jukebox to the retro cameras and televisions to the collection of books, games and so forth.

reviews.text: lovely moment... i really missing

A tiny joint that caters till late night. With interesting choices for Tandoori and Biryani lovers. Got the food quicker than I ordered and tasted really good. Recommended for late night cravings after some drinks.

Jantar mantar.

I was craving for Naans ever since I've come back from my trip to Delhi. I found this hidden gem called Jantar Mantar in juhu to have their Paneer tikka roomali roll and  Paneer Zaikedar Naan Turnover. I mean the food is great, you can just take your car, and drive to this place and have literally good quality and quantity food from here. Especially, the non veg is top notch. Gonna be back for more!

restaurants.Cuisines: Fast Food, North Indian, Parsi, Desserts
restaurants.address: 11, Vikas Building, Bank Street, Near, Horniman Circle, Kala Ghoda, Fort, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

reviews.text:
Recently revisited this eatery for a takeaway, the luxury of dine in experiences being lost to COVID.
Everything they make is done fabulously well. 
The garlic cheese croissant is very soft and has filling upto the last bite. One can really taste the garlic so it isn't just an overdose of cheese. This is how a garlic cheese croissant ought to be made.
The chicken mayo sandwich is delicious. It is the old school/classic version without any novel 'twist' ruining it. Just soft white bread (without sides) with a very subtly flavoured chicken filling drenched in mayonnaise.
The chicken patties, which seem more like puff pastry, are fantastic. Creamy chicken stuffing encased within layers of flaky pastry firm enough not to start disintegrating or falling apart at each bite.
The mutton cutlets are crisp on the outside and firm on the inside. The fries that are served along with the cutlets are absolutely fresh and have a crunch.
The choco lava cake has a delicious crust and a soft, gooey centre. Just how it should be.
All the fare we ordered were fairly regularly available items, nothing really fancy. This eatery does them so well that a lot of other eateries serving similar items could use these as a template and learn from them
Taste was really okay... Not so great that you would really fall in love with it....
Sandwiches are really Good. Try Chicken Sandwich. The bread quality and the cleaned cooked chicken tastes awesome

One of the best places to be for Parsi food. Cozy atmosphere, welcoming staff n awesome food. What else you need for a relaxing Saturday evening :-) 
Liver the spicy chicken burger. The strawberry cheesecake was so yummy that I had to order another one üòã

As I am a foodie, All my friends from Mumbai recommended to visit this place. Very good Parisian food with delicious taste and quality. We ordered mutton dhansak, Berry pulao and raspberry soda. My personal favourite was Bun Maska üòä. We liked the food so much that we bought Mawa cake for home to go. Must try place for all foodies.

restaurants.address: C 57, G Block BKC, Bandra Kurla Complex, Bandra East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400051, India

reviews.text: The experience was very nice. They had set menu for day which was very good. We were able to taste all the flavors. There was just one suggestion for the desert the layer of the cream on the cake should be less and motichur ladoo spread should have been more.

Bangladeshi Food Festival
Date 12th - 21th of April 
Lunch 12 - 3pm
Dinner 7 - 11.30pm
Around INR 5,200 for 2 persons without alcohol exclusive taxes.. 

10 day celebration to welcome Bengali New Year, Poila Boisakh.. 

Created the perfect mood in Jyran, Sofitel BKC...
This luxury property is famous for celebrating Food Festivals with all the festivities and authentic delicacies prepared by famous visiting chefs..

Huge chandeliers are hanging in the ceiling..
A huge open terrace is decked up beautifully..

With Home Chef Nayana Afroz
The star üéâ Chef of the Bangladeshi Food Festival Jyran - Sofitel,BKC
A good soul with a sweet smile üòç
Down to earth person üíó
An extraordinary self-made successüëèstory of an ordinary soul.. 
From my forefathers' hometown Faridpur, Dhaka, Bangladesh.

A real life inspiration for many Housewives.
Belongs to a typical Bangladeshi family of good home cooks.. 
Her cooking skills & tasty traditional recipes got lots of admirers in Bangladesh & India 
A journey of non-stop success stories.. 
Sofitel Mumbai BKC üëèüëèüëè has
started this new encouraging  trend of inviting Famous Home chefs from various states & countries for Food Festivals.. 

Ala carte set signature menu, authentic traditional delicacies inspired by the various regions of Bangladesh, curated specially by talented Chef. 
Refreshing mocktails - sugar cane mojito 
and water melon mojito were lovely.. 

Started our meal with paya yakhani Jyran - Lamb trotter cooked over night with garlic & Indian spices.

Excellent authentic appetizers -
Chicken Jali Kebab - chicken minch patty shallow fried by egg wash

Prawn Patora - shallow fried shrimp cake with mustard coriander onion

Mutton Hari Kebab - chunks of mutton marinated in Bangladeshi spices and cooked in a clay pot. 

Bangladeshi vegetable roll - deep fried vegetable crepes 

Main course was equally lovely -
Bangladeshi mutton razela - tender lamb cooked in yogurt with aromatic spices in onion gravy.. 

Bangladeshi Murgh Musallam -chicken cooked in tomato saffron gravy.. 

Narkeli Hash - Duck cooked in coconut milk with coconut paste and coconut slivers. Very tasty.
Anaaras Ilish - my all time favourite hilsa fish cooked in an innovative way.. First time tried Hilsa fish cooked in fresh pineapple gravy, not at all sweet, perfect balance of spices, made the dish very tasty..

Vegetarian dishes-
Paneer Kofta curry -dumplings of cottage cooked in almond and yogurt gravy.. 
Cholar daler turai - Bengal gram cooked with exotic spices.. 
Served with assorted breads & plain rice.. 

Two amazing traditional desserts -
Lachha custard - fried fine vermicelli softly mixed with mava mixture, mildly sweetened.. 

Green mango halwa- pudding made with raw mango, milk fudge, sugar & ghee .. Very unique and tasty, a perfect balance of sweet & sour.. 
I never visited Bangladesh. Grown up hearing about authentic amazing dishes of Bangladesh..
It's my privilege to attend this lovely food festival.
My Bengali New Year celebration became more special..
Am highly recommending to try the traditional Bangladeshi delicacies.. Very lightly cooked with mild aromatic spices.. 
Each & every dish has distinctive taste ..
Well done Home Chef Nayana Afroz. 

A big thank you to Jyran, Sofitel Group for this New Year gift to the Bengalis & foodies of Mumbai.. 

Ambiance -5/5,
Food presentation - 5/5,
Taste - 5/5,
Service - 5/5,
Hygiene - 5/5...
Wheel chair accessible
Valet parking available..
Free Wi-Fi
A fine dining restaurant with 5* facilities..
An amazing experience...

A restaurant carved with extreme opulence, luxurious golden glittering interiors, polite staff and extravagant food. Jyran is based in the star Sofitel property and all set to welcome you for a scrumptious treat be it with your family or a date, it's ideal.

The best part about Jyran is they host plethora of festivals like Bangladeshi festival and I read on the media about the ongoing Mohd Ali Road festival. This just keeps the enthusiasm going. The chefs who takeover the culinary drive during these feativals are masters of flavours and I witnessed this during Bangladeshi festival.

I enjoyed a Thali which was so satisfying with an array of dishes served.

Began with a pomegranate and sugarcane welcome drink

Then we had a murg shorba.

Next was a platter of starters.

Then was the main thali. I eat chicken hence it was customised for me with Chicken And Vegetarian dishes.

PANEER KOFTA

RICE

DAL

NAAN

MIXED VEGETABLE

CHICKEN CURRY

DRY CHICKEN (KHEEMA STYLE)

After relishing all this, the only bite I could savour was dessert. For dessert we had Dudhi Halwa and Sevaiya.

It was a good meal indeed !

I had went here for the Kashmiri Food Festival in November. The food here was amazing. We tried a lot of things and barring a few, everything was delicious. The ambience of the place is soothing. I would've given it 5 stars but the service was dismal. There were only two waiters serving 6 tables.

As they define it in Persian , lost love! I will say a love just found!
This is a wonderful place for tandoor dining at Sofitel.
Though it was afternoon, the dining was busy and happening place.
With wide range of veg and non veg menu, we went by marvelous starters and veg dishes. Meticulously developed by chefs Sadaab and Vijay Pawar, everything was excellent and melting in mouth. We had a lengthy session of eating with ever smiling Asif helping us with large servings.
There is also choice of a fixed veg and non veg menu @  4000 to 5000‚Çπ per person.
There signature dish which we particularly appreciated was Paratdaar Paneer, Daal Makhani and Biryani which is never too be missed out.

reviews.text:
Kailash Mandir is famous for Lassi since olden times. You can witness the employees wearing Hindu cap. They serve delicious lassis. All range within ‚Çπ100. Its a tiny place, super quick service. Very economical. One glass lassi can make you feel full.
In frame - Maharaja Lassi
‚Çπ80
There's abundance of dry fruits added. It is a totally worthwhile deal. Anna was hungry that evening. Trains were late and only thing that could quench his hunger was this lassi.
We give it a 5/5

Kailash Mandir Lassi & Sweets is within walking distance from Dadar station. The Consistency of Lassi is excellent. It's super smooth & sweet, with the top of cream and dry fruits. They also serve here snacks like vada pav & samosa.

Lassi was great.
Worth calling it a legend of Mumbai.
Only Shiv Kailash opposite Pune station serves better than this.
Quality is amazing and they try to maintain the higine as well.
The normal lassi is the best amongst all their offerings.
Do visit once.

Worst lassi i have ever tasted, trust me its over hyped. Their is nothing special about their lassi and the rates are even quite high.

reviews.text: Food over here is very nice and their specially good in Punjabi dishes

Kailash Parbat is a very well known chain in Mumbai, with branches all over. This one is particularly well located in the arrival area Mumbai Aiport Terminal 2, and gives you a ‚Äòback home‚Äô feeling just as you leave the exit. The food is of very good quality, and is served piping hot ‚Äì with very quick service. Go for the usual favourites ‚Äì idli sambhar, medu vada, pao bhaji, rava masala dosa....you cannot go wrong with any of these. Combine these with filter coffee or any of the fruit juices, and you have a nice meal on the go ‚Äì at any time of the day!! So whether you are arriving or waiting for someone to arrive, this is a very good choice for a quick snack or a proper meal.
Excellent Indian Veg Food. Sweets, snacks, Chole Bhatura, Dahi Vada, Chat etc.

Travelling first time to Mumbai, I decided not to test my bowels with food items fron cheap restaurants and I specifically navigated to this veg restaurant in Colaba after finding it from Zomato. They didn't disappoint with the quality and taste but the price seemed to be a little higher.
Its Good Hotel with Delicious Food...

reviews.text:
Kakke Di Hatti - A delivery kitchen is a superb option to order some lip smackling authentic food .
Words are not enough to describe the food they serve , must must try place and highly recommended.
For Starters we tried:
Murgh Kalimiri Kebab- very tender and fresh chicken , marinated in curd and kalimiri, very well cooked and super taste .
Prawns Tandoori- fresh water prawns with good size and green chutney makes it's more delicious.
For mains we ordered:
Murgh Amritsari : good preparation and tasty gravy and tender fresh chicken pieces went well with Cheese Garlic Naan.
Dal Makhani- pure Ghee and butter, flavour of Punjab and authentic dish preparation.
Chicken Tikka Biryani: long grain basmati rice with nice chicken Tikka pieces in it , very aromatic. 
Cheese Garlic Naan: fully cheese loaded went well with above main course.
Sweets:
Gulab Jambun and Rabdi : soft large 1 piece served , thick fresh Rabdi 
To sum it up they deserve 10/10 for food packaging and presentation.
Must try always place , go try try..
Good quatilty and good quantities yumies yumies

To start with, i loved the place and will definitely be visiting it again. This place is basically from delhi and definitely gets some good food. It has a outdoor seating and service is super quick. From chicken to mutton to paneer, everything was cooked to perfection. Dal makhani stole our heart.! Everything was rich in flavours & taste. Definitely one of the places that serve real good punjabi food! A big thumbs up to the place.
Small outlet which offers delhi style dishes that are mouth watery. The outlet gets a lot by online ordering but yet they have some outdoor seating arrangement. The dishes are the best to taste buds.

One of the best Delhi outlet is in Mumbai now. What are you waiting for, head over to this small , tiny outlet that offers amazing delicious food and is worth every penny . Though the ambience might not appeal you but it is decent enough to have a dine for their awesome food.
Starting with Paneer Tikka Roll , damn the roll was so heavy stuffed with loads of paneer and the sauce and taste just blends completely well . It is a perfect start to your dine.
A perfect kick off lead us to Paneer Malai Tikka and Tandoori Soya Chaap . Soft paneer with the malai and onions garnished just mouth watering and something to crave for. Amazing, Tandoori Soya Chaap just perfectly made and couldn't ask much more..
After a heavy start , we ordered laccha Paratha and Dal makhani . Loads of ghee on the yummy Dal Makhani is what all North Indians should definitely try. Laccha Paratha tasted okayish .

Overall had a very decent experience. Fast service , delicious food is what defines this place.

reviews.text:
A great place for family visits. Quality, flavor, ambience are top notch. The only thing is starters are way too expensive as compared to main course in terms of quantity. We ordered prawns starters, biryani (chicken duh!) and almond brownie with vanilla ice-cream which was delicious! 
     In a nutshell, a  great place for experiencing an authentic maharashtrian flavor.

We had lunch today here.We ordered the following dishes.

1.Cucumber Mint Cooler- It was a mocktail made out of cucumber and mint.Fine chopped cucumber,mint,salt and soda.It was a good refreshing drink

2.Chaas- Could have been more better in taste and thickness.

3.Chicken Wada- Fried dumplings made like batata vadas with chicken minced stuffed in it.It was served with dips which included mayonnaise.It should have been served with a homemade chutney.

4.Coconut Stew-Thin coconut water,milk and coriander was added.Some spices were added to but we found a hair in the soup.Very disappointing would request to take care in food hygiene.

5.Malvani Prawn Curry-We ordered this curry with steamed rice and Bhakri.The curry was very good up to the mark.

The restaurant was busy and we had to wait for nearly 10m , despite a reservation and were led upstairs to a crowded, smoky, dining area. There were a few old Marathi film posters, books and some weapons displayed on the walls. The food was really good. We had the Sol kadi, alu wadi and chicken patty for starters.

1.  located conveniently on service road , so no problem of parking .
2. Food taste was very yummy . Mushroom cutlet was very tasty . Infact all dishes we tried were awesome.
3. Staff is very polite and helpful.
4. Interiors are very premium and soothing.

Quality of food is very good.. good environment and Interior is very amazing.. loved the place.. the only thing is quantity of food is not enough as compared to the rates..  otherwise good place to eat Marathi style food

reviews.text: Best Kathi Rolls...Must Try Peri Peri Chicken and Burnt Garlic chicken..Taste was awesome‚ô•Ô∏è

One of the best place to try rolls in Lower Parel area. Situated just opposite phoneix Mall. The quality of roti they use for making rolls is what makes their roll so special. You can try all rolls. 
Perry Perry and burnt garlic rolls are must try.
Quantity of filling also good but the upper layer was a bit sweet flavoured but crispy. Overall very goodüëç

It's nice little 'over the counter' corner shop. They have variety of rolls in 3 segments. Eggs, Paneer and Chicken. 6 to 7 varieties to each segment and some new added for the day which are not part of regular menu. It's pocket friendly and delicious but somehow I find chicken rolls kind of okay compared to egg and paneer rolls.

Ordered the Chicken Burnt Garlic Mayo Roll, frequently mentioned as a must-have, and I have to say, it genuinely is a must-have. Plenty of mayo, multiple big chunks of chicken, lovely wrap, the burnt garlic flavour being spot-on, and reasonably filling in the tummy, this must rank as one of the best rolls In the world üó∫. The service is quick, it's not pricey, there really isn't anything to complain about.Whenever I come to Lower Parel it‚Äôs a must visit place and have delicious rolls.. They offer veg and non veg both at a very reasonable price.

reviews.text: I had been there once..it was ok ok...food was tasty.

Just love the parathas over here. The staff is good. Ambience is good. But Damn the parathas are worth it. Cheese chilli paratha is love. Highly recommended place. Been here for more than 3 times. reviews.text:
Awesome experience at know chow.
Their breakfast menu is definitely worth a try.
They have great options like fruit bowl and sunny side up and much more.
The steamed buns were also lovely.
Then even the smoothies were too good.
The cappuccino was wow!!
Indeed it was a lovely experience..

The place was fairly small but seemed to be quite popular, considering the footfall. Frankly there's nothing much to write about the ambience or the d√©cor but the food was not bad.
The burnt garlic noodles were strictly okay, with barely a trace of garlic in them. The Asian lamb in oyster sauce was a tad too salty. The bamboo rice seemed to be the only redeeming feature. In addition to tasting rather good, it was served in a unique bamboo container.
The extra point in my rating is for the behaviour of the staff. They were very prompt and rather friendly. Senior staff came over to enquire about the food, the staff served with a smile and everything we ordered was on the table in minutes. They definitely did well!

Recommended by a friend so had to try it out, tasty food, quantity worth the price and a good layout to try. The palace also is spacious with good seating and lighting, chefs work is great and the staff is very well mannered and help you decide on your taste.. great experience overall.. worth recommending to others.

Khow Chow doesn't look all that appealing, however on the inside the ambience is great.
The service is very good, they are prompt and very nice!
The food here is worth the mighty rating the restaurant boasts! A little heavy on the wallet though.
We had:
Lemon chili coriander chicken soup(5/5):
This was a very hearty soup, with a good quantity of veggies and chicken. It had a great flavour, spicy and tangy at the same time.
Chicken Taronest(5/5):
This was just YUM! Great orange sauce chicken, served in a noodle nest. The crispy noodles were perfect with the chicken. This was delicious and fun to eat :)
Stir fry lamb(5/5):
Nice sauce, and generous portion of lamb
Chicken Pan Fried Noodles (5/5):
Very very good! The noodles were perfectly cooked and the gravy was really well seasoned.
Pot Rice(3/5):
This was the low-light, the gravy wasn't that great and it was too much for the rice, couldn't taste the rice at all. 
Honey Sesame Crispy Noodles with Ice Cream(5/5):
Again this was just wow. The noodles were coated with honey and were the right amount of sweet, they paired perfectly with the vanilla ice cream.
Highly highly recommended!

Recently visited them to try their breakfast menu and I must say that they have an exciting breakfast menu which is healthy & refreshing.

The juices are extremely healthy & fresh, we loved the detoxifier and the vision. We also had their Thai omelette which is loaded with shrimps & chicken - in love with it, truffle scrambled eggs though it tasted good but the portion isn't sufficient to fill ones hunger and their avocado toasts were average in taste.

Undoubtedly the food served is of high quality but the portion leaves your hunger unsatisfied.

Having said that you cannot leave without indulging in their hot chocolate - the classic & salted caramel are to die for!

In all our breakfast experience with them was great as the staff is courteous and prompt. The ambiance is warm and comforting.

You must definitely visit Khow Chow!

Krishna Sweets is a chain of sweets and nankeen shops across the prime locations of Thane like opposite Thane Station(platform number 1), Paanchpakhadi etc. They make and serve authentic sweets and namkeen with delicious taste, excellent packing and decent staffs.

reviews.text: Limited seating space, but amazing food. Had veg wantons and stir fried noodles with vegetables in chilly oil. Loved every bit of it. Courteous and well spoken staff. They help you nicely in deciding what to eat. One star less due to shortage of seating space, esp. for group of 4+

They have both inner and outer seating area which accommodate around 40-50 people at a time. This place is huge hit it always crowded. Interiors are simple done with some wall paintings and goes perfectly with the theme of restaurant. 

Let‚Äôs being with what we order here :- 

1. Panda Passion - Kuai Kitchen special in-house passion fruit based mocktail. Quite refreshing and good in taste.

2. Spicy vegetable dumplings - One of best dimsums in vegetarian option. Highly recommended who loves dimsums.

3. Avocado Maki Roll - Avocado stuffed maki sushi roll was blend in taste served with wasabi and ginger. I loved the fact they used fresh avocado. Wasabi served with it was not that strong in taste. 

4. Turnip cake - Made with turnip/ reddish given a shape of cake cooked perfectly crispy outside softer inside served with lots of fried garlic along with chilli oil. 

5. Kuai Special Vegetables - Mixed vegetables with light soya garlic chilli sauce perfect slightly sweet in taste goes very well for main course served with rice or noodles. Not enjoyed much as it was sweet in taste. 

6. Hakka Noodles - Kuai special Hakka noodles served with lots of fresh julienne vegetables tossed in light soy sauce. 

7. Burnt garlic fried rice - Diced vegetables tossed with rice on lots of burnt garlic. One of best burnt garlic fried rice. Highly recommend 

Food 4/5
Service 4/5
Ambiance 5/5
Location 4/5 

Overall I m very happy and satisfied with the place and the food they have to offer. Simple interiors with cozy ambiance. Friendly staff with courteous service. 
Looking forward to visit the restaurant again.

Small outlet but great food.

The sushis are the best.

The staff is nice and also price wise the restaurant is reasonable.

Asian food doesn't get better than this. My go to place everytime I want to go out! Stir fried noodles, pot rice and sushi highly recommend!

It's small warm Korean place where you will spend a fortune to get very small tastey portions of food. The ambience is pretty cool ! reviews.text: Best North Indian food @Bandra
Best chaat, if you are from Delhi and miss felhi chaat then visit this pleace. For aloo chaat and pani puri

Ambience- Spacious bakery with a small sitting option on the first floor which is well lit.

Pocket friendly- Expensive for the quantity and quality served.

Food- Pani puri was very average with the green chilly water being too spicy. Tamarind water was very diluted and the filling consisted only of peas which was dissapointing.

Dahi puri was creamy, rich and mouthful. Spices were well balanced and filling of peas, potato, peanut and dal sprinkled with sev.

Gulab jamun was served hot and was yummy. It was soft on the inside with the right amount of sweetness. Rasgulla was soft and not too sweet and tasty.

Jalebi was crispy and served hot with right amount of sweetness.

Service- Quick and prompt.

Rating- 4 as the menu can be revisited in terms of pricing.

The best stop for north Indian style Street food, the best Indian sweets and Punjabi style khaana! Love the panipuri followed by sumptious sweets from a huge array of Indian sweeetmeats, from an assortment of kulfis to hot Jalebi, rasmalai to rabri.
Food is outstanding always....their roti tokri(basket) and sarsaon da saag is just delightful...a meal to cap off a holiday.

reviews.text: The foods are excellent. The place is full of people around the world who can share with you about their experiences of India. The staffs are also friendly and prompt for their services. Twice in Mumbai (more than six meals with Leopold Cafe) is not enough for me. Hoping to visit there again after the pandemic.

Love the ambience and value for money! Budget friendly plus the food is as good as anything I have had in other places in a long long time! I‚Äôd be a regular there if it was in my vicinity. Even the staff service is very quick, only the waiting area is a little negative but it is compensated by the great food it offers! So a must try place if you haven‚Äôt been there already! üòé‚úåÔ∏è

I have been to this place thrice, but the recent visit was unpleasant. I went with my friends, and the order taking guy was not at all helpful, was talking as if he doesn't care about us sitting there. He wasn't suggesting and answering well. The Buffalo Steak was well cooked though. The crowd was full packed. The food isn't the top notch here. And minus points for the service! 

It felt like they don't care about their guests.

The place has an energy and atmosphere of its own. It's a cafe with an attitude... a good one. Food options are many, decent drink options too, and great staff. But don't go there for gastronomical satisfaction. Spend some time there over a few drinks and just relax.
It's not a big place nor is it very swanky, or even having a great entrance point. Despite this, on a working day evening, the place was almost full.
Definitely a must visit in Mumbai.

Was in Bombay for a small vacation and this cafe was one of the to-do list for me. I had heard about the bullet marks still on the walls. After seeing the marks, felt bad for the place and felt proud to see the place strong and positive. This cafe is on the busy and cool streets of Colaba. Nice atmosphere inside. The folks here are very very friendly. The food is very good, we had ordered broccoli soup and a potato starter. Very tasty.

reviews.text:
Authentic Biryani 
Also famous for Chinese food 
A very old place with the same taste since a long time.

The restaurant is in between Dadar Station and Dadar Beach. The restaurant was established is 1940 due to the ambiance look vintage however the quality and quantity of food is great in terms of price. If you have a sweet tooth then you have to try Caramel Custard which is just ‚Çπ30. Would love to visit the place again and would try some other cruise.

Its a restaurant specializing in non veg having dishes from breakfast to dinner. Their biryani and khepsa are very good. Contact the place before hand to check availability of khepsa. Food quality is good. The ambiance is old irani style ending meals with bun maskaüåü

Some food is testy some food is not that testy. Service is slow. Good crowd. In evening the hotel is always full. Some time you have to wait for the time. Near to Shivaji park. Walking distance from station.

Serves the best value for money food in the locality. Great place to eat mughlai food. Iranian tea is good too. Iranian Bun maska, Chicken liver fry, chicken tikka biryani and mutton dishes are great choices for food to eat here.

restaurants.address: Cooper School, 18B, Juhu Tara Rd, Near Maneckji, Shivaji Nagr, Santacruz West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400049, India

reviews.text: Must visit. One of the best restaurants in Mumbai for some mouth watering foods. Best service and amazing pizza and pasta. You can never go wrong with Little Italy Juhu.

Food: 5/5
Loved the food. Absolutely amazing presentation and very fresh yummy and satisfying.
The stand out for me was the cannaloni as it was delicious and filling. As far as the mocktail was concerned, "dead women walking" stood out. Wonderful chilled drink with a tinge of lime.
Ambiance: 5/5
Crazy and lovely interiors with great theme to go with. A wonderful decor and good seating space.
Service: Quick, clean and well mannered. The staff knew exactly how a dish should be served and thus very humble.
Overall loved every bit. Reasonable for the price as the quantity is good too. Worth it. Would like to visit again. Thanks.

We went to this quirky,cute place in juhu named Little Italy.The ambience was good and staff was also fine. For a change instead of their Italian cuisine we wanted to try something different and we went with bean tacos and the Mini Lebanese jar,and we had quite high expectations with it but it turned out to be quite okayish. The tacos felt like just beans in them,maybe the Italian cuisine is great and we chose the wrong dishes.Will update you guys soon for the Italian cuisine as well! 
Conclusively,good place to go around but wouldn‚Äôt recommend trying these dishes.

Legendary is the best name that suits Little Italy Juhu  been in service since 25 yrs and still going strong and the reason for which can easily be understood once you experience their hospitality. Went there for a dinner date  with my wife as we both are vegetarian for this month. And not to say Little Italy is a pure Veg place having Jain options too.The restaurant is very easy to locate and has valet services. Would advise to pre book and come as it gets busy during rush hours. The place is newly done up and has a very warm and welcoming feel to it.The staff is well verse with the menu and will sure guide and suggest you on what one must pick according to their taste plate. 
Coming to what i called for 

STARTED WITH 

Bruschetta - The classic conti starter which is freshly baked bread grilled with garlic, olive oil,oregano topped with a generiois tooping of freshly cut tomatoes. (added a bit of parmesan grated to enhance tatse ).A good little starter if you looking to have a heavy main.

MAIN FOCUS 

Ravioli in Al Pesto Genovese - Ravioli  stuffed in panner and spanish (the filling was so yummy ) with a pesto sauce (option of saucy or dry is also give by the staff) which is freshly crushed basil tossed in garlic pine nut and again topped with parmesan.This dish is yummy cheese and too filling. 

Spaghetti - Aglio Olio E Peperoncino - The classic aglio olio tossed with Spaghetti was a outstanding dish for some one like me who prefers this dish simple less cheese and full of aromas of garlic chilly and parsley topped with oliver oil. 

THIRSTY US 

To acomapany my meal we  called for two mocktails Peach Please and Coke Float -  Both were perfect to its taste and very well presented.

SWEET TOUCH 

Tramissu - If you end your meal with a great desert the meal feels complete. And the tramissu we called for just did that.Freshly baked each morning as informed by team had the perfect balance of rum coffee vanila cream on the sponge cake topped with chocolate powder. Was over before a eye was winked. Highly recommended 

All in all had a great dinning experience kudos to Sandeep Mandal and team who took prefect care of us and made sure we had a great Date. Looking forward to having more such great dinning experience at Little Italy Juhu....

One of the iconic VEG ONLY fine dine restaurant landmarks that serve authentic Italian food around Juhu. This brand has been around a good 15 years which is a statement in itself which means the food never disappoints. A few years ago during my earlier visits, the interiors were just average and it looks more like a traditional Indian AC restaurant. However, with the recent renovation, the place looks modern, trendy with the use of vibrant colors and greens.

The service is Usually of high standards and will not disappoint you. Valet service is available and a must around the busy lanes of heartland Juhu. We had tried the following dishes and got to say that each and every dish had its own story, taste, wonderful sourced ingredients and a beautiful presentation. The price was a bit steep for a VEG ONLY OUTLET, however, a fine dine and the location being Juhu you would expect something similar. 

‚ñ∂Cheese Fondue - Melted Cheese in White Wine with Italia herbs served with Bread and Vegetables
‚ñ∂Sun Flower Pizza - A multi-grain Pizza base topped with Tomato sauce, Mozzarella Cheese, Grated Parmesan, Bell pepper cubes, Zucchini, Broccoli, Corn, Pine Nuts, Zatar Herb & Sunflower Seed
‚ñ∂Veg Falafel Roll - Served with some great Pita & Hummus, Leafy Veggies with Olives
‚ñ∂Pasta 4 Stagioni - A Creamy Tomato sauce with Garlic, Carrots, Cauliflower Capers, Olives, and Sundried Tomatoes
‚ñ∂Ferrero Rocher Mousse Cake - Delicate Mousse Cake with a 2 layered dark and light chocolate with hazelnut and cake sponge base
‚ñ∂Chocolate Bomb - Muddy melted fantasy Chocolate served with Vanilla Ice-cream

Summary:
‚ñ∂Interiors ‚Äì 5/5 
‚ñ∂Food ‚Äì 5/5
‚ñ∂Service ‚Äì 5/5
‚ñ∂Presentation ‚Äì 5/5
‚ñ∂Quantity ‚Äì 5/5
‚ñ∂Value F.Money ‚Äì 5/5

A beautiful business lunch which ended on a high note considering the desserts were also smashing...!! A big 5 and a highly recommended outlet to anyone who reads this.

reviews.text:
Located in the beautiful location of Kamala Mills Compound, Lower Parel, London Taxi ensured that we spend a quality time there.

An important point to be noted is that every hard-drink used in the cocktail was absolutely pure and of high grade (absinthe as well). The intercontinental food served here is really good. I'd personally recommend Tibetan Chicken Broth and Slow Cooked Chicken Breast. For cocktails, Sazerac is really good !

Overall, a great experience, quality service and equally good food !

The vibe of bustling London is unmistakable in this place and evident through d√©cor elements too. A mix of high tables and plush sofas, makes for comfortable seating. While the snazzy and well-stocked bar may be centre stage, the exhaustive food menu with varied offerings, across cuisines, is equally a huge draw. The chef‚Äôs inventive twists are subtle and cleverly executed, sans any forced gimmicks. The 'Lemon Barley Salad' is crunchy, flavourful and enticingly presented. Among small plates, the vegetarian potsticker stands out owing to its delicate, but distinct flavours.

This place has different vibes altogether.
Have been to many places but this place has different comfort level.
Everything is classy about this place starting from seating arrangement to inner decor everything is just perfect.
The food presentation is best I have seen.
Food recipes are different and deliciously prepared.
Staff is courteous and well mannered.

I Went today for lunch.it serves amazing appetizers.
Ambiance is super cool.
Staff is professional, courteous and helping.
Overall Food was great.
Delicious food with cool ambience makes your day memorable.

The food is good but not extraordinary. They serve wonderful veggie and fruit juices for which they earn another brownie point. I liked the place but I wouldn‚Äôt say it would be my preferred hangout place on any given day.

reviews.text: This place has been there for years now. I think it is third generation now. Since my young age I have seen this place only grow. Reason for growth? QUALITY, QUALITY, QUALITY. No matter what the situation you are in, no matter what season it is, you can always be assured of quality. After unlockdown, this is the only place we, as family,  decidde to buy prepared food. The prices are way too much and the sweets and farsan sold by them is of very very low  quality , I had taken white barfi from them which was very stale and full of only sugar . The counter person was so arrogant he weighed the sweet in a box and added the weight of box too while totalling the amount. You can see the pic I have attached. Please avoid this shop all the time. They even sell mangoes in decorative boxes just to cheat the customer for exorbitant prices , market price for mangoes in current date is 500-600 per dozen and they sell @ 1300 a dozen . See the difference for urself.
Good delivery service..........u people had maintain ur excellent food quality üëåüëå

reviews.text:
Just a amazing and cozy place in a heart of bandra. Location is superb. Its on the main road. Ambiance is quite attractive and simple. Not so much spacious, decent sitting arrangements. 2 sitting area they have. A/C and Non A/C. 
They have wide menu of south Indian dish. They have got staff also from south. 
I went on weekday and that day also restaurant is almost full. 
This restaurant is pure veg. 

I had ordered :

1. Idli Platter - 4 types of Idli they serve (steam, ragi, rava & multigrain) rava idli was delicious. - Platter is quite heavy.

2. Dosa - forgot name of the dosa - but its large in size. 

Beverages

1. Strawberry Smoothie

2. Coconut water with lemonade - its nothing but lemonade with soda (didnt like it ).

They have different types of chutney. 

Overall experience was satisfying. Definatley consider this place for south indian food.

Good to see that favourite restaurants have opened for delivery. I have recently ordered from one of my favourite place that is from Madras diaries. The place serves authentic south indian dishes. i have asker for sweet dahi vada its my all time favourite one whenever i am to this place. Then had Ghee roast dosa which is usual but loved the purely added ghee on it, its batter was just perfect and good in taste, quantity sufficient for one served with chutney and sambhar. Again chutney sambhal truly mouthwatering. Then comes the malabar paratha along with green curry ( made up of fresh veggies) bang on
The restaurant is taking good care in this pandemic and try their best to serve all with hygiene
Highly recommended one should definitely try this place if anyone looking for south indian food. 
Good in terms of taste, quality, quantity, hygience.
Thanks

I recently visited Madras diaries.
It is located in bandra west.

I had came here for breakfast but I ended up having a complete meal.
The taste of food over here is just like south India.
The ambience they had was so similar to South India.

I had

Bread Halwa.
(Check out the pictures attached below)

Thanks.....

Madras Diaries in Bandra is a great place to have some awesome South Indian fare.
They have a really nice ambience and the staff is courteous and helpful.
We tried the following:
Mini Idli: Small Idlis covered in podi, very flavourful and the idlis are perfect bite size
Appam With stew: Classic dish done very well. The appams were the right thickness and the stew was absolutely delicious
Malabar Paratha with Paneer Chettinad: The parathas were very good and paired perfectly with the flavourful curry.
Pesarattu: A moong dal based dosa which is green in colour, it was nice and crispy and a must try!
Elaneer Cooler and Masala Buttermilk: Both were really good
Madras Diaries is a must visit!

Madras Diaries is a very pretty 
63 covers Vegetarian restaurant, that feels like you're dining at someone's house in Chennai or Cochin..
Colorful walls painted in earthly tones, huge hand painted multi-coloured wood-curved entrance door.

The decor has subtle hint of rich Southern culture - Bell shaped lantern lighting, a green background wall, decorated with metal small bells. It's not like a typical Udipi restaurant.

The relaxed home ambiance, a great place to enjoy amazing South Indian vegetarian delicacies created by Chef Murugan.
Just completed 2 years successfully

Restaurant Timing - 8am -- 11pm
Location - Bandra West
No hard drinks available

Mr Shankar & Mr Raika look after the place, greeted and welcome us warmly, made us feel comfortable..

Mr Raika prepared fresh refreshing fruit based drinks
1. Elaneer Cooler - fresh tender coconut served with a pinch of fresh lemon juice
2. Kokum Cooler - refreshing drink with lots of health benefits
3. Fresh watermelon juice
4. Spiced Lemon with basil seeds - another refreshing drink with health benefits

Totally fallen in love of Chef's tasty creative dishes
Served hot ..
5. Kara Pariyaram Chettiyan Mogi Podi toss - coin sized fried idlis were super tasty

6. Signature chutneys served with starters of fresh pineapple with yogurt, beetroot with garlic, bottlegourd with garlic and tomato with garlic

7. Cheese Chilly Jalapeno Idli in masala Fondue - a perfect fusion dish, very delicious

8. Hot fluffy appams with thick coconut milk based veg stew

9. Ghee roast crispy masala dosa with sambar and coconut chutney

Signature yummy traditional desserts -
10. Madras Diaries special hot Bread Halwa
11. Fresh Pineapple hot Sheera
12. Elaneer Payasam - fresh tender coconut pieces are cooked in coconut milk, a cool delicacy of Kerala
13. Hot filter coffee
Reasonably pricedüëç
Fresh traditional vegetarian dishes
Good service
Totally value for money restaurant
I recommend this lovely restaurant..
