A great place to eat for college students and families as well.
The seafood is delicious, especially the prawns were the best I have had in Navi Mumbai.
The service was quick and the ambiance is excellent. 
Also, try Butter Chicken. The chicken was as soft as it can get.

I ordered pudina kebab and mutton masala fry from this restaurant. Food was quite impressive, fresh and flavourful. Kebab was very soft, spicy with some salad and pudina chutney. Mutton was breathtaking, mutton just melts into your mouth with hot gravy. It was a perfect dish for a non veg lover. Service was good. Delivery was prior its time. Good quality food is served here. I would suggest everyone to try mutton dishes from this restaurant.

Maharashtra Lunch Home is an amazing place in the suburb region of Nerul, navi Mumbai.
They serves delicious North indian, Chinese, Malwani and sea food cuisine.
They have speciality in amazing  malvani food and sea food.
We have ordered,

- Paneer Biryani 
  Have sufficient amount of marinated paneer cubes along with spices and it served with the onion-tomato raita. premium quality rice was used and the quantity was sufficient for two people.

- chicken Tikka Masala
   The chicken pieces are so juicy and it was nice with quantity as it sufficient for 2 to 3 people. The taste was really mouth watering.

- paneer Tikka Masala
  In this the paneer chunks are used along with the capsicum and tomato pieces having proper amount of masala with good quantity. It was so tempting.

Overall experience was really very awesome. They have both dine in facility and fastest delivery service.
I must recommend this amazing outlet for their variety of  delicious food items üòã.

restaurants.address: Mahesh Lunch Home, Juhu Tara Rd, Next to J.W.Marriott, Uditi Tarang Housing Colony, Juhu Tara, Juhu, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400049, India

reviews.text: Sorry but I don't like it fish was really smelly
Its a fine place for LUNCH... Food is good. Service is nice... Friendly staff and informative, if you are new to sea foods.

Mahesh Lunch Home continues to be top draw if you want coastal food in Mumbai. They can produce live 'items' for you to chose, particularly the crabs. Upmarket, they have made the name and if you want to enjoy good coastal food, well try this place. They have few branches in Mumbai. The place can burn a small hole in your pocket and if you plan to have drinks too, then it might cost you a little fortune. Good stocked bar but accompaniments like fresh juice or canned juice without sugar were woefully missing and we find that atrocious, particularly when their pricey menu proclaims it to be high end restaurant. Four out of five stars is for good service, good ambience and good food. The one star less,  you know now why?
This place is certainly good but not what the great place it used to be... tried out for sea food but left a little disatisfied to the high standards expected for the best seafood joints in Mumbai

Really nice restaurant with fresh sea food variety options. The staff is really friendly and even properly guide with the menu and their special menu items.
It's best recommended to book a table before visiting so that you don't have to wait for long.

restaurants.address: Shalimar Morya Park, Ground Floor, Off New Link Rd, Veera Desai Industrial Estate, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400053, India

reviews.text:
Mainland China, Has been standing strong for many years and will definitely continue to do so in the future as well. Be it the food or the service, they won't let you down at all. Food is top-notch with maintained authenticity to it. The place is located just opposite Infinity Mall and upon entering this lovely dining place you can notice the huge space. It's more of fine dining with a range of food options. 

They Al-a-carte as well as buffet style, so it's a personal choice with whatever is okay. 
When it comes to Asian food, they have great sushi options, mouth-watering dumplings, and scrumptious Thai delicacies. Also, they have introduced a new menu which I did try out and it was definitely one heavenly meal.
Good portions to be precise, a single portion can be easily had by 2 people.

Started off with few portions of 
"Pan Fried BBQ Fish"
"Lemon Grass Prawns"
"Coriander Chicken" This was the best.

Even tried a range of dumplings and I have a thing for it anyways. Gotta recommend the "Philadelphia Cheese Dumplings" & "Pan Fried Japanese Mushroom Dumplings". Kudos to the chef for making such amazing food.

The mains definitely had to tried and we had "Lotus Leaf Rice" accompanied by a decent portion of "Chicken In Roasted Garlic Sauce". Even tried a small portion of "Singapore Style Fired Noddles with Bean Sprout". A good amount of veggies, fabulous quantity, and the gravy complimented the rice and noodles. Worth it.

We finished our meal on a very sinful and decadent note with a huge portion of "Chocolate Dome". Well presented and extremely well crafted. For those who love chocolate, this is a definite pick for them.

Nothing to complain because everything was just perfect. It's the best place to land up for a good Asian experience.

Mainland China Andheri West
You're doing a marvelous job
Kudos to the entire Group
Satisfying Indian foodies for more than glorious 25 years

If it's Chinese
It's Mainland China...
It a part of Indian thought process..

The way we love our Asian, Chinese, Japanese, Thai, Sushi, you're always winning our hearts by maintaining the same taste, quality and hygiene factors, service into the priorities.

Since, I can't go out now
To have food from my favorite restaurant
I ordered through App.
I got a call, regarding how much spicy I want my curries.

Minimum order value should be  of Rs.2,000/- & above.
It's best to place the order 2 - 3 hours in advance, so that they can  deliver on time. 

Be assured they've undertaken all precautions and maintaining the highest standards of hygiene and safety in the kitchen.

Including regular Temperature checks of their cooks, delivery boys,  drivers, duly tagged on the parcel bags.
Besides, wearing  mandatory face masks, gloves  
And are strictly following social distancing protocol.

I've ordered the following -

1.Fish in Chili Basil sauce.
2.Green Thai Chicken curry
3.Steam Rice.
4.Ginger Capsicum Rice.
5.Vegetables in Mahlak sauce.
6.Corn potatoes tsinghoi sauce.
7.Veg Hakka Noodles.
8.Hot Chocolate Rolls With Caramel sauce .

Excellent taste and quality
Good portion size.
One portion is enough for 2 persons

Fish is my weakness.
Fish in Chilli Basil sauce is prepared the way I love it

Green Thai Boneless chicken curry is prepared by coconut milk, excellent in taste 

Both the vegetarian curries are super tasty, cooked with exotic veggies

My daughter's all time favourite, since her childhood - Veg Hakka Noodles

Hot Chocolate Rolls with Caramel sauce are yummy, coated with coconut powder ...

Totally hygienic, tasty, my soulfood....

"Posted the same review for Asia's kitchen as well."
Definition of Authentic Chinese Food:- Mainland China/ Asia Kitchen.
I must say the old menu was way better than the current one but yet still on point. The lunch buffet is worth every penny.
Hakka Noodles with Mancurian‚ù§
Truffle Flavoured Zucchini Rolls ü§ò
Cream Cheese Rollsüòç
Hot chocolate Roll with ice cream is the best of all.üíé
Overall a great experience.üôå‚ù§

This is a Chinese based restaurant where the prices go from a minimum of 250 to some thousands. If you are not specific for your food go for their buffet. For veg it costs around 800 INR and for Non vegetarian it costs around 1010 INR. The cleanliness is so good and you will be provided excellent service. The cost is somewhat high and if you are a foodie and want to taste something different then it's a must visit place.

Good food, very courteous staff and an elegant, expansive place that can accommodate all your demand. Setting is elegant and priced just right. Mr. Murali was outstanding in service and exceptionally prompt.

restaurants.address: Shop 6, Mahavir Apartments, 241, Tardeo Road, Next to Bharat Petroleum, Old Chikalwadi, Chikalwadi, Tardeo, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400007, India

reviews.text:
Went to this newly renovated outlet yesterday for dinner and absolutely loved it! They have refined their menu and expanded with a seating area. Maiz uses extremely fresh and high quality ingredients. 

I tried the Tortilla chips with the signature salsa. Their chips were super crispy and fresh and the salsa had the perfect amount of flavour. I also tried the cottage cheese grilled burrito which was delicious. They have recently started grilling all their burritos which makes all the difference! It brings out the flavour even more and I really enjoyed it. I also had the watermelon drink which was very refreshing and cooling. Their prices are also very reasonable for the quality of ingredients they provide. Special thanks to their chef Vishal who was extremely polite and nice. Will definitely be back to try more items on their menu!

Super awesome experience! I ordered from swiggy. Delivery was timely. Tried Fajita veggies burrito and lemonade. Obviously taste was great, never got this taste anywhere else in India. Management has put in lot of effort to design the whole experience in a very elegant way. Each item in packaging is well thought of and makes you want to enjoy your meal fully without getting distracted. Agreed the price is a bit expensive but i guess the quality and experience makes up for it!!
Food is excellent and quality is also maintained at the peak.... Loved my chicken Calli and paneer barito. There guac is one of the best so far I have tasted in Mumbai.
One can go here for fresh Mexican Cuisine. All of their Salsa have different yet amazing tastes. Tacos are a must to be tried here.
Superb taste and quality. Amazing food. Keep it up.

restaurants.address: House No. 501 Commerical Property, Building No 38, Eastern Express Hwy, Louis Wadi, Kurla, Thane, Maharashtra 400601, India

reviews.text: The food quality and quantity was too good. But rates could have been a bit more pocket friendly. Overall ambience and service was excellent.

It's a best place to eat fish. Which is very fresh and taste. The fish is perfectly cooked. The food was finger licking. If you want to drink u can drink some alcohol. The restaurant from the interior has a very unique design. I juzz loved the place.

Malvan Tadka is situated at Thane. 
In starters, the Tandoori Crabs are most recommended as they are very delicious. 
Also, the Chicken Alishan Kabab was served with 4 different varieties of chicken. 
In Main course, the prawns biryani was top notch. The prawns were fresh and tasty. 
In Mocktails, the Virgin Pinacolada and Cranberry Coolor were first class. 
In desserts, the Caramel Custard had very yummy taste. 

Food - 5/5
Ambiance - 5/5
Service - 5/5
Overall - 5/5

This place has a very good ambience and that comes from the beautiful interior of the place. Also the working staff of the place is very helpful and good. One can visit this place with friends and family. Malvani food is all that you will find over the place. Coming up to the taste of food, i find a scope of improvement in this section. The food i received was having a chicken that was not very well boiled.

One of the biggest and most bustling places to eat Malvani food chicken and seafood in Thane, prominently located along EEH....they have 2 huge restaurants because of the crowd
this place came highly recommended...had the malvani curry would recommend this place for people who can handle authentic food with flavour and spice... good crowd, jolly family ambience of families enjoying drinks over kombdi vade and kolambi bhaat...enjoyed a lot. service also good, maybe less responsive to special requests....but overall very nice and clean

We also tried paneer chilly dry and chicken pepper dry.
They served with seal pack wooden disposal cutlery with tissue paper.
Also we received jasmime tea sachets.
Ordered the food from Zomato for smooth delivery.

reviews.text: One of most famous places to eat "Pav-Bhaji". The taste is very unique. There are so many varieties of dishes available. You should must visit this place if you love "Pav-Bhaji".

Really one the best place in girgaon area to relish some lipsmacking pav bbhaji. I bet you cant visit this place just once. Also tawa pulav servered here are quite famous. A thumps up to this small eatery located near opera house, Charni road area.

One the best Pav Bhaji in this side of the town. I would not hesitate to put this place in the Top 10 list of Pav Bhaji serving restaurants in Mumbai.
The taste is superb, not too spicy & buttery but a correct balance of spices & vegetables. It is friendly on the pocket as well.
Don't judge the book by it cover; try it once!

I tried this place after a long time. Almost more than 2 year. Must say the taste is exactly the same. Their Amul Makhan Pav Bhaji is the best. Quantity is damm good and sufficient for one person. You can order extra Pav to finish the Bhaji. The Pav is nicely tossed in Butter.

The bhaji is not at all heavy and damm good in taste. One of the best place in Mumbai when it comes to Pav Bhaji.

This place is very special to me. It reminds me of my Childhood. Thank you so much everyone at Manohar Pav Bhaji for serving us delicious Pav Bhaji over the years
good thing pv bhaji was good in taste and quantity was great with lots of maul butter

restaurants.address: Shop No:24, Ground Floor, Angelina Apartment, Baji Prabhu Deshpande Marg, Navpada, Kamala Nagar, Vile Parle, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400056, India

reviews.text: Awesome taste and worth every penny. Try their masala pav. Only joint which is open at night till 3-4am

Maruti Pav Bhaji is an iconic outlet that is known for their Black Pav Bhaji & Spicy Masala Pav. These two things that they serve are excellent, delicious and beyond comparison to any other outlet. If you can ignore the ambiance, visit this small restaurant. Otherwise, ordering from them is your best option and most people do order or pickup. 

Dine in Rating of Maruti Pav Bhaji, Vile Parle:

Date: 6th May 2019
Time: 7:15pm

Please check the rating for each dish we ordered based on various factors:

1) Black Pav Bhaji ‚Äì Rs. 100

Quality ‚Äì 5/5
Portion Size ‚Äì 5/5
Taste ‚Äì 5/5
Value for Money ‚Äì 5/5
Overall ‚Äì 5/5

2) Masala Pav ‚Äì Rs. 50

Quality ‚Äì 5/5
Portion Size ‚Äì 5/5
Taste ‚Äì 5/5
Value for Money ‚Äì 5/5
Overall ‚Äì 5/5

Other Factors:

Ambiance: 2/5
Service: 3/5

The Black Pav Bhaji which is their specialty is super spicy, super delicious and one of the best versions of Pav Bhaji I have had. They do make less spicy version of the Black Pav Bhaji on request. The second must try dish is Masala Pav which is again spicy and contains lots of coriander. There is a burst of flavors in both the dishes and it will make you a fan of this place. You can also order just Black Bhaji along with Masala Pav instead of taking the plain Pav. The prices are super cheap and the food is worth every penny you pay for. Highly recommend this place for an absolutely unique experience. 

Follow us on Instagram: @foodratingsindia
Love it like anything...it's evergreen food for me ..anytym anywhere..no changes in taste n quality...awsm..
little bit spicy you can order less spicy otherwise tasty. You want to eat again again and again. Black pav bhaji. And babu pav .

Do you want to have the best pav bhaji in the town? Maruti pav Bhaji located in Vile Parle West is the best place for you ! It serves our famous Kali Pav Bhaji.
What I tried -

Pav Bhaji - The best Pav bhaji i have ever had. A very unique taste and a must have !

Masala Pav - unlike the regular masala pav that we get, masala pav at Maruti pav bhaji comes with lots and lots of coriander and tastes delicious.

Pulav - Awesome and unique taste. The quantity served is also good.

Good service and a must visit place !

reviews.text: Masala Bay is my favourite Indian restaurant in Mumbai and they serve authentic Indian cuisine as per your choice. Recently I had my parent‚Äôs anniversary celebration here and all our guests and my parents enjoyed and relished the food very much. I highly recommend.
Nice vibe, food is great. Menu is good, good varieties. Rhe good thing with Indian food is that you have lots of veggie options.

The taste of was really very tasty and i would love to tell you that i got a good type of order as some special discount on their dishes which were in a reasonable taste and very much mouth watering!
They are expertised in non veg chinese cuisine and the flavours which are added are authentically good!
This delivery kitchen is situated in Andheri west,near Station,Mumbai.
I would recommend you all to order it from this outlet!
Food-5/5

A posh place to sit back and relax with friends and family. Nice views of the high roof. They have nice drinks and paintings on the wall acoss this place are a masterpiece. The best part is that most of the time you are able to spot celebs at this place.
Beautiful Ambience Beautiful Structure Amazing Food Dapper Hotel courteous staff superb service ! This is an exotic place for not just the view but for the complete fine dine experience.

reviews.text:
Soo guyz I have recently been ordered chicken tikka butter chicken biryani chicken soup.
The whole meal was very fresh n tasty
I like the food very much
Soo guyz must order your stuff from masala kitchen

Masala Kitchen is a delivery kitchen located in Worli besides Casa De Cafe on Dainik Shivner Road... 

This outlet is famous for its North Indian dishes and we ordered a few of their signature dishes... Like :- 

1) Trio Chicken - 6 pieces of boneless chicken marinated in 3 different colours - orange, white and green it and grilled over the tandoor till well done... The taste of these 3 different marinations was amazing and lip smacking. Definitely recommended... 

2) Chicken Tikka Biryani - The biryani was tasty and it consisted boneless pieces of chicken tikkas. Biryani flavour was nice. Liked the biryani out here. 

3) Butter Chicken - Succulent pieces of chicken marinated in red tomato gravy and cooked till perfection... The only thing that it was lacking was the gravy was too sweet. Could have been a lot more better if they could make this savoury dish a little more spicy... 

4) Parathas - Plain Parathas were cute and small in size and so you have to make sure to order more if u are ordering the food from here... Triangle size... 

5) Angoori Gulab Jamun - 6 mini pieces of gulab jamun. The sizes were very small as it was angoori gulab jamun. Finished the dessert within no time. Service was quick and in time...

Today I had ordered my dinner from Masala Kitchen which is a delivery outlet located in worli.
The food was delivered on time hot and fresh.
I had ordered:
1. Chicken Tikka biryani: it was very less and as it was small portion. Only two chicken Tikka pieces were there. The biryani taste was ohk ohk. Not that great. It costed 200 rupees and for that small portion it was way too costly.
2. Chicken Gilafi Seekh: it was yumm!! Best dish! N worth the money. It was cooked Soo well and topped with cheese. They could have added a bit more cheese. But it was great anyways.
3. Make your own meal gravy combo: it consists of butter chicken, roti, salad. N roti was Soo soft. Not at all hard or burnt. Relli impressed! The butter chicken was flavorful and tasty. It had enough boneless chicken pieces. Salad was also good.
3. Moong dal halwa: it was not at all good. It was made in dalda which is not at all healthy and tasty. It was very very dry. I didn't like the taste at all. Halwa should alwys be made in ghee. Not at all recommended here.
Overall I loved the food. It was good. I had given special instructions not to make it too oily or too spicy and they prepared it accordingly. Good!

Masala Kitchen is one of the few good delivery options for Indian food in SoBo. Their packaging is neat and spill-proof; delivery is well on time. I tried the following items:

Salli Boti Bun Muska: this is a Parsi dish which I liked quite a lot. Very succulent salli boti stuffing inside the classic bun muska.

Murg Gilafi Seekh: I love seekh kebabs, though I didn't quite like this one due to overload of ginger.

Khade Masale ka Murg: a rich, medium spicy chicken gravy dish which I loved. Went well with butter rotis. Chicken chunks were quite tender and juicy.

Hyderabadi Mutton Dum Biryani: This was the best dish out of all. Loved the aromatic biryani with soft and delicious mutton pieces. Well balanced on spice.

Jalebi Rabri: Perfect end to a hearty meal with crispy jalebi and creamy rabri.

They had also provided mint chutney, raita and salad with the order. Thumbs up for that. Definitely gonna try out more items from the menu in future.

Masala kitchen is located in worli. This is delivery kitchen
Recently ordered from Masala Kitchen.Masala kitchen is a best delivery.Delivery was quick.they give veg and non veg delivery.We ordered this yummmy nonveg  meal combo from Masala kitchen which was soo tasty and yummy.They serve different types of food.
I ordered make your own gravy meal combo.and the combo .the combo is soo amazing and I love it. In this combo they have butter chicken and the butter chicken was soo tempting and mouthwatering and they gave also butter roti.
And i ordered Kashmiri gosht ki Biriyani small the Biriyani taste is little sweet but it's yummm.and Biriyani is is tastty.And then ordered desert also in desert i I ordered my Favourite rabdi jalebi it soo soo tasty. And sweets also.

reviews.text:
Good restaurant. I have been only once and left with an impression that it was just ‚Äòalright‚Äô. Nothing special, nothing negative either. Positives:
Pleasant ambience, courteous staff, good food. No negatives, the only negative being it wasn‚Äôt anything special. I wouldn‚Äôt want to go again. It‚Äôs Indian food without any embellishments. Simply made and presented. I felt it lacked imagination / creativity. If that‚Äôs what you‚Äôre looking for, go for it. Won‚Äôt be disappointed but will be left without a memorable experience.

Everyone time I am in Mumbai, I always pay a visit to this restaurant.

Located within the luxurious Taj Hotel, this restaurant offers a fine dining experience which should be absorbed by ALL your senses.

Security is tight when arriving at the hotel. As you walk through the large lobby area and down the corridor, there you will find Masala Kraft.

Masala Kraft features an array of menus including the Masala Mumbai Tiffin, Wine Paired Menu and the Health Menu. The menu bursts with recipes seasoned with local spices, dry powders accompanied with flavored chutneys and indulgent desserts.

Service is attentive and a good beverages menu.

The food served here is excellent. The visit I recently made served food from the four corners of India. Since our party of 6 came from various parts of India, this was an ideal visit.

Service: 5/5

Food: 5/5

Quality: 5/5

Cleanliness: 5/5

Atmosphere: 5/5

The service was not what I expected for the price we pay. Food was served after an interval of 10 to 15 minutes which happened to almost kill the hunger. Also, according to me, the staff didn't pay complete attention as we had to call for the waiter twice for just water which again was brought into just 2 glasses knowing there were 4 people present on the table. The ambience was calming and pleasant at first but as soon as the time passed, it became all noisy which broke the peaceful vibe. Overall, the food was delicious but it would've been better if the service was more than satisfactory  as for the price. Thanks.

I absolutely loved the food except the Paneer starter...The corn soup and the tomato soups were delicious so were the vegetable preparations that we ordered... However, I was disappointed by the service. The staff was very courteous but probably because we went on a Sunday it was understaffed resulting in delays and lack of attention... Its an expensive place as expected and I feel I dint get the value for money as far as the service was concerned.. Though they did come and apologize for the delays and the food pretty much made up for it... I would want more at the price I paid... I think weekday would be a better idea for a meal at this place!

Seating is spacious, ambience is wonderful and food is very tasty. However, the cost is too high and it limits the amount of fun one can have. Recommended only for special occasions for an average Indian family. This place is for the upper crest.

reviews.text:
This place is approximately 550;m from Airport road metro station. I ordered Prime minister matka khichdi from here and I was not much satisfied with its taste. First of all this was not daal khichdi , it was actually a khichdi which not many Mumbaikars are aware. I suppose it's the one of the very few places in Mumbai which actually serves Khichdi and not dal khichdi in the name of khichdi. It's the maximum you can go close to a khichdi at this place in Mumbai. 
If you are fed-up of having dal khichdi in name of khichdi then this place is a must go. After that you may decide if u want to continue going to this place or not. But it's a must go for a one time experience. Who knows you may like the actual taste of khichdi.
All the best.

A colleague of mine was looking to having something light for lunch when I came upon this restaurant. And I was pleasantly surprised seeing the variety of khichdi options these guys have and thus ordered a Dal Makhani Khichdi with Boondi Raita as an add-on.

Coming to the package, they send the khichdi in a plastic container, the boondi raita in a real Matka and a small container containing green chutney. Coming to the Khichdi first, it tasted good. The rice and dal and the entire mixture were cooked properly and as it was a dal makhani khichdi I could see a nice layer of butter on top although it had melted completely due to the heat. The quantity was sufficient for a single person who is damn hungry or even for 2 people with medium appetite.

Coming to the Boondi raita, it was nice and it had a unique flavor to it and was nowhere near the boondi raita we generally eat. But the taste complemented the khichdi perfectly and so was the green chutney that came with the package. All in all the entire package at a cost of just Rs. 156 after discount from zomato was really good and all in all the taste was also satisfying.

Some awesome tastes and flavours given to bland khichdi ‚Äòs . A place where you start loving khichdi‚Äôs . Served in earthen pots they are really special and tasty. Love for khichdi never ends here. They have amazing home delivery service as well.

Good for locals of Marol to get a nice and tasty daal khichdi. Its really good. Slightly over priced but worth giving a try. One thing you cannot have it there but order it online so have 1 hour patience guys.
Definitely a big no guys their staff told us that they cook veg and non veg in same pan.

According to the Hindu mythology, modak is believed to be Ganesh's favourite food, and hence he is also known as Modakapriya, someone who likes modak. As per the rituals, 21 modaks are offered to the Lord Gajanan as bhog and eventually served as prasad to all the devotees. Ganesha is the Lord of Wisdom, Success and Good Luck.

This is how the restaurant derives its name ‚Äì MODAKAM (Prasad from Lord Ganesha). You will also find a big modak carved at the top of the restaurant.

Modakam is situated right outside¬†the iconic and famous¬†Shree Siddhivinayak Ganapati Mandir.¬†The temple has its foundation 2 centuries ago on 19th¬†November, 1801. A small temple has now turned into a grand premise housing many deities. The Siddhivinayak Ganesha idol is quite unique and unusual as it was carved out of a single black stone and has Ganesha‚Äôs trunk to the right instead of left.

The temple is situated in the heart of city Mumbai. Centrally located and easily accessible via various public transport services.

Modakam is a pure vegetarian restaurant with multiple fast food options. It serves variety of maharashtrian, south Indian and Punjabi cuisines. They also specialize into fasting food items as well.

Starters :

KOTHAMBIR WADI, an authentic maharashtrian dish, had a beautiful colour of green and brown. Fried perfectly to make the outer layer crisp. Served along with coriander chutney and ketchup. A must-have!!!

CHEESE PAKODA, one of the most delicious snack dishes, were bought hot from the kitchen. Crispy layer outside and melting cheese on the inside was a perfect mix.

Main course:

Restaurant has a live¬†PAV BHAJI¬†counter right at its entrance. The aroma of pav bhaji fills the ambience and you can‚Äôt hold back in ordering one. The dish surpasses the expectations.

Many devotees come walking to the temple from different parts of Bombay and haven‚Äôt eaten anything till the darshan is over. Hearty meal of¬†PANEER TIKKA MASALA AND ROTI¬†is a big recommendation to anyone looking for a full family meal. After all the hard work, pamper your system with some protein.

Juices/Milkshakes:

King of fruits and yogurt, tongue‚Äôs delight is¬†MANGO LASSI. Perfectly sweetened, not too thick nor too thin is a healthy smoothie along with food.

How about a feast for your eyes and taste buds? A must try is¬†ROSE FALOODA. Modakam also adds chunks of jelly pieces. Kind of took me back to my childhood days.

Desserts:

Ever thought of a spicy ice cream?¬†GUAVA ICE CREAM¬†with sprinkle of chilli powder was a blast of taste‚Äôs in the mouth. It is a wonderful mix of sweet and spicy (very little). Almost felt like eating guava fruit with masala.

Modakam aaye aur Modak nahi khaya toh kya khaya? But how about modak with a twist ‚Äì¬†MODAK ICE CREAM.¬†It is unique and different. Modakam‚Äôs speciality.

So overall it was a good experience with multiple flavours... Service is quick & rates are reasonable.. Definitely a good option for some quick snacking with family & friends.

Do come for darshan and a hearty meal.

If you visit to Siddhivinayak Temple, this is the nearest food outlets just outside the main gate of the temple. It serves all types of North Indian and South Indian food. With that it has a Sweet Corner too. It opens early in the morning. So you have breakfast options also. üôå

Situated just outside Siddhivinayak Temple, Modakam is small yet amazing veg restaurant serving Maharashtrian, Punjabi and South Indian Cuisine.
  This is our must visit place, whenever we come to seek Bappa's blessings,  

Along with regular menu, Modakam has lots of options for fasting too. Here is what I tried during my recent visit:

Snacks:
Kothimbir Vadi: Crispy & Tasty
Sabudana Wada: Authentically prepared & served with sweet curd

Juices:
Maramari: Lovely fusion of Mosambi & Pineapple juice
Watermelon: Cool & Refreshing 

For mains we tried their Mushroom Masala with Butter Naan.. Naan was bit  thick for my liking but it was loaded with butter & went well with Sabji.. 

& for desserts we had Ukadiche Modak.. Modakam aake Modak nahi khaye to kya matlab hai na?? This is absolutely must try dish here.. Indulge in once & you will be in love forever...

So overall it was a good experience... Services is quick & rates are reasonable.. Definately a good option for some quick snacking with famil & friends if you are in around Prabhadevi

reviews.text: Food was good.. But quantity is pretty less.. One portion of anything will never be sufficient for one person...

In the jam packed lane of Tulsiwadi lies a gem of a restaurant - especially if you are Bengali who relishes his food! For me - being a true Mumbaikar, I was a bit skeptical to try out the freshwater fishes and mustard oil preparation of Bengali cuisine. But so impressed I was, after having a feast at Oh! Calcutta.
To begin with, they have a well kept and professional Valet Parking - which is such a necessity - in the cramped Tardeo area. Once you enter the restaurant - the seating and interiors of the restaurant are a mix of traditional and modern, to make you feel at comfort. For menu card - they provide you a Tablet phone, where you can view how the dish looks like, before you order.
Well, we feasted on a variety of dishes - each better than the other and it's difficult to call out a favourite.
Nizami Murgh Malai Tikka - Delicious chicken malai tikka
Gondhoraj Mach - Steamed fish in leaves
Topsher Cutlet - Mango fish cutlet
Kosha Mangsho - Sukka Mutton
Daab Chingri - Prawns cooked in coconut milk and served artistically in a coconut
Rui Kalia - Rui fish in traditional bay leaf and garam masala curry
Hot puffy Luchi - Piping hot and puffy puri¬†¬†
Calcutta Chicken Biryani
Mishti Doi - famous bengali sweet and creamy yoghurt
Rosogulla¬†- needs no description
Gur Sondesh
So all you Mumbaikars, if you want a taste of Bengal, you don't need to travel all the way to Kolkata. You have right here in Mumbai - Oh Calcutta!

Oh! Calcutta at Andheri West, is arguably the best restaurant for Bengali cuisine in Mumbai. The food is oh so authentic that it always manages to transport me back to my childhood days in Kolkata. Its absolutely impossible to pick out which items are the best.
Such a good ambience. Perfect for Bengali Cuisine, but I expected a bit more according to their reputation on the genuinity and authenticity of the food.

Hilsa Hilsa Hilsa üòãüòãüëåüëå
Bengalis most favorite Monsoon delight
Any preparation with Hilsa fish..
Am privileged to cebratrate
Hilsa Festival in Oh! Calcutta, Tardeo

The Hilsa Festival will go on till 1st of September
Don't miss this chance...
Indulge yourself in totally Bengali delicacies..
This restaurant has received Times Good Food Awards 16 times..

Hilsa - whatta fish üê† üëå
Dazzling in silver look
No Bong/ foodie can't say No to Ilish.
Bongs can't imagine monsoon without Hilsa.
Oh! Calcutta deserves all the credit to bring Bengali cuisine and making it popular in Mumbai.
When we think about the most popular Bengali cuisine restaurant of this city - Oh! Calcutta comes first in mind

The ambiance totally goes with the rich culture and heritage of Bengal...
The iconic hand-pulled rickshaw, huge wall painting of Victoria Memorial, instrumental Rabindra Sangeet in the background, pictures of Bengali celebraties like Satyajit Ray and many more, an antique gramophone...
The sketches on the plates of iconic structures of Kolkata's - Howrah Bridge, Victoria Memorial & few more.
Fish net in one corner to celebrate Hilsa Festival..

Chef Rajesh Mallick created lovely dishes to satisfy the foodies' souls..
The few delicacies I tried of Hilsa festival-

1) Mochar ilish cutlet (boneless)- Absolutely awesome creation of banana flowers with boneless hilsa, mild spices, tawa fried..

2) Posto narkol ilish (bonless) - A great combination of poppy seeds grated coconut paste cooked with lots of care with boneless Hilsa.

3) Lal Lankar ilish (with bone) - a thick red gravy of tomato chilles (without seeds) paste, covered a fish piece of Hilsa..

4) Meghna Majhider ilish (Boneless) - the name comes from Meghna river, very popular for good quality of Hilsa fishes, the thick gravy was prepared by grated coconut and curry paste.
The birthday celebration started with special curated menu by Chef-

Signature Mocktails -
1) Gondhoraj lebur sorbot - (aromatic special kind of green thick-skinned) lemons were infused in water & sugar syrup, they are getting these lemons from Kolkata on daily basis.

2) Aam pora sorbot - Roasted green mango pulp is used to make this refreshing mocktail..

Veg signature starters -
1) Chana korai sutir chop - patty made of cottage cheese and smashed green peas

2) Mochar chop - a delicacy, banana flower patty with mild spices

3) Gondhoraj Paneer tikka - Soft paneer tikka infused with special aromatic lemon juice

Non-veg starters -
4) Mochar Ilish - boneless Hilsa and banana flower cutlets

5) Gondhoraj Bhapa Murgi Kebab - an amazing creation of aromatic lemon juice, minched chicken steamed dumplings, wrapped in banana leaves

6) Murshidabadi Murgi Fry - boneless roasted chicken with mild spices

7) Fish Fry - Big size Bhetki pieces were marinated & deep fried with crispy coating..

Veg Maincourse -
1) Jhinge Aloo Posto - ridged gourd and potatoes were cooked in poppy seeds paste

2) Cholar Daal - traditional preparation of Bengal gram lentil.

3) Aloor Dom - a very popular Bengali dish of baby potatoes curry

4) Til Lonkaar Tarkari - a mixed vegetables curry cooked in sesame seeds green chilies & coriander leaves paste

Non-veg Maincourse -
5) Bhapa Ilish  6) Kosha Mangsho  7) Chingri Malai curry  8) Fish Tomatoor Jhal served with Luchi & steamed rice 

Tomato dates sweet chutney 
Chaler Payesh - a yummy kheer, sweet Paan,   sparkling wine, made the birthday celebration totally memorable

reviews.text: It has an old feel to. So it's understandable why people are nostalgic about it. Food is average, but it's very good value for money. Loads of non-veg items to choose from. Olympia is one of the rare gems hidden in by lanes of colaba. An age old eatry specialised in daily fares olympia is best known for their amazing breakfast and lunch. Place start early and serves an amazing spread of kheema, eggs for breakfast. It has been ritual for me since last few years to start my Colaba stroll with a pitstop at Olympia. Don‚Äôt forget to try their luncj specials including chicken/mutton masala, Biryani and kebabs. Spiced moderately and served with indian bread roti you‚Äôll not be disappointed after trying it. The prices
Are dirt cheap and hygiene, quality, service are top notched.

The only reason I‚Äôm giving 3 stars is because the quality matched the prices. Very cheap place and the food is reflected. Nothing fancy at all. 
Also, it‚Äôs a very local (religious) place, and as foreigners we felt out of place a bit. No English at all. 
Eggs happened to be oily, bread was fresh and fluffy. 
Overall- not going back.
Friendly stuff. It was almost empty. 450rps for 220g burger Juicy Lucy and 480rps for french fries...??? Totally rip off.

Out of the Blue

Service: 5/5

On recomnendation of waiter 'Vinod', we went for tasty 'Dahi Ke Kabab' and 'Khatte Meethe Aloo Chat'. The rhird starter was 'Papadi Paneer Cheese Shots' which was beautifully presented in a small glass on 'chutney and salad base'.

For main course we had lovely 'Cheese Garlic Kulcha' and 'Pyaaz Tandoori Paratha' with delicious 'Veg. Amritsari', Chole, Pickle and Curd.

A typical Punjabi meal cannot end, without a 'Lassi'.

Ended the meal wirh sweet 'Peda Lassi', which I was curious to know, 'phirni' for dessert, presenred in an earthen-ware and mouth-freshner'.

I recently got this splendid opportunity to visit this place Oye Kake in Lower parel
Right from the food till the service, everything was top notch.
By far the best vegan food I have ever had:
Here is the list of the food items I had:
1)MOCKTAILS:-
 A)Banana Lassi:Nice sweet and tasty lassi was very good to have.
 B)Kesar Lassi:Nice and refreshing kesar lassi.

2)STARTERS:-
 A)Papadi Paneer Cheese Shots:Four glass shots of paneer in cheese dipped in creamy tasty mixture of green chutney,brown onions and tomatoes.
 B)Hara Bhara Kabab:Crispy and tasty kabab's served with green chutney was very good in taste.

3)MAINS:-
 A)Subj Paneer Biryani: Jain Biryani which actually blew my mind away with it's taste. Rice was well cooked and it was very good to have.
 B)Veg Amritsari with Butter Kulcha:Tasty and delicious amritsari mix subji with kulcha which was crafted well with butter was a treat to have.

4)DESSERTS:-
Amritsar ki Fruit Ice-cream: An indian form given to fruit custard is a perfect definition of the dish.

restaurants.address: Amin Compound, Kalina Kurla Rd, Kolivery Village, Kunchi Kurve Nagar, Kalina, Santacruz East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400029, India

reviews.text:
Delivery review

The food was delivered tamper proof and oil was also not leaking out of the box, onion and lemon was packed in a small box which was very good.

Food review:

Had ordered their best selling dish banjara kofta and yes there is a reason why this is the best selling dish.

1)The stuffing of kofta was superb.
2)The masala used for preparing the gravy was excellent.
3)With perfect balance of sweetness and spiciness, this is one of the best dish from oye pappe.5/5

Worth: I would say it's worth the taste but the quantity needs to improve.3.5/5

Located in Santacruz, Oye pappe! Is a delivery kitchen which serves Vegetarian dishes of North Indian cuisine. They serve some tasty starters, mains and alot more. 

To start off with, we had:
-Bharwan Mushroom Tikka : These were some soft mushrooms marinated in tikka masala and served with grilled capsicum bits and onion along with a spicy yet delicious chutney. Not to forget the mushrooms were filled with cheese and hence were really yummy! A must try definitely. 

-Daal Makhani :Daal makhani was fine. Not the best I've had but a nice dish to try out with their delectable naans. 

-Shah Jahani Biryani. : 
Spicy Biryani rice mixed with veggies and paneer was delicious. Not a fan of Vegetable Biryani but this was great especially when savored with Dahi Boondi. 

-Subzi Panchali: 
Had fine vegetables in them but too oily. The taste wasn't something to brag about. 

-Paneer Lababdar : 
Probably a dish paneer lovers would look forward to. Personally I didn't find this all too appetizing. But no harm in trying it out. 

-Chilli Cheeze Naan:
Well the best naans ever. They were basically butter naan filled with cheese and chilli flakes. The perfect naans to have with the gravy dishes. 

All in all, a nice place to order vegetarian dishes. What I liked about them was that the delivery was made on time. The quantity of the dishes was decent. A fine place to try out Indian dishes.
Amazing place! Delicious food and friendly place.

I have been meaning to try oye pappe since long... I would give oye pappe! a thumbs up for the delivery speed and food packaging. But the food was a bit of a turndown.

The cheese veg seekh kebabs were dry and tough, also there was hardly any cheese on it.

The paneer makhani roll was too much on the sweeter side

The only Good thing amongst our order was the veg Hyderabadi biryani .. I would not advise carnivores to order from here at all.

Oye Teri - The Kulcha Kulture, Boriwali

SEATING ARRANGEMENT & SERVICE : ( 3.5/ 5)
This place is near to the Boriwali station so travelling at this outlet is not a tough task. Have decent seating arrangements and staff were very helpfull. Now coming to the food, As the Name suggest, this place serves some fabulous kulchas but one should also try their side starters.

Has thick consistency and tasted good. 

 Then some appetizers

reviews.text: Everyday I visit in morning to have one of my favourite breakfast because I drive my clients nearby. Poori with cooked dry vegetables. I get it packed for lunch too. Being a Vegan I'm glad its not prepared with ghee & its the most simple, hygienic & tasty food.

Pancham Puriwala is pure vegetarian restaurant which is located near to CST station, Mumbai Maharashtra India 
.
This restaurant owner came from Uttar Pradesh and started their Puri business in Mumbai after few years their succeed in this business, then started a restaurant named it Pancham Puriwala. 
Pancham Puriwala mainly known for their pancham thali & this thali is quite famous in local, travellers and food lovers.
Beside this thali they also serves so many other types of thali and some other types of food items ( and we called as combo like Rajma chawal , Paneer Chawal, Chola Chawal, Chola puri, Rajma puri and many more)..

In Pancham thali it's consist of five different types of Sabzi (gravy) like Chola, Paneer, Aloo Tamatar, Bhendi fry and Kadi & four different types of puri :- 1 piece masala puri, 1 pic beetroot puri, 1 pic besan stuff puri and 1 pic Sadi puri , Matar Pulao , kheer , Chacha..
My experience was amazing and am loving their thali, this thali cost me Rs.150. Which is quite pockets friendly..

Timing 10 am - 11 pm

Any restaurant which is crowded definitely will be a safer place to eat. Pancham Puriwala is a similar place, small restaurant, legacy of over 150 years and yummy puries.

If you are near CST Station, and feel hungry, this is the place to head to.

You may have to wait for ten minutes or so during lunch and dinner time, but for sure you will get tasty and hygienic food. Must try.

Don't expect luxury seating as the food is the USP here and not ambience.

One of the best places to relish vegetarian food. The puri served here with varieties of bhaji is just amazing. Pocket friendly and quick service. It's a must visit for food lovers #mumbaifoodie #foodlove

restaurants.address: 39-B, Suren Rd, Gundavali, Andheri East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400047, India

reviews.text:
Since my office is near to this restaurant I thought of ordering from the same through Zomato. So the first points are for zomato for the discount and super fast delivery.

Coming to the order, I had ordered an Aloo Paratha Chole Combo. Coming to the entire package it contained 2 Aloo Parathas, one box of chole and one small box of Boondi Raita. The aloo parathas were just awesome. Properly wrapped in the silver foil paper and they were cut into half. The aloo parathas tasted just perfect being that they were not too spicy and neither were they overcooked. Just perfect. The best part was that they did not put any chilies according to the special instructions. The parathas themselves were so thick that it became difficult to go beyond one and a half with all the chole and boondi raita.

Coming to the chole, the gravy was really tasty not too oily and contained nice amounts of chole. The chole were also properly cooked and it perfectly complemented the parathas. The chole was a bit on the spicier side. Coming to the boondi raita it was also good. The curd was thick and fresh and the best part was it was not even a bit sour. The boondi had been properly dipped in the curd and had become soft which was good. And since it was served cold it did have a soothing effect on eating the hot parathas and spicy chole.

All in all the items were really good. The packing and all was also perfect. Would definitely recommend to try these parathas. Just super good and tasty

Had a simple veg thali without rice. They served me 5 butter chapatis, mix veg, dal fry, boondi raita, onion, and pickle. Two chapati out of five was of yesterdays. Mix veg was also not fresh hence they added some extra spices, salt to cover the spoilt texture and smell. Moreover, the price of this thali was whopping Rs.162. No idea about their parathas or other stuff. But the tendency of mixing stale food is absolutely not acceptable. No recommendation for this Andheri east outlet at Suren Road.
Ordered aloo methi paratha, great quantity and taste, it consisted of 2 Parathas served along with dal makhani and dahi, enough for 2 people

Paratha world has always been successful in making me feel amazed with their fabulous quality of food and timely service. I must have tried parathas from several competing brands and do make them on my own several times but these guys make it in such a remarkable way like none other. I like to stick to traditional ones because they give you the true authenticity of what a paratha should be. Simple aloo paratha with chole and pickle sounds like my kind of occasional lunch. 4 pieces of paratha is more than likely to suffice anyone's hunger and so do it mine..

I ordered special stuffed paratha thali. Packaging of food was good. Neatly packed no oil stains around the box or the cover. There are 5 types of thali boxes which you can try. I found this one to be the most suitable. In my option of choosing a special paratha I decided to try paneer onion capsicum because I like the combination. Along with the paratha I received jeera rice, dal makhni, butter paneer gravy, raita, papad and gulab jamun. Price of this box is 240 and I believe 2 people can share it. The rest of the things like dal rice gravy are one person quantity but a stuffed paratha with it makes it difficult for a single person to finish. According to me this meal box was worth every penny. It was good in taste and value.

reviews.text:

Lamb Schezwan

Chicken in Green Garlic Sauce

Prawns Burnt Garlic Rice

Chicken Chowmein

Chicken Chowmein, was for by far the best of the lot, very subtle and calms your hunger with its chicken stock. noodles was cooked perfectly and all the veggies tossed really brought this dish to life.

Overall a great experience.

reviews.text: Quality and Quantity both are good. It's very small place but have lots of Tables provided to sit. This place is good to have a Tea or bun maska. They even serve Chinese food. And various chicken Dishes. They Serve water in a Bottle. You can also ask them for Bisleri bottle instead of normal Water bottle. Place is good and it's very pocket friendly. It is not expensive at all. You can also take delivery. They provide good service. Most importantly it's open for 24/7. Hungry by 3 am go to Qutuz.

Irani tea is the most famous tea in Mumbai since the name of this city was Bombay. 
This irani tea was mostly seen in a Parsi restuarant which are now very few in numbers left in Mumbai now people have copied the recipe and are opening their shop, its very reach in taste with pure and thick milk less water in it as it is continuously kept on low flame which makes it thicker by making the water get evaporated.

One of the best irani chai cafes in town. Flavor and taste of tea is very good. It's so unique unlike other chai which we get in India. So thick and creamy one. They serve Bun maska as well which is so yummy to eat with chai. Must try it when in Mira road. It's so refreshing. 5* for chai and prompt service.

The mutton keema here was nothing like the other irani caf√©s in Mumbai. The hotel as well as the kitchen was not clean. Nevertheless, the Iranian Tea was good and they made it the traditional way, so 2 stars

I have ordered food from swiggy, these people delivered it in one hour, on top of that the packing was so poor quality and food taste was worst, such hotels and restaurants should get banned and shut down...

reviews.text: Nicely done interiors with touches of Bengali sensibilities. This place in the by lanes of Lokhandwala area have outdoor seating too. Menu is purely Bengali cuisine, food lack authenticity, probably to adjust to the palate of cosmopolitan crowd. Chef needs a serious brush up in Bengali cooking. Polite and courteous staff. Pricing is based on location only.

The only thing that pushed back is that the restaurant charges Service Charge@10% on the total bill amount. Rest being an authentic Bengali cuisine restaurant, they has a good spread of menu. Food quality & taste wise are also good, along with their services. Ambient of the resturant shall give you a complete flavour of Bengal.

I visited this place for lunch with a friend and this place serves amazingly authentic Bengali food 
The ambience was so atheistic and peaceful 
I was totally in love the mirror work on one of the wall they have 
They have indoor and outdoor seating area . 
To enjoy the best of Bengal I would suggest seating indoor 
From the interior to the Plates and spoons everything was so traditional 
 
They serve a variety of veg and non veg dishes as Bengalis are very well known for their Sweet water fishes they have it all . 

Starting with the food I ordered for 
Beetroot Chops : There were 2 rolls of beetroot served made with little spices and were perfectly crumped fried 
Even though it was fried they made sure it does not losses it taste . 
It was served with chutney and it tasted amazing 

Other than this 
I ordered Luchi, basically Luchi is a bengali puri  it is made up of maida flour and served hot 
 Bhaja  Masala Dumm Alooo : The dum alloo tasted so good ,It had a perfect blend of all spices and the gravy was so perfect also the portion this dish was good enough. 

Last but not the least the desert 
Let me take a moment and tell you guys that this was really a different and one of the best Indian Dessert I have ever had it had such a perfect amount of sweetness to it 
It was Narkel gur patishapta 
so basically it is a pan cake made up of semolina flour stuffed with a filling of jaggery and coconut  they served 2 pieces and it was all worth 
Other than the food and ambience I would also say they have really economical prices and the cleanliness and the customer service was so on point . 
It was a good experience and there are very few restaurants in Mumbai who serves bengali food so this place is worth the visit .

Visited this place for dinner. Dimmed lights, Bengali music in background and traditional Bengali artworks make a very warm n homestyle ambieance.
We started with -
1) Lebu Paani - Nimbu Sharbat which tasted quite different from usual one as this had the gondraj lemon.
2)Chicken Bakura Pan Fry - very tangy taste due to lemon,less oily, crisp outside n soft n juicy chicken inside.
3) Robibar Barbela - the traditional Bengali Sunday chicken curry which had potatoes,very spicy has strong cloves flavour but tasty.
4)Basmati rice - usual plan basmati rice
5) Kolkata Fish Fry- bhetki fillet coated with breadcrumbs n deep fried but very thin slice
Loved their traditional plates made out of kasa metal.
Very friendly staff.

I'm not a Bengali, but I had descent amount of Bengali food in Bengali houses. Keeping no expectations I went to Rajbari Rasoi and it hit me with pleasent surprise.

Taste and portion size were good. It's being maintained by a nice lady who also helped us figuring out what we would like and what we should try to be a Bengali experience. She also made us(not on menu) a mix veg curry in poppy seeds and muster which I really liked, and would like to visit again for that same dish.

Betki Paturi was descent, but chicken kousha was a disappointment. As they claim all the recepies are home cooked style so you won't find it spicey.

Ordered:

Mix veg curry - super tasty
Chicken kousha - below average
Betki Paturi - good
Luchi - perfect
Moong Dal - good
Rice - good

Ambience - Could be better, if remove few tables, it's really tight.
Staff - Excellent(it's only been couple of months it's opened)
Hygiene - Good(has fishy smell once you enter into the place, within 5-10 mins you won't mind it)

Place has a artistic outlook to it, with music, paintings, small waterfall and wallpapers. Though tables are really tightly placed.

It's an excellent place to visit at least once to try, you won't regret.

reviews.text:

Royal China As Altogether 3 Outlets Across India, i.e Mumbai, Pune and Delhi. We Visited Mumbai Outlet Which is Situated Near Sterling Cinemas, Hazarimal Somani Marg, Fort

Veg Mushroom Bao, Chicken Prawns Sui Mai and
Prawns Crab Dumblings With Dimsums, Dumplings & Bao, We Ordered For Mocktails To Refresh Ourselves Were Virgin Diequri, Mumbai Ginger Blossom and Lemongrass Blossom

Moving Onto Traditional Mains, Royal China Provides Lots Of Options in Mains, We Managed To Have Few Of Them That Were Mushroom Pot Rice and Exotic Veg. We All Know About Desserts Section at Royal China.

Yes! Yes I Had The Signature Desserts Here. Which are Melting Chocolate Dome (Signature) and Banana Toffee. Overall We had Wonderful Time at Royal China. Awesome Outlet with Amazing Cuisine and Atmosphere. Highly Recommending This Place If you are looking for Such type of Cuisine Around CST Station Area
One of the finest traditionally authentic Chinese in Mumbai

Visited this restaurant last week to spend time with a friend who actually lives a few minutes walk from this place. He recommended it highly. Every dish we ate was a hit. A very interesting and extensive menu. Had a set of Appetizers that involved Chicken wings, Caramelised Onions and a Arugula based salad.

I have been visiting this beautiful restaurant for nearly a decade and it has not disappointed me once. Even I though I live overseas now, I found my self helplessly drawn to Salt Water Cafe without hesitation or second thought. The menu has remained largely similar with some brilliant new additions. The spaghettini has been my go to food for every type of lunch or dinner setting and the recipe is still authentic and refreshing. I was so pleased to be remembered by the staff there who offered a warm welcome and flawless service. Their loyalty program is very customer centric which makes it unique and enjoyable. In my day of living in Mumbai (Bandra), I have had breakfast lunch and dinner at Salt Water and would do it many times over if the future gives me an opportunity to do so!

An excellent place to have a leisurely get-together with your gang. Almost all the items in the menu are above par. Though we did find the Grilled Aubergine S/W a tad too spicy for comfort. 
Prices are a bit on the higher side plus there's a 10% service charge in the bill in addition to the 5% VAT. Noise levels are on the higher side, thanks to the reflecting glass. Don't forget to ask for a cushion as the wooden seats can be hard on you.

reviews.text:
Shamiana at Taj Mahal Palace, the name says it all.It's basically a 24-hour cosmopolitan food restaurant, located at the lobby level hence attracts majority of visitors.
Attending Breakfast buffet for the first time at Shamiana was a amazing experience, with a vast menu, and variety of dishes. It involved everything right from detox water, juices, egg station , Indian breakfast, waffles, pastries, fresh fruits, tea and coffee and many more things.
It was worth the experience,it was lovely to help yourself to whatever you wanted. Comfortable seating and staff are extremely proficient.
Overall, I love the ambience, food and service here at Shamiana!‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

Shamiana, the original coffee shop of the city, offers an all-day dining experience with an international √† la carte menu to suit every mood and palate, from breakfast through to dinner. To start the day Shamiana serves an elaborate buffet breakfast daily. The restaurant embraces a ‚Äòrefined ease‚Äô with its relaxed environment, fresh comfort food and service that is sincere and warm. Sumptuous weekend brunches focusing on interactive experiences along with a daily blackboard of curated dishes add to the experience.
CUISINE
Multi-Cuisine
AVERAGE COST FOR TWO
1500 plus taxes
HOURS
24 hours

Restaurant has evolved perfectly from a few years back. The menu is well crafted, contains the Shamiana traditional menu items along with popular dishes from other taj locations, along with Mumbai Street fare. The interior is very trendy, dishes are flavoured beautifully and portion sizes are perfect. Not to mention the attentive, caring service. Wonderful restaurant.

We were a bit unhappy in our latest visit. Keeping up the tradition we visit shamiana on every special occasion. We didn't order much cause somehow we were unhappy from the moment we got our first food plate.

A superb experience of relishing melt in the mouth Indian delicacies. Every dish feels like it is delicately made to achieve taste and perfection. One of the rarest times that I enjoyed vegetarian as much as non vegetarian food. 
Servers are friendly and professional, attention to detail guaranteed.

reviews.text: This place does have a small dine-in. Not usually crowded.

Juss by Sindhful, this is pure veg restaurant by Sindhful. If you want to taste authentic sindhi food than this is must visit restaurant. Ambiance of this restaurant is very pleasant and clam. All walls are decorated with cultural paintings and instruments. Staff was very helpful, soft spoken and prompt in service. Coming to what I had ordered:

Rose sharbat - 5/5

Pink guava cooler - 5/5 (Highly recommended) 
This was the best cooler I have ever tried. This cooler was recommended by staff and it was just amazing. Flavours, taste, everything was just perfect. 

Pakwan chat - 5/5 
This was traditional sindhi pakwan served as chat. It was too heavy as it contained chana daal cooked in secret sindhi masala, crispy papdi with coriander and tamirind chutney. 

Bheeyan ji tikki - 5/5 (Highly recommended) 
This was lotus stem croquettes with Sindhi green masalas finished with tangy lotus stem chips. This tikkis were mouthwatering, must try from this place with tangy lotus stem chips which was just perfect. 

Veg Sindhi thali - 5/5
This thali was lip-smacking, it contained Alu tuk which was amazing starter prepared from aloo served with chilli and coriander powder. Two sabzi Bhindi basar and bhee aloo ki sabzi which was served with phulkas or poori. Sindhi curry with steamed rice, boondi raita, sindhi papad and dessert of the day which was Singhar ji mithai, this was authentic sindhi mithai it was mouthwatering.

reviews.text:
Smoke house deli is in a house that reminds me of the bread and breakfast places in New Hampshire, US. Rustic old house look with a touch of elegance inside.

The sandwich was loaded with avacado , roasted sweet potato and beet , spiced tomato , caramelized onions & cheese with a good amount of mayo.

The service was good and the staff was also very friendly.

what I appreciate the most is the consistency of the experience on every visit, and the friendly staff. 

works well for casual meals, as well as occasions

reviews.text:
We visited the place for dinner on a Sunday night. It was packed, with each table occupied.
For starters we ordered Soam's panki and daal chilla. The panki was suitably thin and had the right subtlety. I didn't fancy the chilla, found it a bit tasteless.
For the main course we ordered matar poori with dahiwale aloo and gatte ki subzi with masala satpadi. The matar poori had a good amount of mashed peas in them, which was quite nice to discover when one pulled a piece off. The gatte ki subzi was splendid. The chutneys were also very good, especially the sweet one
The place had absolutely no ambience to speak of but it was neat and clean. I do wish they'd bring finger bowls to the table instead of making us go over to a wash basin
Extremely hygienic.  Very very delicious. But the only issue is the quantity was less as compared to price. It is heavy on the pocket. However the quality is amazing.
Excellent food. Should be made more spacious. Amras Puri is great.

If you're in the Chawpatty area and are looking for an authentic Indian fare, then this is it. Great vegetarian food at reasonable prices. The sugar cane juice is highly recommended, as they put a hint of fresh lime into it, which brings out the sweetness from the cane even more!

Table arrangement is so crowded that the waiter bumped into the backside of my chair, pushing me towards the table , twice in the span of 20 minutes . Very over rated , overhyped . The Sabudana khichadi was stale and full on mirchified.  My Rajathani friend could not eat even 2 spoonfuls of that dry, firey mishmash. When we informed this to the waiter he replied that khichadi is spicy so we have added more sugar to the raita.  The raita with double , triple quantity of sugar tasted like lassi with cucumber. My panki was half cooked  to say the least.

reviews.text: A nice place for a comfortable Goan dining experience. Great food, very helpful and jovial staff. The Bombay ducks were crispy and hot. The Goan fish curry was simply delicious. The fried fish was well done. The pickle accompaniment was simply yum. Overall an enjoyable evening

Goan restaurant . Cosy interior .. not so loud music .. monday has karaoke nights . Nice vibe . Decent staff . Wifi available . No parking . Fish fry was good . Fish curry was nice n spicy . Pork sorpotel was good .

Place with good Goan and Mangalorean food, known for its seafood fare.
Ordered the bombil fry that was golden fried to perfection.
The Prawn recheado was delectable. The best choice of the day. A tad bit oily, but so is the traditional preparation. A dark red, garlicky, tangy gravy with prawns. 
The goan prawn curry with rice was heartwarming comfort food in a bowl. It was slightly lacking seasoning but nothing a little shake of salt couldnt fix. The gravy was velvety and rich with a good amount of baby prawns served with steamed rice.

The ambience however, is the reason for my below par rating. Has some peculiar smell. Is quite dingy and the AC smells musty. Not very pleasing. But the food is pretty good and is worth a visit if in pali!

Looking for some old-school bandruh Goan vibe?? This is THE place to be. One of the best places for a great Karaoke night!! The vibe is great, the food is very good too, the servers are attentive and service is super!! 
When you come here so often you bump into a lot of regulars, esp on Karaoke night. Overall I totally recommend you come here with friends.

Spice Republic is one of the places where you will feel the vibrancy of a funky themed nightlife experience. The ambiance was really nice. It does attract young generation kids. The quotes are so much quirky, catchy. It really grabs the attention of anyone. The wall paintings, decors absolutely was amazing. They really have an amazing staff very friendly with the customers. 

We went out with the KitKat shake which was really amazing. The taste was amazing. Also, we had tried this perry chilly. One of the amazing mocktails we had have. It was spicy and tangy. We totally enjoyed it! Kindly go for this one

In starters, we started with Spring roll which was really huge in quantity. The taste was so amazing. Definitely recommend ! Go out with the peri sizzler. it's spicy in taste. It came along with rice and noodles combination along with the veggies. The taste was too enjoyable. We loved it! . 

Try out there Life and death by chocolate dessert it's really out of the box. Such a lovely presentation and taste. It comes with chocolate brownie and vanilla ice cream. We enjoyed it. I am definitely recommending this place to everyone. It's amazing! Go out with your friends,family for good night life experience.

Spice Republic 
A perfect place for a vegetarian to enjoy their taste buds. The ambience is based on a theme which is old traffic road and vehicles. Some beautiful quotes related to the theme on the wall. Amazing music playing while you enjoy your food. Has a very spacious and comfortable seating arrangement. The staffs were really 

What We Had:-
Mocktail:-

Kiss on the Beach:- It has a combination of orange and cranberry making it wonderful and refreshing. It is served in a jar.

Shakes:-

Brownie Shake:- It was like any other chocolate shake with brownie pieces in it.

Starters:-

Fusion Confusion:- It was something unique by its name to try out, a combination of paneer along with rajma and cheese stuffed together. Crunchy and topped with cheese and veggies. Tasted well served with nachos.

Arabic Falafel Chaat:- This is one of the best dish we had. It was a chaat served with Lebanese and Indian cuisine style. It had potato, falafel, tomato and onions pieces in it which was really tasty

Mains:-

House Special Chicago Pizza:- Thin crust pizza loaded with creamy spicy tangy sauce and lots of cheese along with some cherry tomatoes and veggies.

Dessert:-

Life & Death by Chocolate:- Crumbled brownie served with vanilla ice cream topped with chocolate sauce and dry fruits. The brownie was warm, soft and gooey that tasted amazing with the ice cream.

The food is okayish not that great tho. The service was quick , i was getting late for a movie and got in late to the restaurant but the person attending us made sure we got the food on time and yes i did reach the movie on time. Ambience was good.

reviews.text: Hotel is good for family and friends. Its pure veg hotel and fully air-condition. Approx 700 rs for two people. Earlier food taste was good but now a day's food taste is degraded. This is a very pocket friendly yet great restaurant. The quality and quantity of food is worth of each rupee you pay. The staff is quite good and service is quick too (provided there is not heavy rush which is found mostly on weekend nights). Some of the dishes that I recommend are:

-Veg Spring Roll: Crisp and properly fried. It has perfect blend of vegetables. Schezwan chutney served with it is very tasty.

-Paneer Kolhapuri: The flavour of 'kolhapuri masala' can be strongly felt. It gives the unique rustic taste to the dish

-Veg Manchurian: Manchurian balls taste different and heavenly. They are more crispy and flavourful than usually served in other restaurants

-Shahi Biryani: This special type of biryani is made with fresh garam masala and topped with fried onions. It is served with Raita and green peas gravy

-Pav Bhaji: It just tastes like any other Pav Bhaji. It is really tasty though. But nothing unique about it.

Unique combination right? But it tastes delicious. Dosa served with gravy Manchurian, coconut chutney and schezwan sauce. Tastes goes along very well.

Recommended.

reviews.text:
This is one of those places which was super hyped among my friend circle so it had to be in my list!!
However it did not fulfill my expectations which I had from it.
A decent spread of starters and main course to go along with the desserts at the end.

The chicken starters were average with either very less or too much salt/masala. Paneer Tikka was a big let down as it was too bland. The Dal Bukhara was very well made along with sarson da saag and makkai roti. Prawns was missing from the menu which is surprising as most buffet places have it in their menu.

The ambiance is good and there is live Bhangra every 30-40 mins which makes the place very lively and people are often seen shaking a leg.
The staff was very supportive and polite. A few changes in the menu would surely make this a great place.
