We decided to go to the Taste of Punjab in Bandra for a week day lunch. And we chose to have veg buffet. Ture to its name, the decor and the set up is very colourful with some shine and glitter.
We started with having some chat. One could walk to the chat counter and enjoy your chat at the counter, as if enjoying street food. Or you can ask it to be served on your table. 
This was followed by starters which were served on the table. There was choice of 5 starters and it would be served unlimited. Same was for chass / lassi.
The lunch buffet spread was limited but good. Different roti / paratha options were available and we're served fresh from the kitchen. 
The desert options were good. Indian desserts are anyway irresistible, and that's exactly what it was here.
The staff was courteous. The service was good, but have been a bit faster. The ambience and music was good. Bollywood Punjabi music was playing in the background.

Think it was a bad day for us. 2 Functions very noisy.  Food was ok but I will never visit again. Table we sat was so shabby n full of stain. Toilet was dirty. While booking  ur table pls ask if there is any function, if yes then don't go as u will not be given preference. The price not worth it that's what we felt. There r many restaurants in Bandra u can enjoy much more for the price we paid.

It was a nice place very spacious and well organised
Decor was very nice and North styled, staff was polite and gentle.
Food was amazing any one who wants to get best north indian cuisine must try Taste of Punjab‚ù§

restaurants.address: Sea Face, Ground Floor, Hotel Parkway, Off, Old Cadell Rd, near Shivaji Park, Dadar West, Dadar, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400028, India

reviews.text: Love the vibes of this place. It has two parts one like a dining area with plentiful yellow lights and other is like a lounge with dim lights , mirrored walls and good music. Food might seem a little expensive but it has a good taste to it. The pizzas in particular are famous. The staff is welcoming and always around just in case you need anything so service is good. The only let down was that they dont allow birthday celebrations like cake cutting but other than that it is a good place near Shivaji park , Dadar. Easily accessible too. Must try once.
Love the food and the vibe of this restaurant!!!! The high chairs section is good and the cocktails here are great creations Pizzas are a must try

Food is usually good here. We had the vegetarian lasagne and the brown rice with mushroom ragout. Portions were great and fed the three not us very well 

We were there for lunch and even though the food, quality, and quantity was good the service was not up to the mark 

Servers weren't around often enough. They didn't check in on us once the food was served. Had to wait a while to get a pepper mill. I brought this up to the manager on duty and he simply said that they were short in staff. At which point I mentioned that we had not seen him come around either. Overall an unsatisfactory response from the manager 

I have usually only been there in the evenings and the service has been great. Not so much during the day

Had this experience sometime back, wasn‚Äôt allowed for having a two year old with me. Such a horrible experience the way we were told off. Don‚Äôt know about the food as never got till there, but place had a very dark and gloomy decor.. not preferred choice neway.

I've been here multiple times and am yet to try something I didn't like. All the cocktails and dishes have been amazing. Particularly the truffle pasta. The staff is warm and attentive. Probably going to keep visiting this restaurant over and over again.

restaurants.address: Number 9, Juhu Supreme Shopping Center, 13, opposite Criti Care hospital, Model Town Society, Gulmohar Road, JVPD Scheme, Juhu, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400049, India

reviews.text: They are maintaining quality and safety standards. Found social distancing, all employees were wearing masks and gloves.

Excellent would be an understatement , It‚Äôs a great place for every tastebud sweet , sour , spicy , tangy , creamy & everything is fresh , never tried dry snacks though , had a lockdown reunion of school .

A very good Sweet and snacks shop at Juhu. Now they have also started restaurant, with seating arrangement inside and outside. The eatables are made in pure Ghee. Taste is good. Staff is good. They have many items on their menu now. Only problem here is there is no queue system. People just barge in and crowd the counter to place their order. Some people are forced to wait longer due to this.

High end version of Mumbai chat stores. Delight for Chaat, India food, Sweet lovers - Loaded with goodness & freshness. Also, high level of hygiene, varieties, food quality, *prices* and A/C. üëçüëç
Amazing place! Tasty and delicious treats.. must try masala dhudh..

restaurants.address: D'souza Compound, Oberoi Garden Esate, Chandivali Rd, Hillside Cooperative Society, Yadav Nagar, Chandivali, Powai, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400072, India

reviews.text: Delicious South Indian dishes... Must try but takeaway Only

It's a casual dining located at Chandivali, Andheri East. It specializes in South Indian cuisine. The food served here never fails to impress its diners.

The cost for two is 350 which is economical.

There are very few good restaurants near Boomerang and Oberoi Garden.  Thambi is one of a good option.

Recommended.
Idli sambhar is delectable with the option of 2 chatnis

Best South Indian restaurant in Mumbai. All food items very tasty and amazing.
One should visit the restaurant to taste all food.
Amazing dosas at best prices. Light food, good service, cleanliness maintained..

restaurants.address: Railway Station, opposite Kotak Mahindra ATM, Dada Patil Wadi, Naupada, Thane West, Thane, Maharashtra 400602, India

reviews.text: Quality of food is nice. Ambience is also good. But the price of food is setting high day by day. Thullu chesse is too much good here.
I visited this before 2 days, currently only take aways And limited option are available. My fav paneer achari was not available  on that day üò≠ and white sauce was also not there in my parcel.

Appetite momos is located outside Thane station due to which getting a decent parking spot is always a headache. Ambience is decent, not that attractive though. Best place for college going students. Pocket friendly and delicious food. Recently they‚Äôve also started serving mocktails and ice tea which are pretty good. 

Recommend dishes:
1. Chilli cheese momos.
2. Chicken achari momos.
3. Cheese peri peri momos.
4. Mutton nawabi momos
Amazing...Must go place

restaurants.address: Hotel Marine Plaza, 29 Marine Drive, 2nd Cross Rd, Churchgate, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400020, India

reviews.text: A very well managed hotel and their strength is their well trained staff. Been there on a date, its good food with amazing view.

I personally have always lived this place. Love to sit and eat with a lovely view of the marine drive and the sea.. Service is good and not to forget the food.. overall a nice place for a meeting or meal with family & friends.. Ambiance is also nice. You looking at a refreshing time with nice meal or beverages, this is place you need to be.

The restaurant 'The Bayview' (Hotel Marine Plaza) gives you an excellent view of Marine Drive. I have visited with my office colleagues for Team Lunch.  For food, their buffet consists of various vegetarian and non vegetarian starters, main course, desserts and many more. Food prepared by skilled chef. Polite staff. The ambiance was good. Overall great experience.

The Bayview ‚ù§Ô∏è

Some Restaurants are on your Bucket List and this was the one for me. Finally I visited The Bayview and trust me I fell in love with this place more.

This place gives you a serene and beautiful view of the Marine Lines. It's so peaceful to just watch the view and have a lovely Dining experience.

We opted for the Lunch Buffet and left very much happy with our Experience. They have such a widespread Buffet for the visitors. The Food is the best hands down.

***APPETIZERS***

The Soups and Appetizers came to the Table. A very few limited options but very yummy and delicious. I loved the Shorba and the appetizers.

***BUFFET***

I tried different option from the Salad Bar, the Bakery, Main course and the Dessert options. I loved the following dishes a lot.

Crab Sushi: A big fan of Sushi and this was one of the best.

Chicken Pepper Salami: Lovely salami with a hint of pepper.

Bengali Chicken Curry: This was an authentic Bengali curry with delicious Chicken pieces.

Paan Cheesecake: My Dessert as well as dish of the day. Wow this was such a unique and mouthwatering dessert. I was simply floored by this Cheesecake.

I definitely recommend this place for Buffet Lovers.

Food: 5/5
Staff: 5/5
Ambience: 5/5
Value for Money: 4/5

The bayview restaurant is a beautiful dine out venue over lapping the dazzling waters of marine drive. The venue has a gorgeous buffet spread which can be thoroughly enjoyed with a beautiful view.

The buffet spread consists of a variety of Indian, continental and chinese dishes. They also have live counters where you can ask them to prepare something for you before your eye. The dessert counter is more than inviting having more than 5 kinds. 

While the buffet has a widespread of eateries, we felt there could be some beverages like fresh juices which could be added.

restaurants.address: 2, AB Nair Rd, Gaothan Number 2, Vithal Nagar, Juhu, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400049, India

reviews.text: My friend and I, from Canada, had a distinct pleasure of partaking of this unique style food. The multi-course meal, a blend of dishes of Gujarati, Afghani, Rajastani, Sindhi food and their variations was delicious. The hostess gave a preamble of the traditions behind the foods.

If you have attended a bohri wedding you would have surely tried their thaal. The lingering taste of that thaal made me try the bohri delicacies once again. Ordered a few dishes from this delivery outlet:

Chicken cheese shahi rolls: Highly recommended. You surely need to try this dish if you love the combo of cheese and chicken.

Smoked mutton samosa: Minced mutton filled in a samosa. Great preparation great taste.

Pakki murgh biryani : Every grain of rice in this preparation was good in size along with sufficient pieces of chicken. Though had higher expectations in its taste.

Moms caramel custard: A perfect way to end the dinner with this soft custard. Recommended

Overall a great place to order from. In time service.

Back from office Early on Friday and decide to order food from a place which has been on my wishlist for a long time. The delivery was on time and the taste of the food was out of this world. We had Chicken Russian cutlet,Smoked Keema mutton Samosa,Paki Murg bori biryani and Moong dal halwa, the Moong Dal Halwa was the best I have had in recent times. A big thumps up to the restaurant.

I have always been very fond of Mughlai and North Indian food. So I am always looking to try new places that serve this cuisine because it‚Äôs my comfort food.
Recently came across Bohri Kitchen and ordered-

1. Paneer and Peanut Samosas- Crisp Samosas stuffed with a filling of paneer and peanut. When I first saw this on the menu, I was a bit apprehensive about how it will be, but I was tempted to try it because i wanted to taste how these two ingredients would go along. And to my surprise, the samosas tasted really nice, the combination really worked. 
2. Cheese Corn Cutlets- They were size of my palm, they tasted really nice. The saltiness of cheese and sweetness of corn was a good blend. The crust of the cutlet was not crisp and the binding was not in place. Taste was on point, the crust can be worked on and made more crisp. 
3. Mom‚Äôs special Paneer and Veggie Biryani- just like the name says, it really tastes like it‚Äôs homemade, very less oil, packed with veggies and paneer and perfectly spiced. 
4. Mom‚Äôs Caramel Custard- it was well set, the texture was really good and had the right amount of sugar. A very light and delicious dessert. 
I am a vegetarian so the options for me were a little limited, but if you eat non-veg, you should definitely check out their menu.

Ordered home delivery from Bohri Kitchen juhu outlet. 
TBK is a delivery outlet that serves tasty North Indian, Mughlai & Biryani dishes.

Delivery took approx 20-25 mins. 
Food was delivered hot, well packed and tightly sealed which dint cause any wreckage or spills. 

We were just two of us & were in the mood to try some tasty quick bites and biryani so we ordered as follows :- 
        
1. Tur Dal & Jeera Patti samosa 

Ingredient mix blended perfectly & Each portion offers 4 small pcs which are mild in taste. Have it with the theekha and Meetha chutney provides. It tastes much better. 

2. Cheese Corn Cutlets 

1 portion offers 2 big pieces. Cutlet‚Äôs outer layer was crispy and inside it was soft with cheese and corn combined which oozed out and made it yummy üòã 

3. Mom‚Äôs Paneer Veg Biryani
Bohri kitchen is known to serve delicious biryani‚Äôs and when I opened the box I could see why. It looked and tasted divine. 
The flavours were well balanced and paneer was a nice mix to it. 
Rich in texture, flavour & taste this dish is highly recommended. They serve curd/ raita too. 

4. Gulab Jamun 
Perfect way to end my dinner with some meetha in the form of Gulab Jamun. Soft, tasty and sweet ( just the way I like it ). 

One thing Bohri Kitchen needs to work on is the quantity / portion size of the quick bites which I felt was less for the price.

All in all a great delivery place to order some tasty food.

restaurants.address: Unit-1, Process House, S.B. Road, Kamala Mills, Near Radio Mirchi Office Lower, Parel, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400013, India

reviews.text: Had a fab time here with the team from Dental Concepts for our celebratory meal. They kept bringing out food and the service was excellent.  Has a wonderful vibe and ambience in the restaurant. A very trendy Indian with traditional flavours. We ordered so many things.  Its similar to Indian tapas and sharing plates.  Well worth a visit.  I will visit again next time I am in India!

How does one even begin to describe an experience called The Bombay Canteen? Right from the venue to the food and wine to the service with a smile, all of it adds to create total experience. Its a place for people who really want to enjoy a good meal rather than just grab a bite and run. The staff treats you like a guest and recommends and then paces out the courses just like the way it should be. Look forward to my next trip.

I had this place on my must visit list from 2017 but could never go. January 2020 is the first time I get to visit and the experience left me a little aloof. From what I gathered by reading through reviews my expectations were possibly placed differently. The food presentation was top notch but the quantity left a little more to be desired. I understand the nuances of fine dining but I believe that portion sizes shouldn‚Äôt be abysmally small for the price any place charges. We were a group of four and all four of us felt the same and therefore we made a quick exit. Had a couple of chhotas (their version of bar bites) then an appetizer or two and a couple of drinks. Ambience and presentation were definitely beyond comparison but as I said earlier the portion size and relative pricing leave a significant room for improvement.

WOW! What an awesome place 'The Bombay Canteen' really was...we truly had an amazing time engaging with the staff and had some great food items. The ambience, food quality, staff courteousness & overall experience was just simply great! Watch through the Kodak moments captured during the visit to get the flavour...

This restaurant is a must for anyone who wants to experience the best of modern Indian food in a stylish environment. We enjoyed the ‚ÄúFeed Me‚Äù Menu - each of the 12 small plates was an explosion of flavours which complimented each other. Service by Rajesh was excellent.

restaurants.address: Shop 10, 11, 12, Springfield 1, Sundar Ln, Malad, Orlem, Malad West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400064, India

reviews.text: There's no such place in Malad better than this one. I would specially mention about its geographical location. The surrounding area is entertained by lesser crowd which serves to be a unique point. The quantity of drinks or shakes is worth the cost but when it comes to pasta, even one person cannot fill up the stomach partially. Menu is in the modern style however the names are confusing as the staff doesn't repeat the order again and they tend to forget. I had to wait 20 mins for a lemonade which was quite depressing. Staff is friendly and efficient. The place and the interior is worth spending time here. Just some improvements and this cafe would prosper to its best.

This place is located at malad ! Nice & comfortable place with outdoor & indoor sittings with good ambience & low background music ! The place was not so crowded ! Service was quick with good staff ! 

We ordered - 
1. Chicken roast salad - which was amazing & lil sweet it had pineapples ! 
2. Italian parmesan - roasted chicken topped with cheese & basil 
3. Lemonade - perfectly made ! 

Loved the food & the place !
Quaint little place for breakfast or catching up with friends. Friendly stuff and good food.

Great new place in Orlem - the Uncle's Kitchen lane - but the problem with Burrow Cafe is the same as with many good Indian restaurants: the waiters have no clue about the food on their menu. We ordered a salad called White Queen's Guilty Pleasure and the first ingredient written below was potato but what came to our table had not a single speck of potato. When we quizzed the waiter, first he confidently said that this salad doesn't come with potatoes. We showed him the menu card and then he thought for a moment and said that customers complained and so they have stopped giving potato in this particular salad. Hilarious, isn't it? So these little things are what completely ruins a great restaurant experience. Anyway, the food here is really good, especially the tenderloin items. And they've got a lovely outdoor sitting setup, which you'll prefer because the staff is always chatting inside.
Nice cozy place with a variety of tasty foods. Worth ordering from burrow cafe

restaurants.address: Shop Number 22, Oshiwara Link Plaza, New Link Road, Near, Oshiwara Police Station Rd, Mhada Colony, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400053, India

reviews.text: When it‚Äôs authentic it‚Äôs out of the world, Yes this place is one if those where you deep dive into the authentic flavours of the distinct Calcutta cuisine. The fun part was I couldn‚Äôt stop eating and ended up ordering a lot more then I generally eat. Each dish was a new continent which I have never been to. All the stars for food as I could notice nothing more there as the food stole the show.

I have always liked this restaurant. The Calcutta Club is one place for authentic Bengali Cuisine at reasonable prices. The taste of food is quite good. Yummy. My favorite dish here is the SHUTKI. It is awesome. I love going here and would visit again soon. The staff is friendly and the interior is different.

A small restaurant mainly subsisting on delivery. Bengali food that's just Ok. Veg menu is limited. Most of the combos in menu are removed and dishes are available individually. Cutlery and plating is nice. Bengali fritters absent in the menu. Playlist is nostalgic and staff very polite.

If u looking to enjoy a authentic Calcutta meal then this place is the ideal place to visit.With no frills this place is a pleasure of the great tasty of food and value of money dinning experince .Food here is served in brass plates and some great Bengali classical music playing in the background .Making the dinning experince more authentic. We ordered the ru fish mutton cutlet chicken curry and lacha paraths with a basket of puris .All dishes were yummy .to end our meal we had rosogula with malai to enjoy the sweetness of Calcutta. Anand the steward who served us gave us  good suggestion and served us well.Do give this place a visit guys

Ma , papa all your mates and FOOD which calls you back home . This place somewhat helps you to go back in a moment to all that you have left while leaving for Mumbai . Being from Calcutta , I can assure you , this place just takes you to all those places in Kolkata where you might have had mutton, fish , chicken , biriyani  etc . Even if you're not from calcutta or not a bong you will relish all the dishes they offer you at such rates. 
Though found golbari mutton not equal to the dish it refers to , still tasteful enough to tickle your taste buds . luchi/Puri, I think is pretty round and fluffy.,except the price is slightly on the higher side for a bong like me , who's regular diet is luchi and don't feel like paying 99 bucks for 4 pieces of it. 
Would suggest not to try mishti doi / dahi untill and unless it's fresh . As it is sweet curd , it should not  be old and go on to higher fermentation , which makes it sour .
Still , as I have said earier , the space having all Calcutta like images and good choice of old Bengali music , will take you back and may make  you nostalgic and sad . But the food will surely bring you back to reality and give you a sensation of eternal happiness which is filled with lots of mishti doi and patishapta .

Please visit and enjoy the eternal delicacy of Bengal.

restaurants.address: shop no 96, cadell road , near hinduja hospital, Shivaji Park, Mahim (W), Asavari, Mahim, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400016, India

reviews.text: This place is located near Shivaji park due to which it is easy to locate. This place can be considered as an heaven for those guys who prefer having deserts. Ambience is pretty amazing with artistic interiors. They do have variety of deserts which are available at affordable rates. Due to this outlet being pocket friendly, you‚Äôll see a lot of teenage crowd visiting this place.  This place is always over crowded due to its peak location. Service is a bit slow, but the quality of food being served over here makes up for it. Overall a pretty good place go spend time with your loved ones.
You get continental food a lot here, but try fries, I just loved them with cheesy garlic dip. As the name suggest Chocolate heaven, this is one. Definitely try a dessert, you will not regret.

The Chocolate heaven ,appropriate to its name was heavenly place. We started of with some nice shakes. Ferrero Rocher Shake and Toblerone Shake true to their name were beautifully made and tasted amazing. 100% recommended to have these when you visit here.
Then we have the Spinach Tartlets. It had the appropriate amount of Spinach, corn and cheese. So yummy and also healthy!!
Then we had the awesome Grilled cottage cheese Burger. It was so crispy and yummy. The exact amount of spice with side of fries. It is a perfect meal.
Then the most amazing thing was the Pesto Blooming Bread. With amazing Pesto filling in the bread with creamy cheese topped on it, it was a finger-licking meal.
We ended our meal with classic Maple Waffle. With sweet as heaven Maple syrup with some vanilla icecream on side. It was the best!!

Ambiance-4/5
Food-5/5
Service-5/5

I haven't visited this place quite often but it's a great place for people who have sweet tooth or dessert lovers. They have varieties of desserts and they are pocket friendly plus delicious. When I went to this place we ordered the Belgian chocolate waffle which is ofc chocolaty and is served with vanilla ice cream ü•∞I'm a huge waffle lover so according to me these were amazing tho. The service is pretty good. Also the ambience is pretty well. So it's a big yes for a great recommendation!!!

Chocolate Heaven is like real heaven for the chocolate lovers. This places has 3-4 branches in Mumbai. I choose to try their mahim branch. It's on padder road before hinduja hospital opposite to Coffee by di bella.

The place is quite cute.the interior and decor is very nice with 7-8 tables.staff and the service is very fast. Here they have not just chocolate items but all kind of others food items too like pizza, pasta, and waffles and many more.

We ordered  - 

1] Mac and cheese pasta - this dish can never go wrong on the world. It was served with 2 garlic breads and quantity was also very good (5/5).

2] Makhni Blooming Bread - it was the best item I had from many days...its a cheese pull bread with paneer inside it. (5/5).

3] Baked Hot Chocolate - so this very nice a tux we ordered this because I didn't wanted to have something with ice cream. So this was a cup of full of cream and choco chpis on it and if u eat all the cream you will get brownie at the down. It was mouthwatering (5/5).

So if you are a chocolate lover and crazy for chocolate dishes then it's actually heaven for you.

restaurants.address: Shop No. 1, Ground Floor, Vallabh Vihar, MG Road, opp. Kotak Mahindra Bank, Rajawadi Colony, Ghatkopar East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400077, India

reviews.text: Some of the dishes get too complicated to understand and the servers themselves get confused. Getting a table here during normal times was not very easy. Still a good hang out place with good desserts. Worth a visit

The food is good. The ambience is great! Service is a bit slow but its fine. Its a must visit f or chocolate lovers as the name suggests. Sundaes and shakes are the best. Its not noisy or crowded. Ambient and great to have conversations over a cup of coffee, a glass of shake or some dessert.

Amazing place for chocolate loversüòã
Pizza and pasta was average
But pancakes were amazing 
Worth all hype. Must visit

A small cafe located in Ghatkopar. Food is good. Pastries are bit sweet. 
The cafe also has indoor games like zenga, taboo...
Only problem is that when its crowded, then it becomes noisy
Awesome place.. love with choclate nd cool ambiance.. happy happy

restaurants.address: Shah Industrial Estate, Opposite to Huntsman Building, Bus Stop, Saki Vihar Rd, next to John Baker, Ganesh Nagar, Marol, Andheri East, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400072, India

reviews.text: Been here thrice! Food is good. The kale Greek pizza being my personal favourite. Try their in house kraft beers! The manager was kind enough to give us a tour of their distillery and we had a opportunity to talk about the entire beer making process with him at length. Live music was good. DJ after the live music was decent.. although not many people come to the dance floor, so you need to initiate on a working day! Had office team dinners here twice.

food is good, cider is amazing, they had live band the day i dropped in and it was great. Nachos was really loaded and amazing. they have ample seating and staff is very courteous. had a good friday night experience. you might want to reserve as they are usually full during weekends.

The best part was i got to taste 6 different flavour of beer..  Some of them was nice in taste... The ambiance and food is also good...  With different live band performing every time.. And yes  best DJ music will make you sway your body and your legs would be out of control...  
Over fun place  to be visited with friends and family
Apart from food they also serve live Cockroaches mixed in food...pls always scan their food before consuming!!

This is a fun place. They have live music every night. And I have played with many of my music acts at The Finch. Their hospitality for artists is good. The staff is also quite helpful. From an artist's perspective this place is amazing cause the stage is acoustically very superior and well designed. It's a very pleasant experience to perform there. Food is also good here. And I believe they have Zomato gold for drinks.

restaurants.Cuisines: Fast Food, North Indian, Indian, Sandwich, Desserts, Juices
restaurants.address: Shop No. 13, Sterling CHSL, Sundervan Complex Rd, Sundervan Complex, Lokhandwala Complex, Andheri West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400053, India

reviews.text: Always a delight to have food rich in taste and herbs. The food never disappoints. Margarita pizza and creamy pasta is a must try.

It's a small cafe...

Cosy interior.. the best thing is the see through kitchen.. you can see how your order is been prepared..

All orders are freshly prepared..
As the orders are prepared freshly you have to wait a bit longer, I personally didn't mind waiting..

We had been to a few of their outlets before this one and we have always been satisfied with them. This time, we visited their Andheri outlet and it is slightly bigger than the other outlets we have visited. We seated ourselves in their casual but cool ambience and moved onto ordering dishes from a lot of sections.

We started off with the Broccoli Cheese soup. This soup was served in a mug and looked creamy. The aroma was soothing and as we sipped onto it, we realized that it was indeed food for the soul. There were tiny bits of broccoli along with other veggies and a hint of oregano with a cheesy texture. It was just amazing.

Next one was the Cheese Garlic Bread. This one was made on the base of a rusk like bread. It was thick and had a hint of sweetness. It was topped with a bed of cheese and garlic with a generous amount of butter. The topping was good but the proportions were not balanced. They could probably use a different kind of bread as a base for this one.

The Quattro Formage Pesto Risotto was absolutely heavenly. Quattro Fromage essentially means four cheese and this dish was true to its name. The refreshing flavor of basil pesto along with the filling texture of cheese made this one just perfect. It was served with a side of garlic bread which sort of complemented the dish and completed it as well. It was one of the best pesto risottos that we have had.

The Margherita Wheat Wafer Pizza over here has great flavor. It had a tangy base of Marguerite sauce over a paper thin wafer. It was flavored with basil and a balance of tomato and cheese. The taste is amazing here but the quantity of this one was quite less for the price. They could work on that for sure.

Lastly, we ended our meal with the Brownie shake. The brownie shake was loaded with chocolate and brownie crumbs. It was topped with chocolate sauce and was frothy and chilling. It was cool and good. The place serves some of the best pastas and risottos. If you are looking for a soulful delight while enjoying these, you should definitely try this one out!

Ambience: 3/5
Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5

Visited Italy in a box Lokhandwala outlet. This one is newly opened hence not very crowded, yet!
Italian food is favourite hence I am quite fussy when the experience is not right, Italy in a box on the other hand was a great experience.
What draws your attention first is an amazing interior of this place and the boxes in which they serve food.
Though it looks small, mind you the quantity is quite filling (I am dead serious about this)
Food that we tried
Premivera piquante pink sauce rissoto - Spicy yet filled with flavours. This was undoubtedly the best and you should not miss it! 
Quottro formage - as the name suggests it comes with white sauce made up of 4 types of cheese. Try it only if you like cheese. Needless to say I LOVE cheese hence loved this pasta! 
Pesto pizza - the unique point about their pizza is the crust!
It's a 7" pizza sufficient for one person. If you like thin wafer crusts, this one is just a star in the menu! Choose only 2-3 toppings. I added 5 which overpowered the taste of pesto sauce.
Desserts - in desserts we tried brownie which was good!
Nutella shake - this one was surprisingly good. Not too sweet and you get to enjoy it without facing 'on your face' kind of a sweetness.

Service and cost wise Italy in a box is definitely good! If you love Italian food I am sure you would love this.
Small cosy place with good food.

restaurants.address: Opp Sterling Theatre, Murzabaan Streeet, Azad Maidan, Fort, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400001, India

reviews.text: The Goose and Gridiron is a decent pub located opposite Sterling Cinema. They have an open air outdoor seating and an AC indoor area. Their Continental food is better than their Indian or Chinese dishes and they have a good enough selection of alcohol. Prices are a bit expensive for the kind of taste and service provided.

It is nice finding that place where you can just go and relax......A Cool place to Hang out with friends..... Good food and nice ambiance....... Tried white wine char grilled prawns it's good enough..... Staff is very friendly.
The second time i tried square Pizza and chicken Roulade.

A wonderful place tucked away in the bylanes close to VT station. 
There is both indoor and outdoor seating. Both with its own special touch. Inside walls are covered with pictures and art. There is a bit of nostalgia in the air. Outdoor seating is more of a gazebo garden setting. Well lit and fresh. 
Food and drinks available here. The service was good and quick. Menu is very British.  All in all had a wonderful experience at this place.

This is located in Fort. The ambience is very good. Sitting is unique. Friendly staff. Good variety in menu. The quality of food is good and higenic. The quantity is good. Nice place to visit with family and friends. I liked the cheesecake very much, It just melted in my mouth.

Becoming a Go2 place in CST area. Good selection of booze. Decent food. Service time needs improvement but staff is courteous. Food selection is slightly short on veg stuff but can survive the evening. Non veg is just fine. Until next visit üëç

restaurants.address: 3, Oskar Classic Building, Malad - Marve Rd, Malad, Orlem, Malad West, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400064, India

reviews.text: Small place with self service. Service in restaurant is not quick. Take away orders quicker. Portions are small compared to pricing.

restaurants.address: 29, 1st Floor, Marine Plaza Hotel, Marine Dr, Churchgate, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400020, India

reviews.text:
The Oriental Blossom ‚ô•Ô∏è

Another amazing restuarant of Mumbai is off my Bucket List now. Finally got an opportunity to visit The Oriental Blossom and we were lucky enough to visit during the Claypot Menu which is being done in the month of August.

It's located in the Hotel Marine Plaza exactly opposite Marine Drive. You get to dine with a beautiful view of the sea. The ambience is super just like a Chinese diner.

The Staff is excellent and very efficient. Stud Vijay attended our table and helped us choose some really good dishes from the Menu.

***Cocktails***

We tried Chandon Delice and Chandon Mojito. Two amazing Wine drinks made using the special Chandon Sparkling Wine.

***Appetizers***

We tried a variety of dishes like Dumplings, Prawns in Salt & Pepper, Fillet Pomfret Garlic Chilly and Crispy Schezwan Lamb. We loved the dumplings especially the Prawns variant and also Prawns and Lamb appetizers.

***Main Course***

And finally the main thing that we loved here were their Claypots. We tried Braised Pomfret Claypot and Prosperity Chicken Claypot in XO Sauce. Two equally different but amazing dishes. 

***Desserts***

Desserts were a perfect end to one of the best Lunch that I have had in recent times. We tried the Philadelphia Cheesecake and Kahlua Triamisu. Both the deseertst were simply delicious and mind-blowing.

I surely recommend Chinese Food Lovers to visit The Oriental Blossom in the month of August to try their Claypots.

Food: 5/5
Staff: 5/5
Ambience: 5/5
Value for Money: 5/5

Awesome, delicious food, courteous staff, nice ambience and lovely cocktails. Located bang on Marine drive, restaurant is located on 1st floor of Hotel Marine Plaza, easy to locate, U turn allowed at traffic junction opposite hotel,valet parking etc etc. Must try

One of the Best Fine Dining experience we had in a long time and the most important part is that it's complemented with our most favourite Chinese cuisine .

Marine Plaza has always given us fond memories as a couple . From our stay after marriage to the great brunch at bay view and now once again this amazing experience at The Oriental Blossom .

It's a ideal place to visit to celebrate your special occasion without a second thought .

Our recommendations for you from their humungous menu :

Manchow Soup and Lemon Corrainder Soup are definitely to savour from the soup section .

Jade Rolls is their signature version of spring roll and is something which you shouldn't miss out when out here for sure .

Steamed Tofu and Fresh Mushrooms with chill soya sauce .
An appetizer for all you mushroom lovers out there .

Stuffed Potatoes with Hot Garlic Sauce & Haka Noodles are the most amazing mains to go for .

Cocktails :

Chandon Mojito is the most unique and luscious drink to enjoy with those appetizers .

Mimosa and Tom Collins are the excellent classic cocktails not to be missed while having your meal out here .

Dessert : 

Darsaan with Vanilla Icecream . Honey laden crisp noodles with Vanilla Icecream marked just a perfect end to this special eve.

Thank You for Reading my Review .

Food : 8/10
Servings : 9/10  
Ambience : 9/10 
Service : 9/10 
VFM : 8/10 

USP : A pure fine dine place with almost authentic Chinese food. Chinese food lovers should try this place once. 

Its a typical fine dine place. This place is mostly filled with the tourists who are from Far east those who want to eat authentic Chinese food. There are are 2 private tables which has capacity of about 6-7 people. The food served is very good and the portions are also enough for 2 people. 

Jade Rolls with Spinach and Shredded : 8/10
Fried Rice : 8/10
Vegetable in burnt garlic gravy : 10/10
Very good ambience,  had called for a reservation. Good food and good service.

reviews.text: It's a South Indian fusion place. The test platter is interesting to get a feel for the different sauces and flavoured rice's offered. The cocktails were good I love the Thalaiva(Rum). My go to appetizer is the gun powdered idlis.

The biggest confusion is to decide on what to eat. At Tanjore, you don't need to stress about it because they let you taste the various gravies before you order the same. The staff explains the origin of each and every sample while you savour them. A must-visit for all South-Indian food lovers!  All I can say is that they have put in a lot of efforts to create their unique menu and I was quite delighted with my experience here. The decor too, is really beautiful and loved the music that surrounded the place.

I went here on a friend‚Äôs recommendation and found this place a delight. They have both indoor and outdoor seating area and we picked outdoor as the atmosphere was better. The staff is super friendly and their service quality exceptional. Everything suggested by them turned out really good. We had the yam cutlets and molagapodi idli for starters, both were very well made. But the highlight is the main course where they offer you a platter with all their Gravy and rice varieties and you can choose the main course by tasting. Then they tell what they can make with the gravy. The dish turned out super delicious and we ended the meal with their kheer which was an apt end to a great meal!

The food is good. The way they start serving and gave choices is different from any other restaurants. You can choose the gravy according to your taste and your choice. Different taste but really good taste. Specialty in South Indian.üëç Coconut gravy is best for try.

Delicious veg food..
Amazingly awesome non veg food..
Calm and Cozy beautifully decorated place..
Courteous staff..
Deserves multiple visits..

The Third House is situated in Andheri lokandanwala its an Dilevery pickup as well as offers A/C dine in that is open from 11:30 Am to 3:30 Pm and then 7 Pm to 4:30 AM so This outlet is ready to serve to all your MIdnight cravings and after party meals.

Coming to what we had:

Chicken tikka slider : Highlights packing was amazing the slider was intact . Sliders are my personal favourite since the gravy is already stuffed im the naan. It tastes blissful.
Love at first Bite.‚ù§. (Reccomended)

starter: Lahsuni chicken : This is their House speciality and comes is an abundance . Nearly 8-9 pieces of soft and juicy chicken this was tossed in lahusi gravy and has a perfect blend of spices and texture . (Reccomended)

Mains: chicken Tikka masala with Butter naan : Again the Quantity was amazing also it serves 4 we ordered 4 butter naan . Naan was also sent in an abudance. Gravy was thick . Also it wasnt much oily . And it had boneless chunks of chicken as well as Inform them you want extra spicy.

Biryani : Murgh Tikka biryani (serves 4) comes with curd and BEST PART IS MASALA AND PLAIN RICE IS IN EQUAL QUANTITY AND CHICKEN IS NOT COMPROMISED. very few outlets Provides this. (Reccomended)

Dessert: Gulab jamun 2 mouth watering pieces of Gulab jamun sent and prepared with Love.

Highlights : Quantity in chicken is not compromised . Pieces are Huge and Boneless.
Also packing is intact and Delivery was Before Time. Also they provide chucks of greeny chutney and salads.

This is a HIGH RECCOMENDATION from my side.

Overall
Quality and Quantity 5/5
Service 5/5
Rates 5/5

reviews.text: We were lucky that we were able to meet up with the owner of this place. It's a beautiful 3 tabled restaurant in Borivali offering lip-smacking European snacks like fries, pasta, burgers etc. We ordered chicken popcorn, cheese chicken burger and vegetable pasta. The food was just amazing and portions were quite big. The taste was really good and we just finished it off in a jiffy. The service was also top notch. The waiter even helped me out with ordering their best dishes. Overall its a very good joint for snacking. Really recommend it to everyone.

The quality and quantity of food is too good. The pizza was aptly loaded with cheese and didn't gave an impression of overloaded one. The restaurant is pocket friendly and avg. cost for 2 is 350/-rs. I rate it as 4/5 stars.

Awesome.. I had chicken stuffed omelet and chicken steak.. Loved it ‚ù§Ô∏è

Must try.
The name 'tiny' speaks itself about the place.. Comfortable and lit üëå
Five stars.. Cheers

Tiny Texas is true to its name. Tiny. However, the food and overall quality is mighty. The three table caf√© serves a good variety of Barbeque and grill dishes, which I guess resemble to that of Texan cuisine.

Menu isn't over the top, much of it is available, and the flavors are punched in for that added effect. The best part about lies in the fact that it is quiet. Apart from the non-blaring music, you can eat in peace.

There isn't much of a staff here, so the service is quite personal with the owners, who suggest the appropriate dishes and the quantity you need to order.

Plus point to the portion sizes and the subsequent cost, which makes this place a value for money joint.

reviews.text: The restaurant is casual and clean. The place was crowded and the seating was a little tight. We ordered a large butter garlic crab, a Bombay duck which is a pan fried filet of fish and grilled jumbo prawns. Everything was all so tasty. I highly recommended this place.

Trishna is a very famous fish restaurant in Mumbai.  They serve crab prawns fish and other sea food in the most delicious sauces it's a place we must visit. We had garlic nan with a prawn dish made in garlic and butter this was followed by crab made in a tomato sauce and finished with a cream caramel

If you like seafood you definitely have to make this a stop. They have crab, giant prawns and other types of seafood. I had the tandoori prawns, butter garlic prawns, and garlic chili squid. All were exceptional. They also have a full bar and quite a few vegetarian entrees. The service is great and I would definitely come back.

This place serves delicious and fresh seafood. The butter garlic crab was to die for. Ambience is great too. We didn't have prior reservation but there was absolutely no waiting time. There's so much more in the menu that I'd like to try. Definitely going back there.

Why is there no 6 stars?? Oh let me start with the best one. Butter garlic crab. Highly recommended. Followed by the hyderabadi fish. To die for. The food is mind blowing. If in Mumbai u need to go for it

reviews.text:
Had been to purchase some delicious food stuff from this store however the people working there are giving less product (NET WT) than what is ordered and paid for. Beware consumers to check weight properly and ask shop to exclude the packaging weight from the actual product weight.

It's high time for Trupti farsan to stop doing these things.

Consumer pays for actual weighed (NET) product excluding it's packaging (GROSS WT). However at this and other stores one feels cheated when the store gives less product to the tune of minimum 30grams less without excluding the packaging weight.

Here are definitions for consumers ready reference:
Gross weight¬†is the total¬†weight¬†of the shipment, including the raw products, its packaging, pallets, containers, and¬†weight¬†of transport vehicle.¬†Net weight¬†refers to the¬†weight¬†of the raw product ordered. ... Tare¬†weight¬†forms the basic¬†difference¬†between the¬†gross weight¬†and¬†net weight¬†of a shipment.

Losing its charm.
The eatables are not tasty & fresh as they used to be.
Varieties have increased but the quality has decreased.
Had recently bought farsan which was stale & not at all crispy.
Was very disappointed.
Ordered a few times from here. Samosa & Jalebi are highly recommended. Khandvi too is amazing and so is Khaman dhokla.
Have you had sweet paties ever? This is the single outlet in all of Mumbai where I found this tasty small dumpling is available. And we are waiting for Trupti to come online!
Had purchased methi Pakodas.. Totally put off by the hair found in it

reviews.text: If you are bored of having the same old salted fries at major fast food providers, then consider this place! It has some amazing twists in their fries. We went for the steamed veg as well as paneer momos along with the fried veg momos. None of the momos were seasoned properly. You have to heavily depend on the dipping sauces to enjoy this. The fried momos are slightly better.

You can say that you get what you pay for but I've experienced amazing food at the same price range. Avoid  Yummy Momos if you enjoy good quality food.

reviews.text:
Zaffran has always been favorite place in town.Analyzing the ongoing pandemic, I've ordered some lipsmacking food from Zaffran. The food I've ordered was really very delicious and all the safety precautions were taken. The delivery Menu is quite extensive so I've ordered 

Kurmuri Bhendi Masala : The kurkuri bhendi I tried for the first time, it was nicely fried, crispy ,piping hot, served with some delicious mouthwatering gravy inside.

Dal Makhini : It was delicious, freshly prepared and was delivered hot along with steamed rice. The flavours in Dal Makhni will surely give you the punjabi flavours.

Veg Galouti Kebab : These were patty shaped kebab which had a crispy texture. Taste was delicious and its highly recommended.

Kurmuri Methi Palak Kebab : It is basically a starter which will fully satisfy your taste. This kebab is served along with green chutney which was really very lipsmacking.

Overall the food was good and was delivered with a note of body temperatures of chef's to delivery boy. Food was delivered on time and was welly packed. Looking forward to order some more food from here !!

üî∏We recently had a delicious meal from Zaffran Lower parel branch.

üìçWhat we ordered:

Starters:
üëâAchari Paneer Tikka - Tikka's are something I love a lot and these were exactly the way I like. They were good in size with cooked perfectly from all side.

Mains:
üëâMurg Musallam - A special chicken
curry made by the outlet is winning hearts. This one was extremely good with an amazing curry and good cooked chicken pieces. Full of flavours and would ask everyone to give a try.

üëâDum ghost Handi - Tender and well cooked mutton pieces in a flavourful and spicy tikka masala gravy. Enjoyed it. Recommended.

üëâDum Subz Handi - Fresh mix veggies in a rich and creamy butter gravy. Mildly spiced and perfect. Good to go for veg option.

üî∏The food came in a good quality paper bag which was sealed and each dish was in a different container (microwavable). The food was fresh and at a temperature that we could consume it directly.

üî∏Enjoyed a great meal as all the dishes were awesome. Would highly recommend ordering from Zaffran.

Ordered from here today after long! I've always loved Zaffran for their food. What I ordered:

1 Butter Chicken Roll - Who doesn't love butter chicken? This was really delicious roll and as a starter.

2 Achari Paneer Tikka - This is a good vegetarian appetizer to go for! Classic Paneer Tikka with delicious taste. 

3 Murg Musallam - This was a maincourse, ofcourse. I had this for the first time from here and it was truly pleasing for my appetite. A good one to go with Roti or even Chapati. 

4 Murg Banjara Kabab - This is a chicken starter. Tasted well with the mint chutney. The chutney can be better but the kababs were just perfect. 

Surely gonna try more things from here.

Ordered from here last week for my birthday dinner! I've always loved Zaffran's food when it comes to Non Vegetarian. 
Since Shravan was going on, I decided to order Veg from here because I thought I should try it out. It takes immense pleasure for me to say, I LOVED IT SO MUCH!!!!
It was totally worth ordering from here. Going ahead with what I ordered : 

‚Ä¢ Veg Galouti Kebab (4/5): Absolutely loved these!!! They were so melt-in-mouth kinda soft and delicious. Really good alternative for your Mutton Galouti Kebabsüòã

‚Ä¢ Achari Paneer Tikka (3/5): So this was a main course. Had this with Roti & Naan. The taste was obviously Achari kinda. Really creamy gravy & a decent one!
 
‚Ä¢ Dum Subz Handi (5/5) : This was again a maincourse. Had this with Roti and Naan as well. This was loaded with veggies and paneer, just exactly the way I love it. Was a bit spicy but that totally improved the taste‚ù§Ô∏è

‚Ä¢ Dal Makhani (4/5): I ordered this with steam rice (ofcourse). It was buttery and thick. A bit sweet but was really really delicious üòã

It was such nicely packed, felt so safe while accepting the delivery of this food. It's a must try outlet, not only for Non Veg food but also Veg. 

Cheersüçª

While having some  irrresitible Mughlai Food Cravings we started our hunt and came across this place called Zaffran and immediately decided to get our craving fulfilled 

With an Array of Options it was extremely difficult to choose dishes but ended up ordering some lip smacking ones ,and decided to hop into Main Course straight since we were super hungry to begin with we called for Murgh Biryani ,it was extremely rich and flavorful also the aroma of it would literally get you drooling a total must have from here, next to go along with Biryani we called for Murgh Mussalam a heavy creamy gravy, with the goodness of boneless chicken and authentic spices also a total recommendation here ,in Veg we called for Dum Sabz Handi which was one of best one I had , loaded with good amount of veggies and paneer this will surely get your tummies full and lastly we called for some Dal Makhani which was extremely rich and tasty

Overall this place is heaven for Meat Lovers and Paradise for Veg Lovers too , with their thrilling options to choose from one will easily love this place and should definitely order from here
